const e=JSON.parse(`[{"id":"alam2024detection","title":"Detection Made Easy: Potentials of Large Language Models for Solidity Vulnerabilities","authors":"Alam, Md Tauseef and Halder, Raju and Maiti, Abyayananda","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2409.10574","abstract":"The large-scale deployment of Solidity smart contracts on the Ethereum mainnet has increasingly attracted financially-motivated attackers in recent years. A few now-infamous attacks in Ethereum's history includes DAO attack in 2016 (50 million dollars lost), Parity Wallet hack in 2017 (146 million dollars locked), Beautychain's token BEC in 2018 (900 million dollars market value fell to 0), and NFT gaming blockchain breach in 2022 ($600 million in Ether stolen). This paper presents a comprehensive investigation of the use of large language models (LLMs) and their capabilities in detecting OWASP Top Ten vulnerabilities in Solidity. We introduce a novel, class-balanced, structured, and labeled dataset named VulSmart, which we use to benchmark and compare the performance of open-source LLMs such as CodeLlama, Llama2, CodeT5 and Falcon, alongside closed-source models like GPT-3.5 Turbo and GPT-4o Mini. Our proposed SmartVD framework is rigorously tested against these models through extensive automated and manual evaluations, utilizing BLEU and ROUGE metrics to assess the effectiveness of vulnerability detection in smart contracts. We also explore three distinct prompting strategies-zero-shot, few-shot, and chain-of-thought-to evaluate the multi-class classification and generative capabilities of the SmartVD framework. Our findings reveal that SmartVD outperforms its open-source counterparts and even exceeds the performance of closed-source base models like GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 Mini. After fine-tuning, the closed-source models, GPT-3.5 Turbo and GPT-4o Mini, achieved remarkable performance with 99% accuracy in detecting vulnerabilities, 94% in identifying their types, and 98% in determining severity. Notably, SmartVD performs best with the \`chain-of-thought' prompting technique, whereas the fine-tuned closed-source models excel with the \`zero-shot' prompting approach.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["fine-tuning","solidity"],"summary":"Proposes SmartVD framework benchmarking LLMs on Solidity OWASP Top Ten vulnerabilities using VulSmart dataset, achieving 99% detection accuracy after fine-tuning GPT-4o Mini.","summary_zh":"提出SmartVD框架，使用VulSmart数据集对LLM在Solidity OWASP十大漏洞上进行基准测试，微调GPT-4o Mini后检测准确率达99%。","abstract_zh":"以太坊主网上Solidity智能合约的大规模部署近年来越来越多地吸引了有经济动机的攻击者。本文全面研究了LLM在检测Solidity中OWASP十大漏洞方面的能力。引入VulSmart数据集，对开源LLM和闭源模型进行基准测试。SmartVD框架通过BLEU和ROUGE指标评估。探索了零样本、少样本和思维链三种提示策略。SmartVD优于开源模型，微调后闭源模型达99%检测准确率、94%类型识别和98%严重性判定。","contributions":["Introduces VulSmart, a class-balanced labeled dataset for Solidity smart contract OWASP Top Ten vulnerability detection.","Proposes the SmartVD framework and benchmarks it against CodeLlama, Llama2, CodeT5, Falcon, GPT-3.5 Turbo, and GPT-4o Mini.","Evaluates three prompting strategies: zero-shot, few-shot, and chain-of-thought for multi-class vulnerability classification.","Achieves 99% accuracy in vulnerability detection, 94% in type identification, and 98% in severity determination after fine-tuning.","Demonstrates chain-of-thought prompting works best for SmartVD while zero-shot works best for fine-tuned closed-source models."],"contributions_zh":["引入VulSmart，一个用于Solidity智能合约OWASP十大漏洞检测的类别均衡标注数据集。","提出SmartVD框架，并与CodeLlama、Llama2、CodeT5、Falcon、GPT-3.5 Turbo和GPT-4o Mini对比。","评估零样本、少样本和思维链三种提示策略用于多类漏洞分类。","微调闭源模型后，漏洞检测准确率达99%，类型识别94%，严重性判定98%。","思维链提示对SmartVD效果最佳，零样本提示对微调闭源模型效果最佳。"],"system_name":"SmartVD","experiment":{"language":["Solidity"],"platform":["Ethereum"],"target_domain":["smart-contract"],"llm":["CodeLlama","Llama2","CodeT5","Falcon","GPT-3.5 Turbo","GPT-4o Mini"],"model_family":["llama","codet5","falcon","gpt"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":true,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["VulSmart"],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":["CodeLlama","Llama2","CodeT5","Falcon","GPT-3.5 Turbo","GPT-4o Mini"],"vulnerability_type":["OWASP Top Ten"],"key_results":"99% detection accuracy, 94% type identification, 98% severity determination after fine-tuning","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1},{"id":"asmita2024busybox","title":"Fuzzing BusyBox: Leveraging LLM and Crash Reuse for Embedded Bug Unearthing","authors":"","year":2024,"venue":"USENIX Security'24","abstract":"BusyBox, an open-source software bundling over 300 essential Linux commands into a single executable, is ubiquitous in Linux-based embedded devices. Vulnerabilities in BusyBox can have far-reaching consequences, affecting a wide array of devices. This research, driven by the extensive use of BusyBox, delved into its analysis. The study revealed the prevalence of older BusyBox versions in real-world embedded products, prompting us to conduct fuzz testing on BusyBox. Fuzzing, a pivotal software testing method, aims to induce crashes that are subsequently scrutinized to uncover vulnerabilities. Within this study, we introduce two techniques to fortify software testing. The first technique enhances fuzzing by leveraging Large Language Models (LLM) to generate target-specific initial seeds. Our study showed a substantial increase in crashes when using LLM-generated initial seeds, highlighting the potential of LLM to efficiently tackle the typically labor-intensive task of generating target-specific initial seeds. The second technique involves repurposing previously acquired crash data from similar fuzzed targets before initiating fuzzing on a new target. This approach streamlines the time-consuming fuzz testing process by providing crash data directly to the new target before commencing fuzzing. We successfully identified crashes in the latest BusyBox target without conducting traditional fuzzing, emphasizing the effectiveness of LLM and crash reuse techniques in enhancing software testing and improving vulnerability detection in embedded systems. Additionally, manual triaging was performed to identify the nature of crashes in the latest BusyBox.","paperUrl":"https://www.usenix.org/system/files/sec24fall-prepub-1014-asmita.pdf","codeUrl":"https://github.com/asmitaj08/FuzzingBusyBox_LLM","slidesUrl":"https://www.usenix.org/system/files/usenixsecurity24_slides-asmita.pdf","talkUrl":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=amzgAEWqQ5s","categories":["fuzzing"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Leverages LLM-generated initial seeds and crash reuse to enhance BusyBox fuzzing, substantially increasing crash discovery in embedded Linux systems.","summary_zh":"利用LLM生成的初始种子和崩溃重用来增强BusyBox模糊测试，大幅提高嵌入式Linux系统中的崩溃发现率。","abstract_zh":"BusyBox是一个开源软件，将300多个基本Linux命令打包到单个可执行文件中。本研究利用LLM生成特定目标的初始种子来增强模糊测试，并引入崩溃重用技术。成功在最新BusyBox中识别了崩溃，突显了LLM和崩溃重用在嵌入式系统漏洞检测中的有效性。","contributions":["Proposes using LLMs to generate target-specific initial seeds for fuzzing BusyBox, substantially increasing crash counts.","Introduces a crash reuse technique that repurposes crash data from similar fuzzed targets to accelerate testing.","Successfully identifies crashes in the latest BusyBox without traditional fuzzing by combining LLM and crash reuse.","Performs manual triaging to identify the nature of crashes in the latest BusyBox version.","Reveals the prevalence of older BusyBox versions in real-world embedded products."],"contributions_zh":["提出使用LLM生成针对BusyBox的特定目标初始种子进行模糊测试，大幅增加崩溃数量。","引入崩溃重用技术，将类似模糊目标的崩溃数据重新用于加速新目标测试。","结合LLM和崩溃重用技术，无需传统模糊测试即可识别最新BusyBox中的崩溃。","执行手动分类以识别崩溃性质。","揭示旧版BusyBox在实际嵌入式产品中的普遍存在。"],"experiment":{"language":["C"],"platform":["Linux","IoT"],"target_domain":["software-vulnerability"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Substantially increased crashes using LLM-generated seeds; identified crashes in latest BusyBox without traditional fuzzing","real_world_impact":"Identified crashes in the latest BusyBox version","open_source":true,"cost":""},"recommendation":3},{"id":"bae2024enhancing","title":"Enhancing software code vulnerability detection using gpt-4o and claude-3.5 sonnet: A study on prompt engineering techniques","authors":"Bae, Jaehyeon and Kwon, Seoryeong and Myeong, Seunghwan","year":2024,"venue":"Electronics","abstract":"This study investigates the efficacy of advanced large language models, specifically GPT-4o, Claude-3.5 Sonnet, and GPT-3.5 Turbo, in detecting software vulnerabilities. Our experiment utilized vulnerable and secure code samples from the NIST Software Assurance Reference Dataset (SARD), focusing on C++, Java, and Python. We employed three distinct prompting techniques as follows: Concise, Tip Setting, and Step-by-Step. The results demonstrate that GPT-4o and Claude-3.5 Sonnet significantly outperform GPT-3.5 Turbo in vulnerability detection. GPT-4o showed the highest improvement with the Step-by-Step prompt, achieving an F1 score of 0.9072. Claude-3.5 Sonnet exhibited consistent high performance across all prompt types, with its Step-by-Step prompt yielding the best overall results (F1 score: 0.8933, AUC: 0.74). In contrast, GPT-3.5 Turbo showed minimal performance changes across prompts, with the Tip Setting prompt performing best (AUC: 0.65, F1 score: 0.6772), yet significantly lower than the other models. Our findings highlight the potential of advanced models in enhancing software security and underscore the importance of prompt engineering in optimizing their performance.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Evaluates GPT-4o, Claude-3.5 Sonnet, and GPT-3.5 Turbo on SARD C++/Java/Python vulnerability detection using three prompting techniques, with GPT-4o achieving F1 0.9072.","summary_zh":"评估GPT-4o、Claude-3.5 Sonnet和GPT-3.5 Turbo在SARD C++/Java/Python漏洞检测上的表现，GPT-4o达到F1值0.9072。","abstract_zh":"本研究调查了GPT-4o、Claude-3.5 Sonnet和GPT-3.5 Turbo在检测软件漏洞方面的效果。使用NIST SARD数据集，专注于C++、Java和Python。采用三种提示技术。GPT-4o在逐步型提示下F1达0.9072，Claude-3.5 Sonnet最佳F1为0.8933。","contributions":["Evaluates GPT-4o, Claude-3.5 Sonnet, and GPT-3.5 Turbo on vulnerability detection using NIST SARD dataset across C++, Java, and Python.","Compares three prompting techniques: Concise, Tip Setting, and Step-by-Step for vulnerability detection.","GPT-4o achieves highest F1 score of 0.9072 with Step-by-Step prompting.","Claude-3.5 Sonnet shows consistent high performance with best F1 of 0.8933 and AUC of 0.74.","GPT-3.5 Turbo significantly underperforms with best F1 of 0.6772."],"contributions_zh":["使用NIST SARD数据集在C++、Java和Python上评估三个模型的漏洞检测能力。","比较简洁型、提示设定型和逐步型三种提示技术。","GPT-4o使用逐步型提示达到最高F1值0.9072。","Claude-3.5 Sonnet表现一致优秀，最佳F1值0.8933。","GPT-3.5 Turbo表现明显较差，最佳F1值0.6772。"],"experiment":{"language":["C++","Java","Python"],"platform":[],"target_domain":["software-vulnerability"],"llm":["GPT-4o","Claude-3.5 Sonnet","GPT-3.5 Turbo"],"model_family":["gpt","claude"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["SARD"],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":["GPT-3.5 Turbo"],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"GPT-4o F1: 0.9072; Claude-3.5 Sonnet F1: 0.8933, AUC: 0.74","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":2},{"id":"boi2024smart","title":"Smart contract vulnerability detection: The role of large language model (llm)","authors":"Boi, Biagio and Esposito, Christian and Lee, Sokjoon","year":2024,"venue":"ACM SIGAPP Applied Computing Review","abstract":"Smart contracts are susceptible to various vulnerabilities that can lead to significant financial losses. The usage of tools for vulnerabilities is reducing the threats but presents some limitations related to the approach used by the tool itself. This paper presents a novel approach to smart contract vulnerability detection utilizing Large Language Models (LLMs), as a tool to detect all the vulnerabilities at once. Our proposed tool leverages the advanced natural language processing capabilities of LLMs to analyze smart contract code and identify potential security flaws. By training the LLM on a diverse dataset of known smart contract vulnerabilities and secure coding practices, we enhance its ability to recognize subtle and complex vulnerabilities that traditional static analysis tools might miss. The evaluation of our tool demonstrates its effectiveness in detecting a wide range of vulnerabilities with satisfaction and accuracy, providing developers with a robust mechanism to improve the security of their smart contracts before deployment. This approach signifies a significant advancement in the application of artificial intelligence for blockchain security, highlighting the potential of LLMs to enhance the reliability and safety of decentralized applications.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["fine-tuning","solidity"],"summary":"Proposes an LLM-based tool for detecting all smart contract vulnerabilities simultaneously, leveraging NLP to identify flaws missed by traditional static analysis.","summary_zh":"提出基于LLM的工具同时检测所有智能合约漏洞，利用NLP识别传统静态分析遗漏的安全缺陷。","abstract_zh":"智能合约容易受到各种可能导致重大经济损失的漏洞影响。本文提出利用LLM进行智能合约漏洞检测的新方法，作为一次性检测所有漏洞的工具。评估证明了其在检测各种漏洞方面的有效性。","contributions":["Presents a novel LLM-based approach to detect all smart contract vulnerabilities simultaneously.","Trains the LLM on a diverse dataset of known smart contract vulnerabilities and secure coding practices.","Demonstrates effectiveness in detecting a wide range of vulnerabilities with high accuracy.","Highlights the potential of LLMs to enhance reliability and safety of decentralized applications."],"contributions_zh":["提出新颖的基于LLM方法同时检测所有智能合约漏洞。","在已知漏洞和安全编码实践的多样数据集上训练LLM。","证明在检测各种漏洞方面的有效性和准确性。","突显LLM增强去中心化应用可靠性和安全性的潜力。"],"experiment":{"language":["Solidity"],"platform":["Ethereum"],"target_domain":["smart-contract"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":true,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":2},{"id":"boi2024vulnhunt","title":"VulnHunt-GPT: a Smart Contract vulnerabilities detector based on OpenAI chatGPT","authors":"Boi, Biagio and Esposito, Christian and Lee, Sokjoon","year":2024,"venue":"Proceedings of the 39th ACM/SIGAPP Symposium on Applied Computing","abstract":"Smart contracts are self-executing programs that can run on a blockchain. Due to the fact of being immutable after their deployment on blockchain, it is crucial to ensure their correctness. For this reason, various approaches for static analysis of smart contracts have been proposed, but they may be on the one hand imprecise or on the other hand difficult to train. In this paper, we propose a novel approach for detecting smart contract vulnerabilities using OpenAI’s Generative Pre-trained Transformer 3 (GPT-3) language model. Our approach, called VulntHunt-GPT, uses GPT-3 to examine Ethereum smart contracts in order to identify the most popular vulnerabilities according to OWASP. We train VulntHunt-GPT on a dataset of smart contract functions and vulnerabilities to improve its accuracy. Our experiments show that VulntHunt-GPT outperforms almost all the existing state-of-the-art approaches in detecting a variety of vulnerabilities, including reentrancy attacks, integer overflow, and uninitialized storage. In addition, we conduct a case study to demonstrate the effectiveness of VulntHunt-GPT in detecting real-world smart contract vulnerabilities. We show that VulntHunt-GPT can identify previously unknown vulnerabilities in popular smart contracts, highlighting its potential for improving smart contract security. Our approach provides a promising direction for using natural language processing techniques to improve smart contract security and reduce the risk of smart contract exploits.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["solidity"],"summary":"Proposes VulnHunt-GPT using GPT-3 to detect OWASP vulnerabilities in Ethereum smart contracts, outperforming state-of-the-art in reentrancy, integer overflow, and uninitialized storage.","summary_zh":"提出VulnHunt-GPT，使用GPT-3检测以太坊智能合约中的OWASP漏洞，在重入、整数溢出和未初始化存储方面优于现有方法。","abstract_zh":"智能合约是可在区块链上运行的自执行程序。本文提出使用GPT-3检测智能合约漏洞的新方法VulnHunt-GPT。实验表明其在检测重入、整数溢出等漏洞方面优于现有方法，并能识别流行合约中的未知漏洞。","contributions":["Proposes VulnHunt-GPT, a novel smart contract vulnerability detector based on OpenAI GPT-3.","Trains on a dataset of smart contract functions and vulnerabilities targeting OWASP categories.","Outperforms almost all existing state-of-the-art approaches in detecting reentrancy, integer overflow, and uninitialized storage.","Conducts a case study demonstrating detection of previously unknown vulnerabilities in popular smart contracts."],"contributions_zh":["提出VulnHunt-GPT，基于OpenAI GPT-3的新型智能合约漏洞检测器。","在智能合约函数和漏洞数据集上训练，针对OWASP类别。","在检测重入、整数溢出和未初始化存储漏洞方面优于现有方法。","案例研究证明能检测流行智能合约中的未知漏洞。"],"system_name":"VulnHunt-GPT","experiment":{"language":["Solidity"],"platform":["Ethereum"],"target_domain":["smart-contract"],"llm":["GPT-3"],"model_family":["gpt"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":true,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":["reentrancy","integer-overflow","uninitialized-storage"],"key_results":"Outperforms almost all existing state-of-the-art approaches","real_world_impact":"Identified previously unknown vulnerabilities in popular smart contracts","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":2},{"id":"cao2024llm","title":"LLM-CloudSec: Large Language Model Empowered Automatic and Deep Vulnerability Analysis for Intelligent Clouds","authors":"Cao, Daipeng and Jun, W","year":2024,"venue":"IEEE INFOCOM 2024-IEEE Conference on Computer Communications Workshops (INFOCOM WKSHPS)","abstract":"The advance of intelligent cloud applications has brought attention to potential security vulnerabilities. Vulnerability detection is a critical step in ensuring the security of cloud applications. However, traditional techniques for vulnerability detection, such as static and dynamic analysis, are challenging to apply in heterogeneous cloud environments. Using data-driven methods such as Machine Learning (ML) to automate vulnerability detection in cloud applications shows promise. However, current ML solutions are limited to coarse-grained vulnerability categorization and function-level analysis. Therefore, we propose LLM-CloudSec, an unsupervised approach to fine-grained vulnerability analysis based on the Large Language Model (LLM). LLM-CloudSec uses Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) and the Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE) as an external knowledge base to improve its ability to detect and analyze vulnerabilities. We conduct experiments on the Juliet C++ test suite, and the results show that LLM-CloudSec enables CWE-based vulnerability classification and line-level vulnerability analysis. Additionally, we applied LLM-CloudSec to the D2A dataset, which was collected from real-world scenarios. We obtained 1230 data entries labelled with CWE and detailed vulnerability analysis. To foster related research, we publish our work on https://github.com/DPCa0/LLM-CloudSec.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Proposes LLM-CloudSec using RAG with CWE knowledge base for fine-grained, line-level vulnerability analysis in cloud apps, evaluated on Juliet C++ and D2A datasets.","summary_zh":"提出LLM-CloudSec，使用RAG结合CWE知识库对云应用进行细粒度行级漏洞分析，在Juliet C++和D2A数据集上评估。","abstract_zh":"智能云应用的进步引起了对安全漏洞的关注。提出LLM-CloudSec，使用RAG和CWE作为外部知识库。在Juliet C++和D2A数据集上验证，生成1230个带CWE标签的条目。","contributions":["Proposes LLM-CloudSec, an unsupervised LLM-based approach for fine-grained vulnerability analysis in cloud environments.","Integrates RAG with CWE as external knowledge base to improve detection and classification.","Enables CWE-based vulnerability classification and line-level analysis on Juliet C++ test suite.","Applies to D2A real-world dataset, producing 1230 CWE-labeled entries.","Publishes the tool as open source on GitHub."],"contributions_zh":["提出LLM-CloudSec，无监督的基于LLM的云环境漏洞分析方法。","集成RAG与CWE作为外部知识库。","在Juliet C++测试套件上实现CWE分类和行级分析。","应用于D2A数据集，生成1230个CWE标签条目。","在GitHub上开源发布。"],"system_name":"LLM-CloudSec","experiment":{"language":["C++"],"platform":["cloud"],"target_domain":["software-vulnerability"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["Juliet C++","D2A"],"benchmark_size":"1230 data entries","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Enables CWE-based classification and line-level analysis; produced 1230 labeled entries from D2A","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1},{"id":"cao2024realvul","title":"RealVul: Can We Detect Vulnerabilities in Web Applications with LLM?","authors":"Cao, Di and Liao, Yong and Shang, Xiuwei","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2410.07573","abstract":"The latest advancements in large language models (LLMs) have sparked interest in their potential for software vulnerability detection. However, there is currently a lack of research specifically focused on vulnerabilities in the PHP language, and challenges in extracting samples and processing persist, hindering the model’s ability to effectively capture the characteristics of specific vulnerabilities. In this paper, we present RealVul, the first LLM-based framework designed for PHP vulnerability detection, addressing these issues. By vulnerability candidate detection methods and employing techniques such as normalization, we can isolate potential vulnerability triggers while streamlining the code and eliminating unnecessary semantic information, enabling the model to better understand and learn from the generated vulnerability samples. We also address the issue of insufficient PHP vulnerability samples by improving data synthesis methods. To evaluate RealVul’s performance, we conduct an extensive analysis using five distinct code LLMs on vulnerability data from 180 PHP projects. The results demonstrate a significant improvement in both effectiveness and generalization compared to existing methods, effectively boosting the vulnerability detection capabilities of these models.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["fine-tuning","other"],"summary":"Proposes RealVul, the first LLM-based PHP vulnerability detection framework, using normalization and data synthesis on 180 PHP projects with five code LLMs.","summary_zh":"提出RealVul，首个基于LLM的PHP漏洞检测框架，在180个PHP项目上用五个代码LLM评估。","abstract_zh":"LLM的最新进展引发了对其漏洞检测潜力的兴趣。提出RealVul，首个PHP漏洞检测的LLM框架。通过规范化和数据合成技术，在180个PHP项目上评估五个代码LLM，结果显示显著改进。","contributions":["Introduces RealVul, the first LLM-based framework for PHP vulnerability detection.","Employs normalization techniques to isolate potential vulnerability triggers.","Improves data synthesis methods to address insufficient PHP vulnerability samples.","Evaluates five distinct code LLMs on vulnerability data from 180 PHP projects.","Demonstrates significant improvement in effectiveness and generalization."],"contributions_zh":["引入RealVul，首个专为PHP漏洞检测设计的基于LLM框架。","采用规范化技术隔离潜在漏洞触发点。","改进数据合成方法解决PHP漏洞样本不足。","在180个PHP项目上评估五个代码LLM。","展示显著的有效性和泛化能力改进。"],"system_name":"RealVul","experiment":{"language":["PHP"],"platform":[],"target_domain":["software-vulnerability"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"180 PHP projects","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Significant improvement in effectiveness and generalization over existing methods","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1},{"id":"chatafl2024ndss","title":"Large Language Model guided Protocol Fuzzing","authors":"","year":2024,"venue":"NDSS'24","abstract":"How to find security flaws in a protocol implementation without a machine-readable specification of the protocol? Facing the internet, protocol implementations are particularly security-critical software systems where inputs must adhere to a specific structure and order that is often informally specified in hundreds of pages in natural language (RFC). Without some machine-readable version of that protocol, it is difficult to automatically generate valid test inputs for its implementation that follow the required structure and order. It is possible to partially alleviate this challenge using mutational fuzzing on a set of recorded message sequences as seed inputs. However, the set of available seeds is often quite limited and will hardly cover the great diversity of protocol states and input structures. In this paper, we explore the opportunities of systematic interaction with pre-trained large language models (LLMs), which have ingested millions of pages of human-readable protocol specifications, to draw out machine-readable information about the protocol that can be used during protocol fuzzing. We use the knowledge of the LLMs about protocol message types for well-known protocols. We also checked the LLM’s capability in detecting “states” for stateful protocol implementations by generating sequences of messages and predicting response codes. Based on these observations, we have developed an LLM-guided protocol implementation fuzzing engine. Our protocol fuzzer CHATAFL constructs grammars for each message type in a protocol, and then mutates messages or predicts the next messages in a message sequence via interactions with LLMs. Experiments on a wide range of real-world protocols from PROFUZZBENCH show significant efficacy in state and code coverage. Our LLM- guided stateful fuzzer was compared with state-of-the-art fuzzers AFLNET and NSFUZZ. CHATAFL covers 47.60% and 42.69% more state transitions, 29.55% and 25.75% more states, and 5.81% and 6.74% more code, respectively. Apart from enhanced coverage, CHATAFL discovered nine distinct and previously unknown vulnerabilities in widely-used and extensively-tested protocol implementations while AFLNET and NSFUZZ only discovered three and four of them, respectively.","paperUrl":"https://www.ndss-symposium.org/wp-content/uploads/2024-556-paper.pdf","codeUrl":"https://github.com/ChatAFLndss/ChatAFL","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=31JPvlrXfQ0","categories":["fuzzing"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Proposes ChatAFL, an LLM-guided protocol fuzzer constructing grammars and predicting messages via LLM interaction, covering 47.60% more state transitions and finding 9 new vulnerabilities.","summary_zh":"提出ChatAFL，通过LLM交互构建语法和预测消息，多覆盖47.60%状态转换并发现9个新漏洞。","abstract_zh":"本文探索了与预训练LLM交互来提取协议信息用于模糊测试的机会。ChatAFL为每种消息类型构建语法，通过LLM变异或预测消息。在PROFUZZBENCH上比AFLNET和NSFUZZ显著提升覆盖率，发现9个未知漏洞。","contributions":["Proposes ChatAFL, an LLM-guided protocol fuzzing engine that constructs grammars for protocol message types.","Leverages LLM knowledge about protocol specifications to mutate and predict messages.","Achieves 47.60% more state transitions than AFLNET and 42.69% more than NSFUZZ on PROFUZZBENCH.","Covers 29.55%/25.75% more states and 5.81%/6.74% more code than AFLNET/NSFUZZ.","Discovers 9 previously unknown vulnerabilities in widely-used protocol implementations."],"contributions_zh":["提出ChatAFL，LLM引导的协议模糊测试引擎。","利用LLM关于协议规范的知识来变异和预测消息。","比AFLNET和NSFUZZ分别多覆盖47.60%和42.69%的状态转换。","分别多覆盖29.55%/25.75%的状态和5.81%/6.74%的代码。","在广泛使用的协议实现中发现9个未知漏洞。"],"system_name":"ChatAFL","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["network-protocol"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":["AFLNET","NSFUZZ"],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["PROFUZZBENCH"],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":["AFLNET","NSFUZZ"],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"47.60% more state transitions, 29.55% more states, 5.81% more code coverage than AFLNET","real_world_impact":"Found 9 distinct previously unknown vulnerabilities in widely-used protocol implementations","open_source":true,"cost":""},"recommendation":3},{"id":"chen2023chatgpt","title":"When chatgpt meets smart contract vulnerability detection: How far are we?","authors":"Chen, Chong and Su, Jianzhong and Chen, Jiachi and Wang, Yanlin and Bi, Tingting and Yu, Jianxing and Wang, Yanli and Lin, Xingwei and Chen, Ting and Zheng, Zibin","year":2023,"venue":"ACM Transactions on Software Engineering and Methodology","abstract":"With the development of blockchain technology, smart contracts have become an important component of blockchain applications. Despite their crucial role, the development of smart contracts may introduce vulnerabilities and potentially lead to severe consequences, such as financial losses. Meanwhile, large language models, represented by ChatGPT, have gained great attentions, showcasing great capabilities in code analysis tasks. In this paper, we presented an empirical study to investigate the performance of ChatGPT in identifying smart contract vulnerabilities. Initially, we evaluated ChatGPT’s effectiveness using a publicly available smart contract dataset. Our findings discover that while ChatGPT achieves a high recall rate, its precision in pinpointing smart contract vulnerabilities is limited. Furthermore, ChatGPT’s performance varies when detecting different vulnerability types. We delved into the root causes for the false positives generated by ChatGPT, and categorized them into four groups. Second, by comparing ChatGPT with other state-of-the-art smart contract vulnerability detection tools, we found that ChatGPT’s F-score is lower than others for 3 out of the 7 vulnerabilities. In the case of the remaining 4 vulnerabilities, ChatGPT exhibits a slight advantage over these tools. Finally, we analyzed the limitation of ChatGPT in smart contract vulnerability detection, revealing that the robustness of ChatGPT in this field needs to be improved from two aspects: its uncertainty in answering questions; and the limited length of the detected code. In general, our research provides insights into the strengths and weaknesses of employing large language models, specifically ChatGPT, for the detection of smart contract vulnerabilities.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Empirically evaluates ChatGPT on smart contract vulnerability detection, finding high recall but limited precision, with F-score lower than specialized tools for 3 of 7 types.","summary_zh":"实证评估ChatGPT在智能合约漏洞检测上的表现，发现召回率高但精确率有限，在7种漏洞类型中有3种F值低于专用工具。","abstract_zh":"本文研究了ChatGPT在智能合约漏洞检测中的表现。发现ChatGPT召回率高但精确率有限，与专用工具相比在3/7种漏洞类型上F值较低。局限性包括回答不确定性和代码长度限制。","contributions":["Conducts an empirical study evaluating ChatGPT on smart contract vulnerability detection using a public dataset.","Reveals that ChatGPT achieves high recall but limited precision.","Categorizes root causes of ChatGPT false positives into four groups.","Compares with state-of-the-art tools: lower F-score for 3 of 7 vulnerability types, slight advantage for remaining 4.","Identifies two key limitations: uncertainty in answers and limited code length for detection."],"contributions_zh":["使用公开数据集对ChatGPT进行智能合约漏洞检测的实证研究。","揭示ChatGPT召回率高但精确率有限。","将误报根本原因分为四组。","与工具比较，3种F值较低，4种略有优势。","识别两个关键限制：回答不确定性和代码长度限制。"],"experiment":{"language":["Solidity"],"platform":["Ethereum"],"target_domain":["smart-contract"],"llm":["ChatGPT"],"model_family":["gpt"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"High recall but limited precision; F-score lower than SOTA tools for 3 of 7 vulnerability types","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":2},{"id":"covrl2024issta","title":"Fuzzing JavaScript Interpreters with Coverage-Guided Reinforcement Learning for LLM-Based Mutation","authors":"","year":2024,"venue":"ISSTA'24","abstract":"JavaScript interpreters, crucial for modern web browsers, require an effective fuzzing method to identify security-related bugs. However, the strict grammatical requirements for input present significant challenges. Recent efforts to integrate language models for context- aware mutation in fuzzing are promising but lack the necessary coverage guidance to be fully effective. This paper presents a novel technique called CovRL (Coverage-guided Reinforcement Learning) that combines Large Language Models (LLMs) with Reinforcement Learning (RL) from coverage feedback. Our fuzzer, CovRL-Fuzz, integrates coverage feedback directly into the LLM by leveraging the Term Frequency-Inverse Document Frequency (TF-IDF) method to construct a weighted coverage map. This map is key in calculating the fuzzing reward, which is then applied to the LLM-based mutator through reinforcement learning. CovRL-Fuzz, through this approach, enables the generation of test cases that are more likely to discover new coverage areas, thus improving bug detection while minimizing syntax and semantic errors, all without needing extra post-processing. Our evaluation results show that CovRL-Fuzz outperforms the state-of-the-art fuzzers in enhancing code coverage and identifying bugs in JavaScript interpreters: CovRL-Fuzz identified 58 real-world security-related bugs in the latest JavaScript interpreters, including 50 previously unknown bugs and 15 CVEs.","paperUrl":"https://dl.acm.org/doi/pdf/10.1145/3650212.3680389","codeUrl":"https://github.com/seclab-yonsei/CovRL-Fuzz","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["fuzzing"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Proposes CovRL-Fuzz combining LLM-based mutation with coverage-guided RL via TF-IDF, finding 58 real-world bugs including 50 new bugs and 15 CVEs in JavaScript interpreters.","summary_zh":"提出CovRL-Fuzz，结合LLM变异和覆盖引导强化学习，在JavaScript解释器中发现58个漏洞含50个新漏洞和15个CVE。","abstract_zh":"JavaScript解释器需要有效的模糊测试方法。提出CovRL，将LLM与覆盖反馈的强化学习结合。CovRL-Fuzz识别了58个安全漏洞，含50个未知漏洞和15个CVE。","contributions":["Proposes CovRL, combining LLM-based mutation with coverage-guided reinforcement learning.","Uses TF-IDF to construct weighted coverage map for computing fuzzing rewards via RL.","Generates test cases more likely to discover new coverage while minimizing syntax/semantic errors.","Outperforms state-of-the-art fuzzers in code coverage and bug detection for JavaScript interpreters.","Identifies 58 real-world security bugs including 50 previously unknown and 15 CVEs."],"contributions_zh":["提出CovRL，将LLM变异与覆盖引导强化学习结合。","使用TF-IDF构建加权覆盖图计算模糊测试奖励。","生成更可能发现新覆盖的测试用例。","在JavaScript解释器测试中优于最先进模糊测试器。","识别58个安全漏洞，含50个新漏洞和15个CVE。"],"system_name":"CovRL-Fuzz","experiment":{"language":["JavaScript"],"platform":[],"target_domain":["software-vulnerability"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"58 real-world security bugs, 50 previously unknown, 15 CVEs","real_world_impact":"Found 50 previously unknown bugs and 15 CVEs in latest JavaScript interpreters","open_source":true,"cost":""},"recommendation":3},{"id":"ding2024vulnerability","title":"Vulnerability detection with code language models: How far are we?","authors":"Ding, Yangruibo and Fu, Yanjun and Ibrahim, Omniyyah and Sitawarin, Chawin and Chen, Xinyun and Alomair, Basel and Wagner, David and Ray, Baishakhi and Chen, Yizheng","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2403.18624","abstract":"In the context of the rising interest in code language models (code LMs) and vulnerability detection, we study the effectiveness of code LMs for detecting vulnerabilities. Our analysis reveals significant shortcomings in existing vulnerability datasets, including poor data quality, low label accuracy, and high duplication rates, leading to unreliable model performance in realistic vulnerability detection scenarios. Additionally, the evaluation methods used with these datasets are not representative of real-world vulnerability detection.\\nTo address these challenges, we introduce PrimeVul, a new dataset for training and evaluating code LMs for vulnerability detection. PrimeVul incorporates a novel set of data labeling techniques that achieve comparable label accuracy to human-verified benchmarks while significantly expanding the dataset. It also implements a rigorous data de-duplication and chronological data splitting strategy to mitigate data leakage issues, alongside introducing more realistic evaluation metrics and settings. This comprehensive approach aims to provide a more accurate assessment of code LMs' performance in real-world conditions.\\nEvaluating code LMs on PrimeVul reveals that existing benchmarks significantly overestimate the performance of these models. For instance, a state-of-the-art 7B model scored 68.26% F1 on BigVul but only 3.09% F1 on PrimeVul. Attempts to improve performance through advanced training techniques and larger models like GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 were unsuccessful, with results akin to random guessing in the most stringent settings. These findings underscore the considerable gap between current capabilities and the practical requirements for deploying code LMs in security roles, highlighting the need for more innovative research in this domain.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["fine-tuning"],"summary":"Introduces PrimeVul dataset with rigorous labeling and deduplication, revealing SOTA 7B model drops from 68.26% F1 on BigVul to 3.09% on PrimeVul; GPT-3.5/GPT-4 near random.","summary_zh":"引入PrimeVul数据集，SOTA 7B模型从BigVul上68.26% F1降至PrimeVul上3.09%；GPT-3.5/GPT-4接近随机。","abstract_zh":"研究代码语言模型在漏洞检测中的有效性。引入PrimeVul数据集，采用新型标注技术和去重策略。SOTA 7B模型在BigVul上68.26% F1，但在PrimeVul上仅3.09%。GPT-3.5和GPT-4在最严格设置下接近随机。","contributions":["Reveals significant shortcomings in existing vulnerability datasets: poor quality, low label accuracy, high duplication.","Introduces PrimeVul with novel labeling techniques achieving human-verified benchmark-comparable accuracy.","Implements rigorous data deduplication and chronological splitting to mitigate data leakage.","Shows SOTA 7B model drops from 68.26% F1 on BigVul to 3.09% F1 on PrimeVul.","Demonstrates GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 perform akin to random guessing under stringent settings."],"contributions_zh":["揭示现有漏洞数据集的重大缺陷。","引入PrimeVul，标签准确率与人工验证基准相当。","实施严格去重和按时间分割。","SOTA 7B模型从BigVul 68.26% F1降至PrimeVul 3.09%。","GPT-3.5/GPT-4在最严格设置下接近随机。"],"system_name":"PrimeVul","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["software-vulnerability"],"llm":["GPT-3.5","GPT-4"],"model_family":["gpt"],"model_size":["7B"],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["BigVul","PrimeVul"],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"SOTA 7B model: 68.26% F1 on BigVul but 3.09% F1 on PrimeVul; GPT-3.5/GPT-4 near random guessing","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1},{"id":"du2024generalization","title":"Generalization-Enhanced Code Vulnerability Detection via Multi-Task Instruction Fine-Tuning","authors":"Du, Xiaohu and Wen, Ming and Zhu, Jiahao and Xie, Zifan and Ji, Bin and Liu, Huijun and Shi, Xuanhua and Jin, Hai","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2406.03718","abstract":"Code Pre-trained Models (CodePTMs) based vulnerability detection have achieved promising results over recent years. However, these models struggle to generalize as they typically learn superficial mapping from source code to labels instead of understanding the root causes of code vulnerabilities, resulting in poor performance in real-world scenarios beyond the training instances. To tackle this challenge, we introduce VulLLM, a novel framework that integrates multi-task learning with Large Language Models (LLMs) to effectively mine deep-seated vulnerability features. Specifically, we construct two auxiliary tasks beyond the vulnerability detection task. First, we utilize the vulnerability patches to construct a vulnerability localization task. Second, based on the vulnerability features extracted from patches, we leverage GPT-4 to construct a vulnerability interpretation task. VulLLM innovatively augments vulnerability classification by leveraging generative LLMs to understand complex vulnerability patterns, thus compelling the model to capture the root causes of vulnerabilities rather than overfitting to spurious features of a single task. The experiments conducted on six large datasets demonstrate that VulLLM surpasses seven state-of-the-art models in terms of effectiveness, generalization, and robustness.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["fine-tuning"],"summary":"Proposes VulLLM integrating multi-task learning with LLMs for vulnerability detection via localization and GPT-4-generated interpretation tasks, surpassing 7 SOTA models on 6 datasets.","summary_zh":"提出VulLLM，将多任务学习与LLM集成，通过定位和GPT-4解释任务，在6个数据集上超越7个SOTA模型。","abstract_zh":"基于代码预训练模型的漏洞检测难以泛化。提出VulLLM，集成多任务学习与LLM。构建漏洞定位和GPT-4解释两个辅助任务。在六个数据集上超越七个SOTA模型。","contributions":["Proposes VulLLM, integrating multi-task learning with LLMs for vulnerability detection.","Constructs vulnerability localization auxiliary task using patches.","Leverages GPT-4 to construct vulnerability interpretation auxiliary task.","Compels model to capture root causes rather than overfitting to spurious features.","Surpasses 7 SOTA models in effectiveness, generalization, and robustness on 6 datasets."],"contributions_zh":["提出VulLLM，将多任务学习与LLM集成。","利用补丁构建漏洞定位辅助任务。","利用GPT-4构建漏洞解释辅助任务。","迫使模型捕获漏洞根本原因。","在6个数据集上超越7个SOTA模型。"],"system_name":"VulLLM","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["software-vulnerability"],"llm":["GPT-4"],"model_family":["gpt"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":true,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"6 large datasets","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Surpasses 7 SOTA models in effectiveness, generalization, and robustness on 6 datasets","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1},{"id":"fang2024llm","title":"Llm agents can autonomously exploit one-day vulnerabilities","authors":"Fang, Richard and Bindu, Rohan and Gupta, Akul and Kang, Daniel","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2404.08144","abstract":"LLMs have becoming increasingly powerful, both in their benign and malicious uses. With the increase in capabilities, researchers have been increasingly interested in their ability to exploit cybersecurity vulnerabilities. In particular, recent work has conducted preliminary studies on the ability of LLM agents to autonomously hack websites. However, these studies are limited to simple vulnerabilities. In this work, we show that LLM agents can autonomously exploit one-day vulnerabilities in real-world systems. To show this, we collected a dataset of 15 one-day vulnerabilities that include ones categorized as critical severity in the CVE description. When given the CVE description, GPT-4 is capable of exploiting 87% of these vulnerabilities compared to 0% for every other model we test (GPT-3.5, open-source LLMs) and open-source vulnerability scanners (ZAP and Metasploit). Fortunately, our GPT-4 agent requires the CVE description for high performance: without the description, GPT-4 can exploit only 7% of the vulnerabilities. Our findings raise questions around the widespread deployment of highly capable LLM agents.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Demonstrates GPT-4 agents can autonomously exploit 87% of 15 real-world one-day CVEs given descriptions, while GPT-3.5, open-source LLMs, ZAP, and Metasploit exploit 0%.","summary_zh":"GPT-4代理在给定描述时能自主利用15个一日漏洞中的87%，其他模型和工具利用率为0%。","abstract_zh":"展示LLM代理可自主利用真实系统中的一日漏洞。GPT-4能利用87%，其他模型和工具为0%。无CVE描述时仅7%。","contributions":["Collects a dataset of 15 real-world one-day vulnerabilities including critical severity CVEs.","Demonstrates GPT-4 agents autonomously exploit 87% of vulnerabilities when given CVE descriptions.","Shows all other models (GPT-3.5, open-source LLMs) and scanners (ZAP, Metasploit) achieve 0%.","Reveals GPT-4 can only exploit 7% without CVE descriptions.","Raises questions about security implications of deploying capable LLM agents."],"contributions_zh":["收集15个包含关键严重性CVE的一日漏洞数据集。","GPT-4代理在给定CVE描述时能利用87%的漏洞。","其他模型和扫描器利用率为0%。","无CVE描述时GPT-4仅能利用7%。","提出部署高能力LLM代理的安全问题。"],"experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["software-vulnerability"],"llm":["GPT-4","GPT-3.5"],"model_family":["gpt"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":["ZAP","Metasploit"],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"15 one-day vulnerabilities","baselines":["GPT-3.5","open-source LLMs","ZAP","Metasploit"],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"GPT-4 exploits 87% of CVEs with description, 7% without; all others 0%","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1},{"id":"fang2024teams","title":"Teams of LLM Agents can Exploit Zero-Day Vulnerabilities","authors":"Fang, Richard and Bindu, Rohan and Gupta, Akul and Zhan, Qiusi and Kang, Daniel","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2406.01637","abstract":"LLM agents have become increasingly sophisticated, especially in the realm of cybersecurity. Researchers have shown that LLM agents can exploit real-world vulnerabilities when given a description of the vulnerability and toy capture-the-flag problems. However, these agents still perform poorly on real-world vulnerabilities that are unknown to the agent ahead of time (zero-day vulnerabilities).\\nIn this work, we show that teams of LLM agents can exploit real-world, zero-day vulnerabilities. Prior agents struggle with exploring many different vulnerabilities and long-range planning when used alone. To resolve this, we introduce HPTSA, a system of agents with a planning agent that can launch subagents. The planning agent explores the system and determines which subagents to call, resolving long-term planning issues when trying different vulnerabilities. We construct a benchmark of 15 real-world vulnerabilities and show that our team of agents improve over prior work by up to 4.5×.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Introduces HPTSA, a hierarchical planning team of LLM agents with subagent delegation, achieving up to 4.5x improvement over prior work on 15 real-world zero-day vulnerabilities.","summary_zh":"引入HPTSA，带有子代理委派的分层规划LLM代理团队，在15个零日漏洞上提高最多4.5倍。","abstract_zh":"LLM代理在网络安全领域越来越复杂。引入HPTSA，带规划代理和子代理的系统。在15个真实漏洞上比先前工作提高最多4.5倍。","contributions":["Demonstrates teams of LLM agents can exploit real-world zero-day vulnerabilities.","Introduces HPTSA with a planning agent that launches specialized subagents.","Resolves long-term planning issues via hierarchical agent architecture.","Constructs a benchmark of 15 real-world vulnerabilities.","Achieves up to 4.5x improvement over prior single-agent approaches."],"contributions_zh":["证明LLM代理团队能利用零日漏洞。","引入HPTSA，规划代理启动专业子代理。","通过分层架构解决长期规划问题。","构建15个真实漏洞的基准。","比先前单代理方法提高最多4.5倍。"],"system_name":"HPTSA","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["software-vulnerability"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"15 real-world vulnerabilities","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":["zero-day"],"key_results":"Up to 4.5x improvement over prior single-agent approaches","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1},{"id":"fu2023chatgpt","title":"Chatgpt for vulnerability detection, classification, and repair: How far are we?","authors":"Fu, Michael and Tantithamthavorn, Chakkrit Kla and Nguyen, Van and Le, Trung","year":2023,"venue":"2023 30th Asia-Pacific Software Engineering Conference (APSEC)","abstract":"Large language models (LLMs) like ChatGPT (i.e., gpt-3.5-turbo and gpt-4) exhibited remarkable advancement in a range of software engineering tasks associated with source code such as code review and code generation. In this paper, we undertake a comprehensive study by instructing ChatGPT for four prevalent vulnerability tasks: function and line-level vulnerability prediction, vulnerability classification, severity estimation, and vulnerability repair. We compare ChatGPT with state-of-the-art language models designed for software vulnerability purposes. Through an empirical assessment employing extensive real-world datasets featuring over 190,000 C/C++ functions, we found that ChatGPT achieves limited performance, trailing behind other language models in vulnerability contexts by a significant margin. The experimental outcomes highlight the challenging nature of vulnerability prediction tasks, requiring domain-specific expertise. Despite ChatGPT's substantial model scale, exceeding that of source code-pre-trained language models (e.g., CodeBERT) by a factor of 14,000, the process of fine-tuning remains imperative for ChatGPT to generalize for vulnerability prediction tasks. We publish the studied dataset, experimental prompts for ChatGPT, and experimental results at https://github.com/awsm-research/ChatGPT4Vul.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Evaluates ChatGPT (GPT-3.5/GPT-4) on vulnerability detection, classification, severity estimation, and repair using 190,000+ C/C++ functions, finding it trails fine-tuned CodeBERT.","summary_zh":"评估ChatGPT在漏洞检测、分类、严重性评估和修复上的表现，使用19万+C/C++函数，落后于微调的CodeBERT。","abstract_zh":"ChatGPT在代码相关任务中表现出色。本文评估其在四个漏洞任务上的表现，使用19万+C/C++函数。发现其明显落后于微调模型，强调微调的重要性。","contributions":["Evaluates ChatGPT on four tasks: function/line-level prediction, classification, severity estimation, and repair.","Uses datasets with over 190,000 C/C++ functions.","Finds ChatGPT trails behind domain-specific fine-tuned models by a significant margin.","Highlights that despite 14,000x larger scale than CodeBERT, fine-tuning remains imperative.","Publishes dataset, prompts, and results on GitHub."],"contributions_zh":["评估ChatGPT在四个漏洞任务上的表现。","使用超过19万个C/C++函数的数据集。","ChatGPT明显落后于领域特定微调模型。","尽管规模是CodeBERT的14000倍，微调仍至关重要。","在GitHub上发布数据集和结果。"],"experiment":{"language":["C","C++"],"platform":[],"target_domain":["software-vulnerability"],"llm":["GPT-3.5 Turbo","GPT-4"],"model_family":["gpt","codebert"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"190,000+ C/C++ functions","baselines":["CodeBERT"],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"ChatGPT trails behind fine-tuned domain-specific models by a significant margin","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":2},{"id":"fuzz_meets_llm_survey2024","title":"When Fuzzing Meets LLMs: Challenges and Opportunities","authors":"","year":2024,"venue":"FSE'24","abstract":"Fuzzing, a widely-used technique for bug detection, has seen advancements through Large Language Models (LLMs). Despite their potential, LLMs face specific challenges in fuzzing. In this paper, we identified five major challenges of LLM-assisted fuzzing. To support our findings, we revisited the most recent papers from top-tier conferences, confirming that these challenges are widespread. As a remedy, we propose some actionable recommendations to help improve applying LLM in Fuzzing and conduct preliminary evaluations on DBMS fuzzing. The results demonstrate that our recommendations effectively address the identified challenges.","paperUrl":"https://dl.acm.org/doi/pdf/10.1145/3663529.3663784","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["fuzzing"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Identifies five major challenges of LLM-assisted fuzzing from top-tier conference papers and proposes actionable recommendations validated on DBMS fuzzing.","summary_zh":"从顶级会议论文中识别LLM辅助模糊测试的五大挑战，提出在DBMS模糊测试上验证的建议。","abstract_zh":"模糊测试是广泛使用的漏洞检测技术。本文识别LLM辅助模糊测试的五大挑战，提出建议并在DBMS模糊测试上验证。","contributions":["Identifies five major challenges of LLM-assisted fuzzing through systematic review.","Revisits recent top-tier conference papers to confirm these challenges.","Proposes actionable recommendations to improve LLM application in fuzzing.","Conducts preliminary evaluations on DBMS fuzzing demonstrating effectiveness."],"contributions_zh":["识别LLM辅助模糊测试的五大挑战。","审视顶级会议论文确认挑战普遍性。","提出改善LLM在模糊测试中应用的建议。","在DBMS模糊测试上进行初步评估。"],"experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["software-vulnerability"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":3},{"id":"gao2023far","title":"How far have we gone in vulnerability detection using large language models","authors":"Gao, Zeyu and Wang, Hao and Zhou, Yuchen and Zhu, Wenyu and Zhang, Chao","year":2023,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2311.12420","abstract":"As software becomes increasingly complex and prone to vulnerabilities, automated vulnerability detection is critically important, yet challenging. Given the significant successes of Large Language Models (LLMs) in various tasks, there is growing anticipation of their efficacy in vulnerability detection. However, a quantitative understanding of their potential in vulnerability detection is still missing. To bridge this gap, we introduce a comprehensive vulnerability benchmark VulBench. This benchmark aggregates high-quality data from a wide range of CTF (Capture-the-Flag) challenges and real-world applications, with annotations for each vulnerable function detailing the vulnerability type and its root cause. Through our experiments encompassing 16 LLMs and 6 state-of-the-art (SOTA) deep learning-based models and static analyzers, we find that several LLMs outperform traditional deep learning approaches in vulnerability detection, revealing an untapped potential in LLMs. This work contributes to the understanding and utilization of LLMs for enhanced software security.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Introduces VulBench benchmark aggregating CTF and real-world data, evaluating 16 LLMs and 6 SOTA deep learning models/static analyzers, finding LLMs outperform traditional DL.","summary_zh":"引入VulBench基准，评估16个LLM和6个SOTA深度学习模型/静态分析器，发现LLM优于传统DL方法。","abstract_zh":"引入VulBench漏洞基准，从CTF和真实应用中聚合高质量数据。评估16个LLM和6个SOTA模型，发现多个LLM优于传统方法。","contributions":["Introduces VulBench, aggregating data from CTF challenges and real-world applications.","Provides annotations for each vulnerable function detailing type and root cause.","Evaluates 16 LLMs and 6 SOTA deep learning models and static analyzers.","Finds several LLMs outperform traditional deep learning approaches.","Reveals untapped potential in LLMs for enhanced software security."],"contributions_zh":["引入VulBench，聚合CTF和真实世界数据。","为每个漏洞函数提供类型和根因注释。","评估16个LLM和6个SOTA模型。","多个LLM优于传统深度学习方法。","揭示LLM在软件安全方面的潜力。"],"system_name":"VulBench","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["software-vulnerability"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["VulBench"],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Several LLMs outperform traditional deep learning approaches in vulnerability detection","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1},{"id":"ghosh2024cve","title":"CVE-LLM: Automatic vulnerability evaluation in medical device industry using large language models","authors":"Ghosh, Rikhiya and Farri, Oladimeji and von Stockhausen, Hans-Martin and Schmitt, Martin and Vasile, George Marica","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2407.14640","abstract":"The healthcare industry is currently experiencing an unprecedented  wave of cybersecurity attacks, impacting millions of individuals. With the discovery of thousands of vulnerabilities each month,  there is a pressing need to drive the automation of vulnerability  assessment processes for medical devices, facilitating rapid mitigation efforts. Generative AI systems have revolutionized various  industries, offering unparalleled opportunities for automation and  increased efficiency. This paper presents a solution leveraging  Large Language Models (LLMs) to learn from historical evaluations  of vulnerabilities for the automatic assessment of vulnerabilities in  the medical devices industry. This approach is applied within the  portfolio of a single manufacturer, taking into account device characteristics, including existing security posture and controls. The  primary contributions of this paper are threefold. Firstly, it provides  a detailed examination of the best practices for training a vulnerability Language Model (LM) in an industrial context. Secondly, it  presents a comprehensive comparison and insightful analysis of the  effectiveness of Language Models in vulnerability assessment. Finally, it proposes a new human-in-the-loop framework to expedite  vulnerability evaluation processes.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Presents CVE-LLM leveraging LLMs trained on historical evaluations for automatic vulnerability assessment in medical devices, proposing a human-in-the-loop framework.","summary_zh":"提出CVE-LLM，利用历史评估训练LLM进行医疗设备自动漏洞评估，提出人机协同框架。","abstract_zh":"医疗行业正经历网络安全攻击浪潮。提出利用LLM从历史评估中学习，用于医疗设备自动漏洞评估。提供训练最佳实践、全面比较和人机协同框架。","contributions":["Provides best practices for training a vulnerability LM in industrial context.","Comprehensive comparison of LM effectiveness in medical device vulnerability assessment.","Proposes a human-in-the-loop framework to expedite vulnerability evaluation.","Addresses automation needs for medical device vulnerability assessment."],"contributions_zh":["提供工业环境中训练漏洞语言模型的最佳实践。","全面比较语言模型在医疗设备漏洞评估中的有效性。","提出人机协同框架加速漏洞评估。","解决医疗设备漏洞评估自动化需求。"],"system_name":"CVE-LLM","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["medical-device"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":true,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1},{"id":"gonccalves2024scope","title":"Scope: Evaluating llms for software vulnerability detection","authors":"Gon{\\\\c{c","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2407.14372","abstract":"In recent years, code security has become increasingly important, especially with the rise of interconnected technologies. Detecting vulnerabilities early in the software development process has demonstrated numerous benefits. Consequently, the scientific community started using machine learning for automated detection of source code vulnerabilities. This work explores and refines the CVEFixes dataset, which is commonly used to train models for code-related tasks, specifically the C/C++ subset. To this purpose, the Source Code Processing Engine (SCoPE), a framework composed of strategized techniques that can be used to reduce the size and normalize C/C++ functions is presented. The output generated by SCoPE was used to create a new version of CVEFixes. This refined dataset was then employed in a feature representation analysis to assess the effectiveness of the tool's code processing techniques, consisting of fine-tuning three pre-trained LLMs for software vulnerability detection. The results show that SCoPE successfully helped to identify 905 duplicates within the evaluated subset. The LLM results corroborate with the literature regarding their suitability for software vulnerability detection, with the best model achieving 53% F1-score.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["fine-tuning"],"summary":"Proposes SCoPE framework for C/C++ code normalization, refines CVEFixes dataset by identifying 905 duplicates, and fine-tunes three LLMs achieving best 53% F1-score.","summary_zh":"提出SCoPE框架用于C/C++代码规范化，识别905个重复项，微调三个LLM达到最佳53% F1值。","abstract_zh":"提出SCoPE框架用于C/C++代码规范化，改进CVEFixes数据集并识别905个重复。微调三个LLM进行漏洞检测，最佳53% F1。","contributions":["Proposes SCoPE for reducing size and normalizing C/C++ functions.","Refines CVEFixes dataset, identifying 905 duplicates.","Conducts feature representation analysis of code processing techniques.","Fine-tunes three pre-trained LLMs for vulnerability detection.","Best model achieves 53% F1-score."],"contributions_zh":["提出SCoPE用于C/C++函数规范化。","改进CVEFixes数据集，识别905个重复。","进行代码处理技术的特征表示分析。","微调三个预训练LLM进行漏洞检测。","最佳模型达到53% F1值。"],"system_name":"SCoPE","experiment":{"language":["C","C++"],"platform":[],"target_domain":["software-vulnerability"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":true,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["CVEFixes"],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Best model: 53% F1-score; identified 905 duplicates in CVEFixes","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1},{"id":"guo2024outside","title":"Outside the comfort zone: Analysing llm capabilities in software vulnerability detection","authors":"Guo, Yuejun and Patsakis, Constantinos and Hu, Qiang and Tang, Qiang and Casino, Fran","year":2024,"venue":"European symposium on research in computer security","abstract":"The significant increase in software production driven by automation and faster development lifecycles has resulted in a corresponding surge in software vulnerabilities. In parallel, the evolving landscape of software vulnerability detection, highlighting the shift from traditional methods to machine learning and large language models (LLMs), provides massive opportunities at the cost of resource-demanding computations. This paper thoroughly analyses LLMs’ capabilities in detecting vulnerabilities within source code by testing models beyond their usual applications to study their potential in cybersecurity tasks. We evaluate the performance of six open-source models that are specifically trained for vulnerability detection against six general-purpose LLMs, three of which were further fine-tuned on a dataset that we compiled. Our dataset, alongside five state-of-the-art benchmark datasets, were used to create a pipeline to leverage a binary classification task, namely classifying code into vulnerable and non-vulnerable. The findings highlight significant variations in classification accuracy across benchmarks, revealing the critical influence of fine-tuning in enhancing the detection capabilities of small LLMs over their larger counterparts, yet only in the specific scenarios in which they were trained. Further experiments and analysis also underscore the issues with current benchmark datasets, particularly around mislabeling and their impact on model training and performance, which raises concerns about the current state of practice. We also discuss the road ahead in the field suggesting strategies for improved model training and dataset curation.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["fine-tuning"],"summary":"Evaluates 6 vulnerability-specific and 6 general-purpose LLMs (3 fine-tuned) on 5 benchmark datasets for binary vulnerability classification, highlighting fine-tuning benefits for small LLMs.","summary_zh":"在5个基准数据集上评估6个漏洞专用和6个通用LLM，突显微调对小型LLM的优势。","abstract_zh":"分析LLM在源代码漏洞检测中的能力。评估6个漏洞专用和6个通用LLM，3个微调。在5个基准数据集上二分类。微调使小型LLM优于大型模型。","contributions":["Evaluates 6 vulnerability-specific models against 6 general-purpose LLMs.","Fine-tunes 3 general-purpose LLMs on a compiled dataset.","Tests on 5 benchmark datasets using binary classification.","Fine-tuning enhances small LLM detection over larger counterparts in trained scenarios.","Underscores issues with benchmark datasets, particularly mislabeling."],"contributions_zh":["评估6个漏洞专用模型与6个通用LLM。","微调3个通用LLM。","在5个基准数据集上二分类测试。","微调使小型LLM在训练场景中优于大型模型。","突显基准数据集错误标注问题。"],"experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["software-vulnerability"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":true,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"5 benchmark datasets","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Fine-tuning enhances small LLM detection over larger counterparts in trained scenarios","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":2},{"id":"haurogne4925500advanced","title":"Advanced Vulnerability Detection Using Llm with Transparency Obligation Practice Towards Trustworthy Ai","authors":"Haurogn{e","year":2024,"venue":"Available at SSRN 4925500","abstract":"Vulnerabilities in the source code are the primary causes of potential threats in software systems. There are a large number of vulnerabilities published each day, and effective vulnerability detection is critical to identifying and mitigating these vulnerabilities. AI has emerged as a promising solution to enhance vulnerability detection. However, AI-based methods often face challenges with large datasets and understanding the problem's specific context. In this context, the industry and research communities now widely consider the Large Language Model (LLM) to tackle more complex tasks and large datasets. However, LLM also exhibits limitations in terms of explaining the model outcome for a specific context due to its black box nature. To address this challenge, this research introduces an advanced vulnerability detection approach using LLMs, specifically the BERT model. Additionally, the approach introduces key dimensions of transparency obligations, model outcome and explainability, which ensure the transparency of decision-making and trustworthy AI practice. We address the black-box nature of LLMs by employing XAI techniques, particularly SHAP to provide clear explanations for the model’s decisions. We propose an architecture that combines the BERT model with transparency obligation practices, which ensures the assurance of transparency dimensions throughout the entire LLM life cycle. An experiment is performed with a source code dataset to demonstrate the applicability of the proposed approach. The result shows an average accuracy of 69% for the chosen model in vulnerability detection. Moreover, the transparency obligation practice is effectively implemented through the entire lifecycle of the LLM model towards trustworthy AI-enabled system development.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Proposes BERT-based vulnerability detection with XAI (SHAP) transparency obligations for trustworthy AI, achieving average 69% accuracy on source code dataset.","summary_zh":"提出基于BERT的漏洞检测，结合SHAP透明度义务实现可信AI，准确率达69%。","abstract_zh":"本研究引入使用BERT的漏洞检测方法，采用SHAP提供可解释性。提出BERT与透明度义务结合的架构。准确率达69%。","contributions":["Introduces BERT-based vulnerability detection with transparency obligation practices.","Employs SHAP as XAI technique to explain model decisions.","Proposes architecture combining BERT with transparency dimensions for trustworthy AI.","Achieves average accuracy of 69% for vulnerability detection.","Demonstrates transparency practices through entire LLM lifecycle."],"contributions_zh":["引入基于BERT的漏洞检测与透明度义务。","采用SHAP解释模型决策。","提出BERT与透明度维度结合的架构。","漏洞检测平均准确率达69%。","在整个LLM生命周期中展示透明度实践。"],"experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["software-vulnerability"],"llm":["BERT"],"model_family":["bert"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Average accuracy of 69% for vulnerability detection","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1},{"id":"hossain2024malicious","title":"Malicious Code Detection Using LLM","authors":"Hossain, Al Amin and PK, Mithun Kumar and Zhang, Junjie and Amsaad, Fathi","year":2024,"venue":"NAECON 2024-IEEE National Aerospace and Electronics Conference","abstract":"In the context of the rising interest in code language models (code LMs) and vulnerability detection, we study the effectiveness of code LMs for detecting vulnerabilities. Our analysis reveals significant shortcomings in existing vulnerability datasets, including poor data quality, low label accuracy, and high duplication rates, leading to unreliable model performance in realistic vulnerability detection scenarios. Additionally, the evaluation methods used with these datasets are not representative of real-world vulnerability detection.\\nTo address these challenges, we introduce PrimeVul, a new dataset for training and evaluating code LMs for vulnerability detection. PrimeVul incorporates a novel set of data labeling techniques that achieve comparable label accuracy to human-verified benchmarks while significantly expanding the dataset. It also implements a rigorous data de-duplication and chronological data splitting strategy to mitigate data leakage issues, alongside introducing more realistic evaluation metrics and settings. This comprehensive approach aims to provide a more accurate assessment of code LMs' performance in real-world conditions.\\nEvaluating code LMs on PrimeVul reveals that existing benchmarks significantly overestimate the performance of these models. For instance, a state-of-the-art 7B model scored 68.26% F1 on BigVul but only 3.09% F1 on PrimeVul. Attempts to improve performance through advanced training techniques and larger models like GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 were unsuccessful, with results akin to random guessing in the most stringent settings. These findings underscore the considerable gap between current capabilities and the practical requirements for deploying code LMs in security roles, highlighting the need for more innovative research in this domain.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Introduces PrimeVul dataset for code LM vulnerability detection, showing SOTA 7B model drops from 68.26% F1 on BigVul to 3.09% on PrimeVul; GPT-3.5/GPT-4 near random.","summary_zh":"引入PrimeVul数据集，SOTA 7B模型从BigVul 68.26% F1降至PrimeVul 3.09%；GPT-3.5/GPT-4接近随机。","abstract_zh":"研究代码语言模型在漏洞检测中的有效性。引入PrimeVul数据集，SOTA 7B模型在BigVul上68.26% F1但PrimeVul上仅3.09%。GPT-3.5/GPT-4接近随机。","contributions":["Reveals significant shortcomings in existing vulnerability datasets.","Introduces PrimeVul with novel labeling techniques.","Implements rigorous deduplication and chronological splitting.","SOTA 7B model drops from 68.26% F1 on BigVul to 3.09% on PrimeVul.","GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 produce results akin to random guessing."],"contributions_zh":["揭示现有漏洞数据集的重大缺陷。","引入PrimeVul数据集。","实施严格去重和按时间分割。","SOTA 7B模型从68.26% F1降至3.09%。","GPT-3.5/GPT-4接近随机。"],"system_name":"PrimeVul","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["software-vulnerability"],"llm":["GPT-3.5","GPT-4"],"model_family":["gpt"],"model_size":["7B"],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["BigVul","PrimeVul"],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"SOTA 7B model: 68.26% F1 on BigVul but 3.09% F1 on PrimeVul; GPT-3.5/GPT-4 near random guessing","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1},{"id":"hu2023large","title":"Large language model-powered smart contract vulnerability detection: New perspectives","authors":"Hu, Sihao and Huang, Tiansheng and {\\\\.I","year":2023,"venue":"2023 5th IEEE International Conference on Trust, Privacy and Security in Intelligent Systems and Applications (TPS-ISA)","abstract":"This paper provides a systematic analysis of the opportunities, challenges, and potential solutions of harnessing Large Language Models (LLMs) such as GPT-4 to dig out vulnerabilities within smart contracts based on our ongoing research. For the task of smart contract vulnerability detection, achieving practical usability hinges on identifying as many true vulnerabilities as possible while minimizing the number of false positives. Nonetheless, our empirical study reveals contradictory yet interesting findings: generating more answers with higher randomness largely boosts the likelihood of producing a correct answer but inevitably leads to a higher number of false positives. To mitigate this tension, we propose an adversarial framework dubbed GPTL ENS that breaks the conventional one-stage detection into two synergistic stages - generation and discrimination, for progressive detection and refinement, wherein the LLM plays dual roles, i.e., AUDITOR and CRITIC, respectively. The goal of AUDITOR is to yield a broad spectrum of vulnerabilities with the hope of encompassing the correct answer, whereas the goal of CRITIC that evaluates the validity of identified vulnerabilities is to minimize the number of false positives. Experimental results and illustrative examples demonstrate that AUDITOR and CRITIC work together harmoniously to yield pronounced improvements over the conventional one-stage detection. GPTL ENS is intuitive, strategic, and entirely LLM-driven without relying on specialist expertise in smart contracts, showcasing its methodical generality and potential to detect a broad spectrum of vulnerabilities. Our code is available at: https://github.com/git-disl/GPTLens.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"system_name":"GPTLens","summary":"Proposes GPTLens, an adversarial two-stage LLM framework (Auditor+Critic) for smart contract vulnerability detection, improving over one-stage detection.","summary_zh":"提出GPTLens，一种对抗性两阶段LLM框架（审计者+评论者），用于智能合约漏洞检测，优于单阶段检测方法。","contributions":["Proposes GPTLens, a two-stage adversarial framework using LLM as both Auditor and Critic for smart contract vulnerability detection.","Reveals that higher randomness in LLM answers increases true positive rates but also false positives.","Introduces a generation-discrimination pipeline that progressively detects and refines vulnerability findings.","Demonstrates that GPTLens is entirely LLM-driven without requiring specialist smart contract expertise.","Releases open-source code at https://github.com/git-disl/GPTLens."],"contributions_zh":["提出GPTLens，一种使用LLM同时作为审计者和评论者的两阶段对抗框架，用于智能合约漏洞检测。","揭示LLM回答中更高的随机性增加了真阳性率但也增加了误报率。","引入生成-判别流水线，逐步检测和优化漏洞发现结果。","证明GPTLens完全由LLM驱动，无需智能合约专业知识。","在https://github.com/git-disl/GPTLens开源代码。"],"abstract_zh":"本文系统分析了利用GPT-4等大语言模型（LLM）挖掘智能合约漏洞的机遇、挑战和潜在解决方案。对于智能合约漏洞检测任务，实现实际可用性取决于尽可能多地识别真实漏洞，同时最小化误报数量。然而，我们的实证研究揭示了矛盾但有趣的发现：以更高随机性生成更多答案大大提高了产生正确答案的可能性，但不可避免地导致更多误报。为了缓解这种矛盾，我们提出了一个名为GPTLens的对抗框架，将传统的单阶段检测分解为两个协同阶段——生成和判别，进行渐进式检测和优化，其中LLM扮演双重角色，即审计者（AUDITOR）和评论者（CRITIC）。审计者的目标是产生广泛的漏洞范围，以期涵盖正确答案，而评论者评估已识别漏洞有效性的目标是最小化误报数量。实验结果和示例表明，审计者和评论者协同工作，相比传统单阶段检测产生了显著改进。GPTLens直观、策略性强，完全由LLM驱动，不依赖智能合约专业知识，展示了其方法的通用性和检测广泛漏洞的潜力。代码可在https://github.com/git-disl/GPTLens获取。","experiment":{"language":["Solidity"],"platform":[],"target_domain":["smart contracts"],"llm":["GPT-4"],"model_family":["GPT"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"GPTLens with dual Auditor-Critic roles yields pronounced improvements over conventional one-stage detection.","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@inproceedings{hu2023large,\\n  title={Large language model-powered smart contract vulnerability detection: New perspectives},\\n  author={Hu, Sihao and Huang, Tiansheng and others},\\n  booktitle={2023 5th IEEE International Conference on Trust, Privacy and Security in Intelligent Systems and Applications (TPS-ISA)},\\n  year={2023}\\n}"},{"id":"keltek2024lsast","title":"LSAST--Enhancing Cybersecurity through LLM-supported Static Application Security Testing","authors":"Keltek, Mete and Hu, Rong and Sani, Mohammadreza Fani and Li, Ziyue","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2409.15735","abstract":"The current cybersecurity landscape is increasingly complex, with traditional Static Application Security Testing (SAST) tools struggling to capture complex and emerging vulnerabilities due to their reliance on rule-based matching. Meanwhile, Large Language Models (LLMs) have demonstrated powerful code analysis capabilities, but their static training data and privacy risks limit their effectiveness. To overcome the limitations of both approaches, we propose LSAST, a novel approach that integrates LLMs with SAST scanners to enhance vulnerability detection. LSAST leverages a locally hostable LLM, combined with a state-of-the-art knowledge retrieval system, to provide up-to-date vulnerability insights without compromising data privacy. We set a new benchmark for static vulnerability analysis, offering a robust, privacy-conscious solution that bridges the gap between traditional scanners and advanced AI-driven analysis. Our evaluation demonstrates that incorporating SAST results into LLM analysis significantly improves detection accuracy, identifying vulnerabilities missed by conventional methods.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["llm-sast"],"system_name":"LSAST","summary":"Proposes LSAST, integrating a locally-hosted LLM with SAST scanners and knowledge retrieval to improve vulnerability detection while preserving data privacy.","summary_zh":"提出LSAST，将本地托管的LLM与SAST扫描器和知识检索系统集成，在保护数据隐私的同时提高漏洞检测能力。","contributions":["Proposes LSAST, a novel approach integrating LLMs with SAST scanners for enhanced vulnerability detection.","Uses a locally hostable LLM combined with a state-of-the-art knowledge retrieval system to ensure data privacy.","Sets a new benchmark for static vulnerability analysis with a privacy-conscious solution.","Demonstrates that incorporating SAST results into LLM analysis significantly improves detection accuracy."],"contributions_zh":["提出LSAST，一种将LLM与SAST扫描器集成的新方法，用于增强漏洞检测。","使用本地可托管的LLM结合先进的知识检索系统，确保数据隐私。","为静态漏洞分析设立了新的基准，提供了隐私感知的解决方案。","证明将SAST结果纳入LLM分析可显著提高检测准确性。"],"abstract_zh":"当前网络安全形势日益复杂，传统的静态应用安全测试（SAST）工具由于依赖基于规则的匹配，在捕获复杂和新兴漏洞方面面临困难。同时，大语言模型（LLM）展示了强大的代码分析能力，但其静态训练数据和隐私风险限制了其有效性。为了克服这两种方法的局限性，我们提出了LSAST，一种将LLM与SAST扫描器集成以增强漏洞检测的新方法。LSAST利用本地可托管的LLM，结合先进的知识检索系统，在不损害数据隐私的情况下提供最新的漏洞洞察。我们为静态漏洞分析设立了新的基准，提供了一个稳健的、隐私感知的解决方案，弥合了传统扫描器与先进AI驱动分析之间的差距。我们的评估表明，将SAST结果纳入LLM分析可显著提高检测准确性，识别出传统方法遗漏的漏洞。","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":[],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Incorporating SAST results into LLM analysis significantly improves detection accuracy, identifying vulnerabilities missed by conventional methods.","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@article{keltek2024lsast,\\n  title={LSAST--Enhancing Cybersecurity through LLM-supported Static Application Security Testing},\\n  author={Keltek, Mete and Hu, Rong and Sani, Mohammadreza Fani and Li, Ziyue},\\n  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2409.15735},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"khare2023understanding","title":"Understanding the effectiveness of large language models in detecting security vulnerabilities","authors":"Khare, Avishree and Dutta, Saikat and Li, Ziyang and Solko-Breslin, Alaia and Alur, Rajeev and Naik, Mayur","year":2023,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2311.16169","abstract":"While automated vulnerability detection techniques have made promising progress in detecting security vulnerabilities, their scalability and applicability remain challenging. The remarkable performance of Large Language Models (LLMs), such as GPT-4 and CodeLlama, on code-related tasks has prompted recent works to explore if LLMs can be used to detect vulnerabilities. In this paper, we perform a more comprehensive study by concurrently examining a higher number of datasets, languages and LLMs, and qualitatively evaluating performance across prompts and vulnerability classes while addressing the shortcomings of existing tools. Concretely, we evaluate the effectiveness of 16 pre-trained LLMs on 5,000 code samples from five diverse security datasets. These balanced datasets encompass both synthetic and real-world projects in Java and C/C++ and cover 25 distinct vulnerability classes.\\nOverall, LLMs across all scales and families show modest effectiveness in detecting vulnerabilities, obtaining an average accuracy of 62.8% and F1 score of 0.71 across datasets. They are significantly better at detecting vulnerabilities only requiring intra-procedural analysis, such as OS Command Injection and NULL Pointer Dereference. Moreover, they report higher accuracies on these vulnerabilities than popular static analysis tools, such as CodeQL.\\nWe find that advanced prompting strategies that involve step-by-step analysis significantly improve performance of LLMs on real-world datasets in terms of F1 score (by upto 0.18 on average). Interestingly, we observe that LLMs show promising abilities at performing parts of the analysis correctly, such as identifying vulnerability-related specifications and leveraging natural language information to understand code behavior (e.g., to check if code is sanitized). We expect our insights to guide future work on LLM-augmented vulnerability detection systems.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["llm-sast","java","c-cpp"],"system_name":"","summary":"Evaluates 16 pre-trained LLMs on 5,000 code samples across 5 datasets in Java and C/C++, finding 62.8% average accuracy with step-by-step prompting improving F1 by up to 0.18.","summary_zh":"在Java和C/C++的5个数据集上评估16个预训练LLM对5000个代码样本的表现，平均准确率62.8%，逐步提示策略将F1提升最高0.18。","contributions":["Evaluates 16 pre-trained LLMs on 5,000 code samples from five diverse security datasets covering Java and C/C++.","Finds LLMs achieve an average accuracy of 62.8% and F1 score of 0.71 across datasets, with better performance on intra-procedural vulnerabilities.","Shows LLMs report higher accuracies than CodeQL on vulnerabilities like OS Command Injection and NULL Pointer Dereference.","Demonstrates that step-by-step prompting strategies improve F1 score by up to 0.18 on real-world datasets.","Identifies LLM strengths in vulnerability-related specification identification and natural language-based code behavior understanding."],"contributions_zh":["在覆盖Java和C/C++的五个多样化安全数据集上评估了16个预训练LLM对5000个代码样本的表现。","发现LLM在各数据集上平均准确率为62.8%，F1分数为0.71，在过程内漏洞上表现更好。","表明LLM在OS命令注入和空指针解引用等漏洞上的准确率高于CodeQL。","证明逐步提示策略在真实世界数据集上将F1分数提高了最多0.18。","识别了LLM在漏洞相关规范识别和基于自然语言的代码行为理解方面的优势。"],"abstract_zh":"虽然自动化漏洞检测技术在检测安全漏洞方面取得了可喜的进展，但其可扩展性和适用性仍然面临挑战。GPT-4和CodeLlama等大语言模型（LLM）在代码相关任务上的卓越表现促使近期研究探索LLM能否用于检测漏洞。本文通过同时检验更多的数据集、语言和LLM进行了更全面的研究，并在定性评估不同提示和漏洞类别的性能的同时解决了现有工具的不足。具体而言，我们评估了16个预训练LLM在五个多样化安全数据集的5000个代码样本上的有效性。这些平衡数据集涵盖了Java和C/C++的合成和真实世界项目，覆盖25种不同的漏洞类别。总体而言，所有规模和系列的LLM在检测漏洞方面表现一般，在各数据集上获得了62.8%的平均准确率和0.71的F1分数。它们在只需要过程内分析的漏洞检测上明显更好，如OS命令注入和空指针解引用。此外，它们在这些漏洞上的准确率高于流行的静态分析工具如CodeQL。我们发现，涉及逐步分析的高级提示策略在真实世界数据集上显著提高了LLM的F1分数（平均提高了多达0.18）。有趣的是，我们观察到LLM在正确执行部分分析方面展示了有前途的能力，如识别漏洞相关规范和利用自然语言信息理解代码行为。我们期望我们的洞察能指导未来LLM增强漏洞检测系统的研究工作。","experiment":{"language":["Java","C/C++"],"platform":[],"target_domain":[],"llm":["GPT-4","CodeLlama"],"model_family":["GPT","CodeLlama"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":["CodeQL"],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"5,000 code samples from 5 datasets","baselines":["CodeQL"],"vulnerability_type":["OS Command Injection","NULL Pointer Dereference"],"key_results":"Average accuracy of 62.8% and F1 score of 0.71; step-by-step prompting improves F1 by up to 0.18.","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@article{khare2023understanding,\\n  title={Understanding the effectiveness of large language models in detecting security vulnerabilities},\\n  author={Khare, Avishree and Dutta, Saikat and Li, Ziyang and Solko-Breslin, Alaia and Alur, Rajeev and Naik, Mayur},\\n  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2311.16169},\\n  year={2023}\\n}"},{"id":"kholoosi2024qualitative","title":"A Qualitative Study on Using ChatGPT for Software Security: Perception vs. Practicality","authors":"Kholoosi, M Mehdi and Babar, M Ali and Croft, Roland","year":2024,"venue":"2024 IEEE 6th International Conference on Trust, Privacy and Security in Intelligent Systems, and Applications (TPS-ISA)","abstract":"Artificial Intelligence (AI) advancements have enabled the development of Large Language Models (LLMs) that can perform a variety of tasks with remarkable semantic understanding and accuracy. ChatGPT is one such LLM that has gained significant attention due to its impressive capabilities for assisting in various knowledge-intensive tasks. Due to the knowledge-intensive nature of engineering secure software, ChatGPT’s assistance is expected to be explored for security-related tasks during the development/evolution of software. To gain an understanding of the potential of ChatGPT as an emerging technology for supporting software security, we adopted a twofold approach. Initially, we performed an empirical study to analyse the perceptions of those who had explored the use of ChatGPT for security tasks and shared their views on Twitter. It was determined that security practitioners view ChatGPT as beneficial for various software security tasks, including vulnerability detection, information retrieval, and penetration testing. Secondly, we designed an experiment aimed at investigating the practicality of this technology when deployed as an oracle in real-world settings. In particular, we focused on vulnerability detection and qualitatively examined ChatGPT outputs for given prompts within this prominent software security task. Based on our analysis, responses from ChatGPT in this task are largely filled with generic security information and may not be appropriate for industry use. To prevent data leakage, we performed this analysis on a vulnerability dataset compiled after the OpenAI data cut-off date from real-world projects covering 40 distinct vulnerability types and 12 programming languages. We assert that the findings from this study would contribute to future research aimed at developing and evaluating LLMs dedicated to software security.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"system_name":"","summary":"Studies ChatGPT's practicality for vulnerability detection through Twitter perception analysis and experiments on 40 vulnerability types across 12 programming languages.","summary_zh":"通过Twitter感知分析和对40种漏洞类型、12种编程语言的实验，研究ChatGPT在漏洞检测中的实用性。","contributions":["Conducts an empirical study analyzing perceptions of ChatGPT for security tasks from Twitter discussions.","Identifies that security practitioners view ChatGPT as beneficial for vulnerability detection, information retrieval, and penetration testing.","Designs experiments to evaluate ChatGPT's practicality for vulnerability detection on real-world projects.","Evaluates ChatGPT on a dataset compiled after OpenAI's data cut-off date covering 40 vulnerability types and 12 programming languages.","Finds that ChatGPT responses are largely filled with generic security information and may not be appropriate for industry use."],"contributions_zh":["通过分析Twitter讨论，对ChatGPT在安全任务中的感知进行了实证研究。","发现安全从业者认为ChatGPT有助于漏洞检测、信息检索和渗透测试。","设计实验评估ChatGPT在真实世界项目漏洞检测中的实用性。","在OpenAI数据截止日期之后编译的数据集上评估ChatGPT，涵盖40种漏洞类型和12种编程语言。","发现ChatGPT的回复主要充满通用安全信息，可能不适合工业使用。"],"abstract_zh":"人工智能（AI）的进步推动了能够以出色的语义理解和准确性执行各种任务的大语言模型（LLM）的发展。ChatGPT是一个因其在协助各种知识密集型任务方面的出色能力而受到广泛关注的LLM。由于工程安全软件的知识密集特性，预计将探索ChatGPT在软件开发/演进过程中对安全相关任务的辅助。为了了解ChatGPT作为支持软件安全的新兴技术的潜力，我们采用了双重方法。首先，我们进行了一项实证研究，分析了那些探索过使用ChatGPT进行安全任务并在Twitter上分享观点的人的看法。研究确定安全从业者认为ChatGPT有助于各种软件安全任务，包括漏洞检测、信息检索和渗透测试。其次，我们设计了一个实验，旨在调查这项技术在真实世界环境中作为预言机部署时的实用性。特别是，我们专注于漏洞检测，并对ChatGPT在这一重要软件安全任务中给定提示的输出进行了定性检查。根据我们的分析，ChatGPT在此任务中的回复主要充满了通用的安全信息，可能不适合工业使用。为防止数据泄露，我们在OpenAI数据截止日期之后从真实世界项目编译的漏洞数据集上进行了此分析，涵盖40种不同的漏洞类型和12种编程语言。我们认为这项研究的发现将有助于未来旨在开发和评估专用于软件安全的LLM的研究。","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":[],"llm":["ChatGPT"],"model_family":["GPT"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"40 vulnerability types, 12 programming languages","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"ChatGPT responses are largely generic security information, not appropriate for industry use in vulnerability detection.","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@inproceedings{kholoosi2024qualitative,\\n  title={A Qualitative Study on Using ChatGPT for Software Security: Perception vs. Practicality},\\n  author={Kholoosi, M Mehdi and Babar, M Ali and Croft, Roland},\\n  booktitle={2024 IEEE 6th International Conference on Trust, Privacy and Security in Intelligent Systems, and Applications (TPS-ISA)},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"kouliaridis2024assessing","title":"Assessing the Effectiveness of LLMs in Android Application Vulnerability Analysis","authors":"Kouliaridis, Vasileios and Karopoulos, Georgios and Kambourakis, Georgios","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2406.18894","abstract":"The increasing frequency of attacks on Android applications coupled with the recent popularity of large language models (LLMs) necessitates a comprehensive understanding of the capabilities of the latter in identifying potential vulnerabilities, which is key to mitigate the overall risk. To this end, the work at hand compares the ability of nine state-of-the-art LLMs to detect Android code vulnerabilities listed in the latest Open Worldwide Application Security Project (OWASP) Mobile Top 10. Each LLM was evaluated against an open dataset of over 100 vulnerable code samples, including obfuscated ones, assessing each model's ability to identify key vulnerabilities. Our analysis reveals the strengths and weaknesses of each LLM, identifying important factors that contribute to their performance. Additionally, we offer insights into context augmentation with retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) for detecting Android code vulnerabilities, which in turn may propel secure application development. Finally, while the reported findings regarding code vulnerability analysis show promise, they also reveal significant discrepancies among the different LLMs.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"system_name":"","summary":"Compares 9 LLMs on detecting Android vulnerabilities from OWASP Mobile Top 10 using over 100 code samples including obfuscated ones, with RAG augmentation.","summary_zh":"比较9个LLM对OWASP移动端Top 10中Android漏洞的检测能力，使用超过100个代码样本（含混淆样本），并采用RAG增强。","contributions":["Evaluates nine state-of-the-art LLMs on detecting Android vulnerabilities from OWASP Mobile Top 10.","Tests models against an open dataset of over 100 vulnerable code samples, including obfuscated ones.","Provides insights into context augmentation with retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) for Android vulnerability detection.","Identifies key factors contributing to LLM performance and reveals significant discrepancies among different models."],"contributions_zh":["评估九个先进LLM在检测OWASP移动端Top 10中Android漏洞方面的能力。","在包含超过100个漏洞代码样本（含混淆样本）的开放数据集上测试模型。","提供关于使用检索增强生成（RAG）进行Android漏洞检测的上下文增强洞察。","识别影响LLM性能的关键因素，揭示不同模型之间的显著差异。"],"abstract_zh":"针对Android应用的攻击频率不断增加，加上大语言模型（LLM）近期的流行，需要全面了解后者在识别潜在漏洞方面的能力，这对降低整体风险至关重要。为此，本研究比较了九个先进LLM检测最新开放全球应用安全项目（OWASP）移动端Top 10中列出的Android代码漏洞的能力。每个LLM在一个包含超过100个漏洞代码样本（包括混淆样本）的开放数据集上进行评估，评估每个模型识别关键漏洞的能力。我们的分析揭示了每个LLM的优缺点，识别了影响其性能的重要因素。此外，我们提供了关于使用检索增强生成（RAG）检测Android代码漏洞的上下文增强洞察，这反过来可能推动安全应用开发。最后，虽然关于代码漏洞分析的报告结果显示出前景，但也揭示了不同LLM之间的显著差异。","experiment":{"language":["Java"],"platform":["Android"],"target_domain":["Android applications"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["OWASP Mobile Top 10"],"benchmark_size":"over 100 vulnerable code samples","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Reveals significant discrepancies among 9 LLMs in detecting Android vulnerabilities; RAG augmentation shows promise.","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@article{kouliaridis2024assessing,\\n  title={Assessing the Effectiveness of LLMs in Android Application Vulnerability Analysis},\\n  author={Kouliaridis, Vasileios and Karopoulos, Georgios and Kambourakis, Georgios},\\n  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2406.18894},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"li2024attention","title":"Attention is all you need for llm-based code vulnerability localization","authors":"Li, Yue and Li, Xiao and Wu, Hao and Zhang, Yue and Cheng, Xiuzhen and Zhong, Sheng and Xu, Fengyuan","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2410.15288","abstract":"The rapid expansion of software systems and the growing number of reported vulnerabilities have emphasized the importance of accurately identifying vulnerable code segments. Traditional methods for vulnerability localization, such as manual code audits or rule-based tools, are often time-consuming and limited in scope, typically focusing on specific programming languages or types of vulnerabilities. In recent years, the introduction of large language models (LLMs) such as GPT and LLaMA has opened new possibilities for automating vulnerability detection. However, while LLMs show promise in this area, they face challenges, particularly in maintaining accuracy over longer code contexts. This paper introduces LOVA, a novel framework leveraging the self-attention mechanisms inherent in LLMs to enhance vulnerability localization. Our key insight is that self-attention mechanisms assign varying importance to different parts of the input, making it possible to track how much attention the model focuses on specific lines of code. In the context of vulnerability localization, the hypothesis is that vulnerable lines of code will naturally attract higher attention weights because they have a greater influence on the model's output. By systematically tracking changes in attention weights and focusing on specific lines of code, LOVA improves the precision of identifying vulnerable lines across various programming languages. Through rigorous experimentation and evaluation, we demonstrate that LOVA significantly outperforms existing LLM-based approaches, achieving up to a 5.3x improvement in F1-scores. LOVA also demonstrated strong scalability, with up to a 14.6x improvement in smart contract vulnerability localization across languages like C, Python, Java, and Solidity. Its robustness was proven through consistent performance across different LLM architectures.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["semantic"],"system_name":"LOVA","summary":"Introduces LOVA, leveraging LLM self-attention mechanisms for vulnerability localization, achieving up to 5.3x F1 improvement across C, Python, Java, and Solidity.","summary_zh":"提出LOVA，利用LLM自注意力机制进行漏洞定位，在C、Python、Java和Solidity上实现最高5.3倍的F1提升。","contributions":["Proposes LOVA, a framework leveraging LLM self-attention mechanisms for vulnerability localization at the line level.","Achieves up to 5.3x improvement in F1 scores over existing LLM-based vulnerability localization approaches.","Demonstrates 14.6x improvement in smart contract vulnerability localization.","Validates scalability across C, Python, Java, and Solidity programming languages.","Shows consistent performance across different LLM architectures including GPT and LLaMA."],"contributions_zh":["提出LOVA，一种利用LLM自注意力机制在行级别进行漏洞定位的框架。","在F1分数上比现有基于LLM的漏洞定位方法提高了最多5.3倍。","在智能合约漏洞定位上实现了14.6倍的改进。","验证了在C、Python、Java和Solidity编程语言上的可扩展性。","在GPT和LLaMA等不同LLM架构上表现出一致的性能。"],"abstract_zh":"软件系统的快速扩展和报告漏洞数量的增长强调了准确识别漏洞代码段的重要性。传统的漏洞定位方法，如手动代码审计或基于规则的工具，通常耗时且范围有限，通常只关注特定编程语言或漏洞类型。近年来，GPT和LLaMA等大语言模型（LLM）的引入为自动化漏洞检测开辟了新的可能性。然而，虽然LLM在这一领域显示出前景，但它们面临挑战，特别是在更长代码上下文中保持准确性方面。本文介绍了LOVA，一种利用LLM中固有的自注意力机制来增强漏洞定位的新框架。我们的关键洞察是，自注意力机制对输入的不同部分赋予不同的重要性，使得跟踪模型对特定代码行的关注程度成为可能。在漏洞定位的背景下，假设是漏洞代码行会自然吸引更高的注意力权重，因为它们对模型输出有更大的影响。通过系统地跟踪注意力权重的变化并关注特定代码行，LOVA提高了跨多种编程语言识别漏洞行的精度。通过严格的实验和评估，我们证明LOVA显著优于现有的基于LLM的方法，在F1分数上实现了最高5.3倍的改进。LOVA还展示了强大的可扩展性，在C、Python、Java和Solidity等语言的智能合约漏洞定位上实现了最高14.6倍的改进。其稳健性通过在不同LLM架构上的一致性能得到验证。","experiment":{"language":["C","Python","Java","Solidity"],"platform":[],"target_domain":["smart contracts"],"llm":["GPT","LLaMA"],"model_family":["GPT","LLaMA"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Up to 5.3x F1 improvement over existing LLM-based approaches; 14.6x improvement in smart contract vulnerability localization.","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@article{li2024attention,\\n  title={Attention is all you need for llm-based code vulnerability localization},\\n  author={Li, Yue and Li, Xiao and Wu, Hao and Zhang, Yue and Cheng, Xiuzhen and Zhong, Sheng and Xu, Fengyuan},\\n  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2410.15288},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"li2024enhancing","title":"Enhancing Static Analysis for Practical Bug Detection: An LLM-Integrated Approach","authors":"Li, Haonan and Hao, Yu and Zhai, Yizhuo and Qian, Zhiyun","year":2024,"venue":"Proceedings of the ACM on Programming Languages","abstract":"While static analysis is instrumental in uncovering software bugs, its precision in analyzing large and intricate codebases remains challenging. The emerging prowess of Large Language Models (LLMs) offers a promising avenue to address these complexities. In this paper, we present LLift, a pioneering framework that synergizes static analysis and LLMs, with a spotlight on identifying use-before-initialization (UBI) bugs within the Linux kernel. Drawing from our insights into variable usage conventions in Linux, we enhance path analysis using post-constraint guidance. This approach, combined with our methodically crafted procedures, empowers LLift to adeptly handle the challenges of bug-specific modeling, extensive codebases, and the unpredictable nature of LLMs. Our real-world evaluations identified four previously undiscovered UBI bugs in the mainstream Linux kernel, which the Linux community has acknowledged. This study reaffirms the potential of marrying static analysis with LLMs, setting a compelling direction for future research in this area.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"system_name":"LLift","summary":"Presents LLift, combining static analysis with LLMs to detect use-before-initialization bugs in Linux kernel, discovering 4 previously unknown UBI bugs.","summary_zh":"提出LLift，将静态分析与LLM结合检测Linux内核中的使用前初始化错误，发现4个此前未知的UBI漏洞。","contributions":["Proposes LLift, a framework synergizing static analysis and LLMs for detecting use-before-initialization (UBI) bugs in the Linux kernel.","Enhances path analysis using post-constraint guidance based on variable usage conventions in Linux.","Designs procedures to handle bug-specific modeling, extensive codebases, and LLM unpredictability.","Discovers four previously unknown UBI bugs in the mainstream Linux kernel, acknowledged by the Linux community."],"contributions_zh":["提出LLift，一种将静态分析与LLM协同的框架，用于检测Linux内核中的使用前初始化（UBI）漏洞。","基于Linux中的变量使用约定，使用后约束引导增强路径分析。","设计了处理特定漏洞建模、大规模代码库和LLM不可预测性的方法。","在主流Linux内核中发现了四个此前未知的UBI漏洞，已获Linux社区确认。"],"abstract_zh":"虽然静态分析在发现软件漏洞方面发挥着重要作用，但其在分析大型和复杂代码库时的精度仍然具有挑战性。大语言模型（LLM）的新兴能力为解决这些复杂性提供了有前途的途径。本文介绍了LLift，一种将静态分析和LLM协同的开创性框架，重点识别Linux内核中的使用前初始化（UBI）漏洞。根据我们对Linux中变量使用约定的洞察，我们使用后约束引导来增强路径分析。这种方法结合我们精心设计的流程，使LLift能够熟练处理特定漏洞建模、大规模代码库和LLM不可预测性的挑战。我们的真实世界评估在主流Linux内核中识别出四个此前未发现的UBI漏洞，Linux社区已确认了这些漏洞。这项研究重申了将静态分析与LLM结合的潜力，为该领域未来的研究指明了令人信服的方向。","experiment":{"language":["C"],"platform":["Linux"],"target_domain":["Linux kernel"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":["use-before-initialization (UBI)"],"key_results":"Discovered 4 previously unknown UBI bugs in the mainstream Linux kernel, acknowledged by the Linux community.","real_world_impact":"4 previously unknown UBI bugs discovered and acknowledged by Linux community.","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":2,"bibtex":"@article{li2024enhancing,\\n  title={Enhancing Static Analysis for Practical Bug Detection: An LLM-Integrated Approach},\\n  author={Li, Haonan and Hao, Yu and Zhai, Yizhuo and Qian, Zhiyun},\\n  journal={Proceedings of the ACM on Programming Languages},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"li2024llm","title":"LLM-Assisted Static Analysis for Detecting Security Vulnerabilities","authors":"Li, Ziyang and Dutta, Saikat and Naik, Mayur","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2405.17238","abstract":"Software is prone to security vulnerabilities. Program analysis tools to detect them have limited effectiveness in practice. While large language models (or LLMs) have shown impressive code generation capabilities, they cannot do complex reasoning over code to detect such vulnerabilities, especially because this task requires whole-repository analysis. In this work, we propose IRIS, the first approach that systematically combines LLMs with static analysis to perform wholerepository reasoning to detect security vulnerabilities. We curate a new dataset, CWE-Bench-Java, comprising 120 manually validated security vulnerabilities in real-world Java projects. These projects are complex, with an average of 300,000 lines of code and a maximum of up to 7 million. Out of 120 vulnerabilities in CWE-Bench-Java, IRIS detects 69 using GPT-4, while the state-of-the-art static analysis tool only detects 27. Further, IRIS also significantly reduces the number of false alarms (by more than 80% in the best case).","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["llm-sast"],"system_name":"IRIS","summary":"Proposes IRIS, combining LLMs with static analysis for whole-repository Java vulnerability detection, detecting 69/120 vulnerabilities with GPT-4 vs 27 by static analysis alone.","summary_zh":"提出IRIS，将LLM与静态分析结合进行全仓库Java漏洞检测，使用GPT-4检测出120个漏洞中的69个，而单独静态分析仅检测27个。","contributions":["Proposes IRIS, the first approach systematically combining LLMs with static analysis for whole-repository vulnerability detection.","Curates CWE-Bench-Java, a new dataset of 120 manually validated security vulnerabilities in real-world Java projects (up to 7M lines of code).","Detects 69 out of 120 vulnerabilities using GPT-4, compared to 27 by state-of-the-art static analysis tools.","Reduces false alarms by more than 80% in the best case."],"contributions_zh":["提出IRIS，首个系统性地将LLM与静态分析结合进行全仓库漏洞检测的方法。","构建CWE-Bench-Java，一个包含120个在真实世界Java项目（最大达700万行代码）中手动验证的安全漏洞的新数据集。","使用GPT-4检测出120个漏洞中的69个，而先进的静态分析工具仅检测27个。","在最佳情况下将误报减少了80%以上。"],"abstract_zh":"软件容易出现安全漏洞。检测这些漏洞的程序分析工具在实践中的有效性有限。虽然大语言模型（LLM）已展示出令人印象深刻的代码生成能力，但它们无法对代码进行复杂推理以检测此类漏洞，特别是因为此任务需要全仓库分析。在这项工作中，我们提出了IRIS，首个系统性地将LLM与静态分析结合以执行全仓库推理来检测安全漏洞的方法。我们构建了一个新数据集CWE-Bench-Java，包含120个在真实世界Java项目中手动验证的安全漏洞。这些项目很复杂，平均有30万行代码，最大达700万行。在CWE-Bench-Java的120个漏洞中，IRIS使用GPT-4检测到69个，而先进的静态分析工具仅检测到27个。此外，IRIS还显著减少了误报数量（在最佳情况下减少了80%以上）。","experiment":{"language":["Java"],"platform":[],"target_domain":[],"llm":["GPT-4"],"model_family":["GPT"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["CWE-Bench-Java"],"benchmark_size":"120 manually validated vulnerabilities in real-world Java projects","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"IRIS detects 69/120 vulnerabilities with GPT-4 vs 27 by static analysis; reduces false alarms by over 80%.","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@article{li2024llm,\\n  title={LLM-Assisted Static Analysis for Detecting Security Vulnerabilities},\\n  author={Li, Ziyang and Dutta, Saikat and Naik, Mayur},\\n  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2405.17238},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"libro2023icse","title":"Large Language Models are Few-shot Testers: Exploring LLM-based General Bug Reproduction","authors":"","year":2023,"venue":"ICSE'23","abstract":"Many automated test generation techniques have been developed to aid developers with writing tests. To facilitate full automation, most existing techniques aim to either increase coverage, or generate exploratory inputs. However, existing test generation techniques largely fall short of achieving more semantic objectives, such as generating tests to reproduce a given bug report. Reproducing bugs is nonetheless important, as our empirical study shows that the number of tests added in open source repositories due to issues was about 28% of the corresponding project test suite size. Meanwhile, due to the difficulties of transforming the expected program semantics in bug reports into test oracles, existing failure reproduction techniques tend to deal exclusively with program crashes, a small subset of all bug reports. To automate test generation from general bug reports, we propose LIBRO, a framework that uses Large Language Models (LLMs), which have been shown to be capable of performing code-related tasks. Since LLMs themselves cannot execute the target buggy code, we focus on post-processing steps that help us discern when LLMs are effective, and rank the produced tests according to their validity. Our evaluation of LIBRO shows that, on the widely studied Defects4J benchmark, LIBRO can generate failure reproducing test cases for 33% of all studied cases (251 out of 750), while suggesting a bug reproducing test in first place for 149 bugs. To mitigate data contamination, we also evaluate LIBRO against 31 bug reports submitted after the collection of the LLM training data terminated: LIBRO produces bug reproducing tests for 32% of the studied bug reports. Overall, our results show LIBRO has the potential to significantly enhance developer efficiency by automatically generating tests from bug reports.","paperUrl":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2209.11515","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["fuzzing"],"subcategories":[],"system_name":"LIBRO","summary":"Proposes LIBRO, using LLMs to generate bug-reproducing tests from bug reports, successfully reproducing 33% of Defects4J bugs (251/750) with first-place ranking for 149.","summary_zh":"提出LIBRO，使用LLM从缺陷报告生成缺陷复现测试，成功复现Defects4J中33%的缺陷（251/750），其中149个排名第一。","contributions":["Proposes LIBRO, a framework using LLMs to generate failure-reproducing test cases from general bug reports.","Shows that 28% of tests in open source repositories are added due to issues, motivating automated bug reproduction.","Generates bug-reproducing tests for 33% of Defects4J cases (251 out of 750), with 149 bugs reproduced in first place.","Evaluates against 31 post-training bug reports to mitigate data contamination, achieving 32% bug reproduction rate.","Introduces post-processing steps to rank and validate LLM-generated tests."],"contributions_zh":["提出LIBRO，一种使用LLM从一般缺陷报告生成故障复现测试用例的框架。","表明开源仓库中28%的测试是由问题引起的，这激励了自动化缺陷复现。","为Defects4J中33%的案例（750个中的251个）生成了缺陷复现测试，其中149个缺陷排名第一。","对31个训练后缺陷报告进行评估以减轻数据污染，实现32%的缺陷复现率。","引入后处理步骤来排序和验证LLM生成的测试。"],"abstract_zh":"许多自动化测试生成技术已被开发来帮助开发人员编写测试。为了实现完全自动化，大多数现有技术旨在增加覆盖率或生成探索性输入。然而，现有的测试生成技术在实现更多语义目标方面largely不足，例如生成测试以复现给定的缺陷报告。复现缺陷仍然很重要，因为我们的实证研究表明，开源仓库中因问题而添加的测试数量约为相应项目测试套件大小的28%。同时，由于将缺陷报告中的预期程序语义转换为测试预言的困难，现有的故障复现技术往往仅处理程序崩溃，这只是所有缺陷报告的一小部分。为了从一般缺陷报告自动生成测试，我们提出了LIBRO，一种使用大语言模型（LLM）的框架，LLM已被证明能够执行代码相关任务。由于LLM本身无法执行目标有缺陷的代码，我们重点关注帮助我们辨别LLM何时有效的后处理步骤，并根据有效性对生成的测试进行排序。我们对LIBRO的评估表明，在广泛研究的Defects4J基准上，LIBRO可以为33%的所有研究案例（750个中的251个）生成故障复现测试用例，同时为149个缺陷建议第一名的缺陷复现测试。为减轻数据污染，我们还对LLM训练数据收集终止后提交的31个缺陷报告进行了LIBRO评估：LIBRO为32%的研究缺陷报告生成了缺陷复现测试。总体而言，我们的结果表明LIBRO有潜力通过自动从缺陷报告生成测试来显著提高开发人员效率。","experiment":{"language":["Java"],"platform":[],"target_domain":[],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["Defects4J"],"benchmark_size":"750 bugs from Defects4J + 31 post-training bug reports","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Generates bug-reproducing tests for 33% (251/750) of Defects4J cases; first-place ranking for 149 bugs; 32% on post-training data.","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":3,"bibtex":"@inproceedings{libro2023icse,\\n  title={Large Language Models are Few-shot Testers: Exploring LLM-based General Bug Reproduction},\\n  author={},\\n  booktitle={ICSE'23},\\n  year={2023}\\n}"},{"id":"liu2023software","title":"Software vulnerability detection with gpt and in-context learning","authors":"Liu, Zhihong and Liao, Qing and Gu, Wenchao and Gao, Cuiyun","year":2023,"venue":"2023 8th International Conference on Data Science in Cyberspace (DSC)","abstract":"Code vulnerability detection is a software security analysis technique that focuses on recognizing and resolving possible code vulnerabilities and weaknesses. Its primary objective is to mitigate the chances of malicious attacks and system failures. Vulnerabilities encompass mistakes, defects, or insecure programming methodologies found within the code, which can lead to security risks, service denials, data leaks, and various other concerns. Previous research has predominantly focused on deep learning models such as VulDeePecker, Russell, and SySeVR. With the advent of large language models, impressive advancements have been made in various domains, including natural language generation, text classification, and sentiment analysis. However, there is currently no effective method for utilizing large language models in vulnerability detection. Therefore, this study explores and validates the application of such models for code vulnerability detection. In this paper we present a context-based learning approach to enhance the capability of code vulnerability detection named VUL-GPT. Our method combines code retrieval and code analysis, leveraging in-context learning to improve the performance of the GPT model in vulnerability detection. Specifically, we use GPT to generate analysis content for the test code and employ code retrieval methods such as BM-25 and TF-IDF to retrieve the most similar code snippet and its vulnerability information from the training set. Subsequently, we input them along with the test code and its analysis into the GPT model, leveraging the contextual learning ability of the large language model for vulnerability detection. Our experiments demonstrate that combining with code retrieval and code analysis, the GPT models can detect code vulnerability detection more effectively.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"system_name":"VUL-GPT","summary":"Proposes VUL-GPT, combining code retrieval (BM-25/TF-IDF) with in-context learning to enhance GPT's vulnerability detection using similar code snippets.","summary_zh":"提出VUL-GPT，结合代码检索（BM-25/TF-IDF）和上下文学习，利用相似代码片段增强GPT的漏洞检测能力。","contributions":["Proposes VUL-GPT, a context-based learning approach for code vulnerability detection using GPT.","Combines code retrieval methods (BM-25 and TF-IDF) with code analysis for in-context learning.","Uses GPT to generate analysis content for test code and retrieves similar vulnerable code snippets from training sets.","Demonstrates that combining code retrieval and code analysis improves GPT's vulnerability detection effectiveness."],"contributions_zh":["提出VUL-GPT，一种使用GPT进行代码漏洞检测的基于上下文学习的方法。","结合代码检索方法（BM-25和TF-IDF）与代码分析进行上下文学习。","使用GPT为测试代码生成分析内容，并从训练集中检索相似的漏洞代码片段。","证明结合代码检索和代码分析可以提高GPT的漏洞检测效果。"],"abstract_zh":"代码漏洞检测是一种软件安全分析技术，专注于识别和解决可能的代码漏洞和弱点。其主要目标是降低恶意攻击和系统故障的可能性。漏洞包括代码中的错误、缺陷或不安全的编程方法，可能导致安全风险、服务拒绝、数据泄露和其他各种问题。以前的研究主要集中在深度学习模型上，如VulDeePecker、Russell和SySeVR。随着大语言模型的出现，在各个领域取得了令人印象深刻的进展，包括自然语言生成、文本分类和情感分析。然而，目前没有有效的方法来利用大语言模型进行漏洞检测。因此，本研究探索和验证了此类模型在代码漏洞检测中的应用。本文提出了一种名为VUL-GPT的基于上下文学习的方法来增强代码漏洞检测能力。我们的方法结合了代码检索和代码分析，利用上下文学习来提高GPT模型在漏洞检测中的性能。具体而言，我们使用GPT为测试代码生成分析内容，并采用BM-25和TF-IDF等代码检索方法从训练集中检索最相似的代码片段及其漏洞信息。随后，我们将它们与测试代码及其分析一起输入GPT模型，利用大语言模型的上下文学习能力进行漏洞检测。我们的实验表明，结合代码检索和代码分析，GPT模型可以更有效地检测代码漏洞。","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":[],"llm":["GPT"],"model_family":["GPT"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":["VulDeePecker","Russell","SySeVR"],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Combining code retrieval and code analysis improves GPT's vulnerability detection effectiveness.","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@inproceedings{liu2023software,\\n  title={Software vulnerability detection with gpt and in-context learning},\\n  author={Liu, Zhihong and Liao, Qing and Gu, Wenchao and Gao, Cuiyun},\\n  booktitle={2023 8th International Conference on Data Science in Cyberspace (DSC)},\\n  year={2023}\\n}"},{"id":"liu2024exploration","title":"Exploration On Prompting LLM With Code-Specific Information For Vulnerability Detection","authors":"Liu, Zhihong and Yang, Zezhou and Liao, Qing","year":2024,"venue":"2024 IEEE International Conference on Software Services Engineering (SSE)","abstract":"Software vulnerability detection is a software se- curity analysis technique that aims to recognize possible code vulnerabilities and weaknesses. The majority of previous research has primarily concentrated on deep learning models. Recently, with the rapid development of large language mod- els, researchers are exploring the use of G PT in the field of vulnerability detection. However, these works inadequately account for the features of vulnerability detection, lacking specific prompts and code-specific information. This paper primarily investigates the impact of prompts for GPT. We design the following prompts step by step: basic prompts, prompts with code-specific information, and chain-of-thought (CoT) prompts. Firstly, we explore the performance using basic prompts in the field of vulnerability detection. Subsequently, we incorporate code-specific information into basic prompts, focusing primarily on similar code and data flow graph (DFG). The similar code is obtained through our designed code search algorithm, which takes into account both code semantic and structural information. Finally, we further introduce CoT prompts to inspire GPT's ability for gradually detecting vulnerability. We also conduct experiments to explore the impact of the position of code- specific information in the prompts and the suitable temperature value for the vulnerability detection task. Our experiment results demonstrate that, combined with code-specific information and CoT, GPT can detect vulnerabilities more effectively.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"system_name":"","summary":"Investigates prompting strategies for GPT vulnerability detection: basic prompts, code-specific information (similar code, DFG), and chain-of-thought prompts.","summary_zh":"研究GPT漏洞检测的提示策略：基础提示、代码特定信息（相似代码、数据流图）和思维链提示。","contributions":["Designs and evaluates three levels of prompts for GPT vulnerability detection: basic, code-specific, and chain-of-thought (CoT).","Incorporates code-specific information including similar code and data flow graphs (DFG) into prompts.","Designs a code search algorithm considering both code semantic and structural information for retrieving similar code.","Explores the impact of code-specific information position in prompts and suitable temperature values for vulnerability detection.","Demonstrates that combining code-specific information and CoT enables GPT to detect vulnerabilities more effectively."],"contributions_zh":["设计并评估了GPT漏洞检测的三个级别提示：基础提示、代码特定信息提示和思维链（CoT）提示。","将代码特定信息（包括相似代码和数据流图DFG）纳入提示中。","设计了一种考虑代码语义和结构信息的代码搜索算法，用于检索相似代码。","探索了代码特定信息在提示中的位置以及适合漏洞检测任务的温度值的影响。","证明结合代码特定信息和CoT使GPT能够更有效地检测漏洞。"],"abstract_zh":"软件漏洞检测是一种旨在识别可能的代码漏洞和弱点的软件安全分析技术。大多数以前的研究主要集中在深度学习模型上。最近，随着大语言模型的快速发展，研究人员正在探索在漏洞检测领域使用GPT。然而，这些工作对漏洞检测的特征考虑不足，缺乏特定的提示和代码特定信息。本文主要研究提示对GPT的影响。我们逐步设计以下提示：基础提示、包含代码特定信息的提示和思维链（CoT）提示。首先，我们探索在漏洞检测领域使用基础提示的性能。随后，我们将代码特定信息纳入基础提示，主要关注相似代码和数据流图（DFG）。相似代码通过我们设计的代码搜索算法获得，该算法同时考虑代码语义和结构信息。最后，我们进一步引入CoT提示以激发GPT逐步检测漏洞的能力。我们还进行了实验，探索代码特定信息在提示中的位置以及适合漏洞检测任务的温度值的影响。实验结果表明，结合代码特定信息和CoT，GPT可以更有效地检测漏洞。","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":[],"llm":["GPT"],"model_family":["GPT"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Combining code-specific information (similar code, DFG) and CoT prompts enables GPT to detect vulnerabilities more effectively.","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@inproceedings{liu2024exploration,\\n  title={Exploration On Prompting LLM With Code-Specific Information For Vulnerability Detection},\\n  author={Liu, Zhihong and Yang, Zezhou and Liao, Qing},\\n  booktitle={2024 IEEE International Conference on Software Services Engineering (SSE)},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"liu2024vuldetectbench","title":"VulDetectBench: Evaluating the Deep Capability of Vulnerability Detection with Large Language Models","authors":"Liu, Yu and Gao, Lang and Yang, Mingxin and Xie, Yu and Chen, Ping and Zhang, Xiaojin and Chen, Wei","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2406.07595","abstract":"Large Language Models (LLMs) have training corpora containing large amounts of program code, greatly improving the model’s code comprehension and generation capabilities. However, sound comprehensive research on detecting program vulnerabilities, a more specific task related to code, and evaluating the performance of LLMs in this more specialized scenario is still lacking. To address common challenges in vulnerability analysis, our study introduces a new benchmark, VulDetectBench, specifically designed to assess the vulnerability detection capabilities of LLMs. The benchmark comprehensively evaluates LLM’s ability to identify, classify, and locate vulnerabilities through five tasks of increasing difficulty. We evaluate the performance of 17 models (both open- and closed-source) and find that while existing models can achieve over 80% accuracy on tasks related to vulnerability identification and classification, they still fall short on specific, more detailed vulnerability analysis tasks, with less than 30% accuracy, making it difficult to provide valuable auxiliary information for professional vulnerability mining. Our benchmark effectively evaluates the capabilities of various LLMs at different levels in the specific task of vulnerability detection, providing a foundation for future research and improvements in this critical area of code security. VulDetectBench is publicly available at https://github.com/Sweetaroo/VulDetectBench.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["fine-tuning"],"system_name":"VulDetectBench","summary":"Introduces VulDetectBench benchmark evaluating 17 LLMs on 5 vulnerability detection tasks of increasing difficulty; models achieve 80%+ on identification but under 30% on detailed analysis.","summary_zh":"推出VulDetectBench基准，在5个难度递增的漏洞检测任务上评估17个LLM；模型在识别任务上达80%以上准确率，但在详细分析上低于30%。","contributions":["Introduces VulDetectBench, a benchmark with five tasks of increasing difficulty for evaluating LLM vulnerability detection capabilities.","Evaluates 17 models (both open- and closed-source) on vulnerability identification, classification, and localization.","Finds models achieve over 80% accuracy on identification/classification but less than 30% on detailed vulnerability analysis.","Publicly releases VulDetectBench at https://github.com/Sweetaroo/VulDetectBench."],"contributions_zh":["推出VulDetectBench，一个包含五个难度递增任务的基准，用于评估LLM漏洞检测能力。","在漏洞识别、分类和定位上评估17个模型（开源和闭源）。","发现模型在识别/分类任务上准确率超过80%，但在详细漏洞分析上低于30%。","在https://github.com/Sweetaroo/VulDetectBench公开发布VulDetectBench。"],"abstract_zh":"大语言模型（LLM）的训练语料包含大量程序代码，大大提高了模型的代码理解和生成能力。然而，关于检测程序漏洞这一与代码更为相关的具体任务，以及评估LLM在这一更专业场景中的表现，目前仍缺乏全面而深入的研究。为了解决漏洞分析中的常见挑战，我们的研究引入了一个新的基准VulDetectBench，专门设计用于评估LLM的漏洞检测能力。该基准通过五个难度递增的任务全面评估LLM识别、分类和定位漏洞的能力。我们评估了17个模型（开源和闭源）的性能，发现虽然现有模型在与漏洞识别和分类相关的任务上可以达到80%以上的准确率，但在更具体、更详细的漏洞分析任务上仍然不足，准确率不到30%，难以为专业漏洞挖掘提供有价值的辅助信息。我们的基准有效地评估了各种LLM在漏洞检测这一特定任务中不同层次的能力，为该代码安全关键领域的未来研究和改进奠定了基础。VulDetectBench已公开发布于https://github.com/Sweetaroo/VulDetectBench。","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":[],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["VulDetectBench"],"benchmark_size":"17 models evaluated on 5 tasks","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Over 80% accuracy on identification/classification tasks; less than 30% accuracy on detailed vulnerability analysis.","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@article{liu2024vuldetectbench,\\n  title={VulDetectBench: Evaluating the Deep Capability of Vulnerability Detection with Large Language Models},\\n  author={Liu, Yu and Gao, Lang and Yang, Mingxin and Xie, Yu and Chen, Ping and Zhang, Xiaojin and Chen, Wei},\\n  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2406.07595},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"llmif2024sp","title":"LLMIF: Augmented Large Language Model for Fuzzing IoT Devices","authors":"","year":2024,"venue":"IEEE S&P'24","abstract":"Despite the efficacy of fuzzing in verifying the implementation correctness of network protocols, existing IoT protocol fuzzing approaches grapple with several limitations, including obfuscated message formats, unresolved message dependencies, and a lack of evaluations on the testing cases. These limitations significantly curtail the capabilities of IoT fuzzers in vulnerability identification. In this work, we show that the protocol specification contains fruitful descriptions of protocol messages, which can be used to overcome the above limitations and guide IoT protocol fuzzing. To automate the specification analysis, we augment the large language model with the specification contents, and drive it to perform two tasks (i.e., protocol information extraction, and device response reasoning). We further design and implement a fuzzing algorithm, LLMIF, which incorporates the LLM into IoT fuzzing. Finally, we select Zigbee as the target protocol and initiate comprehensive evaluations. The evaluation result shows that LLMIF successfully addressed the above limitations. Compared with the existing Zigbee fuzzers, it increases the protocol message coverage and code coverage by 55.2% and 53.9%, respectively. Besides the enhanced coverage, LLMIF unearthed 11 vulnerabilities on real-world Zigbee devices, which include eight previously unknown vulnerabilities. Seven of them are not covered by the existing Zigbee fuzzers.","paperUrl":"https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/stamp/stamp.jsp?arnumber=10646659","codeUrl":"https://github.com/anonymousAnalyst22/LLMIF","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DZN4R45FmCI","categories":["fuzzing"],"subcategories":[],"system_name":"LLMIF","summary":"Proposes LLMIF, augmenting LLMs with protocol specifications to fuzz Zigbee IoT devices, achieving 55.2% more message coverage and discovering 11 vulnerabilities (8 new).","summary_zh":"提出LLMIF，利用协议规范增强LLM对Zigbee物联网设备进行模糊测试，提高55.2%的消息覆盖率并发现11个漏洞（8个新漏洞）。","contributions":["Proposes LLMIF, augmenting LLMs with protocol specification contents for IoT protocol fuzzing.","Drives LLM to perform protocol information extraction and device response reasoning from specifications.","Increases Zigbee protocol message coverage by 55.2% and code coverage by 53.9% over existing fuzzers.","Discovers 11 vulnerabilities on real-world Zigbee devices, including 8 previously unknown ones.","Seven of the discovered vulnerabilities are not covered by existing Zigbee fuzzers."],"contributions_zh":["提出LLMIF，利用协议规范内容增强LLM进行物联网协议模糊测试。","驱动LLM从规范中执行协议信息提取和设备响应推理。","相比现有模糊器，Zigbee协议消息覆盖率提高55.2%，代码覆盖率提高53.9%。","在真实世界Zigbee设备上发现11个漏洞，包括8个此前未知的漏洞。","发现的漏洞中有7个未被现有Zigbee模糊器覆盖。"],"abstract_zh":"尽管模糊测试在验证网络协议实现正确性方面很有效，但现有的物联网协议模糊测试方法面临若干限制，包括混淆的消息格式、未解决的消息依赖关系以及缺乏对测试用例的评估。这些限制显著削弱了物联网模糊器在漏洞识别方面的能力。在这项工作中，我们展示了协议规范包含丰富的协议消息描述，可用于克服上述限制并指导物联网协议模糊测试。为了自动化规范分析，我们用规范内容增强大语言模型，并驱动它执行两个任务（即协议信息提取和设备响应推理）。我们进一步设计并实现了一种模糊测试算法LLMIF，将LLM纳入物联网模糊测试。最后，我们选择Zigbee作为目标协议并进行了全面评估。评估结果表明LLMIF成功解决了上述限制。与现有Zigbee模糊器相比，它将协议消息覆盖率和代码覆盖率分别提高了55.2%和53.9%。除了增强的覆盖率外，LLMIF在真实世界Zigbee设备上发现了11个漏洞，其中包括8个此前未知的漏洞。其中7个未被现有Zigbee模糊器覆盖。","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["IoT","Zigbee"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":["LLMIF"],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"55.2% more protocol message coverage, 53.9% more code coverage; 11 vulnerabilities found (8 previously unknown).","real_world_impact":"11 vulnerabilities on real-world Zigbee devices, including 8 previously unknown ones.","open_source":true,"cost":""},"recommendation":3,"bibtex":"@inproceedings{llmif2024sp,\\n  title={LLMIF: Augmented Large Language Model for Fuzzing IoT Devices},\\n  author={},\\n  booktitle={IEEE S\\\\&P'24},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"lu2024grace","title":"GRACE: Empowering LLM-based software vulnerability detection with graph structure and in-context learning","authors":"Lu, Guilong and Ju, Xiaolin and Chen, Xiang and Pei, Wenlong and Cai, Zhilong","year":2024,"venue":"Journal of Systems and Software","abstract":"Software vulnerabilities inflict considerable economic and societal harm. Therefore, timely and accurate detection of these flaws has become vital. Large language models (LLMs) have emerged as a promising tool for vulnerability detection in recent studies. However, their effectiveness suffers when limited to plain text source code, which may ignore the syntactic and semantic information of the code. To address this limitation, we propose a novel vulnerability detection approach GRACE that empowers LLM-based software vulnerability detection by incorporating graph structural information in the code and in-context learning. We also design an effective demonstration retrieval approach that identifies highly relevant code examples by considering semantic, lexical, and syntactic similarities for the target code to provide better demonstrations for in-context learning. To evaluate the effectiveness of GRACE, we conducted an empirical study on three vulnerability detection datasets (i.e., Devign, Reveal, and Big-Vul). The results demonstrate that GRACE outperforms six state-of-the-art vulnerability detection baselines by at least 28.65% in terms of the F1 score across these three datasets. Therefore, our study highlights the effectiveness of integrating graph structural information and in-context learning in LLMs for vulnerability detection. These findings motivate further investigation into tailoring such approaches for specific vulnerability types or adapting them to other security tasks.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"system_name":"GRACE","summary":"Proposes GRACE, integrating graph structural information and in-context learning into LLMs for vulnerability detection, outperforming 6 baselines by 28.65%+ F1 on Devign/Reveal/Big-Vul.","summary_zh":"提出GRACE，将图结构信息和上下文学习集成到LLM中进行漏洞检测，在Devign/Reveal/Big-Vul上F1超越6个基线28.65%以上。","contributions":["Proposes GRACE, a vulnerability detection approach integrating graph structural information and in-context learning into LLMs.","Designs an effective demonstration retrieval approach considering semantic, lexical, and syntactic similarities.","Outperforms six state-of-the-art vulnerability detection baselines by at least 28.65% in F1 score across three datasets.","Evaluates on three datasets: Devign, Reveal, and Big-Vul."],"contributions_zh":["提出GRACE，一种将图结构信息和上下文学习集成到LLM中的漏洞检测方法。","设计了一种考虑语义、词汇和句法相似性的有效示例检索方法。","在三个数据集上F1分数超越六个先进漏洞检测基线至少28.65%。","在Devign、Reveal和Big-Vul三个数据集上进行评估。"],"abstract_zh":"软件漏洞造成了相当大的经济和社会损害。因此，及时准确地检测这些缺陷变得至关重要。大语言模型（LLM）在近期研究中已成为漏洞检测的有前途的工具。然而，当仅限于纯文本源代码时，其有效性会受到影响，因为可能忽略代码的语法和语义信息。为了解决这一限制，我们提出了一种新颖的漏洞检测方法GRACE，通过将代码中的图结构信息和上下文学习纳入LLM来增强基于LLM的软件漏洞检测。我们还设计了一种有效的示例检索方法，通过考虑语义、词汇和句法相似性来为目标代码识别高度相关的代码示例，以提供更好的上下文学习示例。为了评估GRACE的有效性，我们在三个漏洞检测数据集（即Devign、Reveal和Big-Vul）上进行了实证研究。结果表明，GRACE在这三个数据集上的F1分数至少超越六个先进漏洞检测基线28.65%。因此，我们的研究强调了将图结构信息和上下文学习集成到LLM中进行漏洞检测的有效性。这些发现激励进一步研究为特定漏洞类型定制此类方法或将其适用于其他安全任务。","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":[],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["Devign","Reveal","Big-Vul"],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Outperforms 6 state-of-the-art baselines by at least 28.65% in F1 score across Devign, Reveal, and Big-Vul datasets.","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":2,"bibtex":"@article{lu2024grace,\\n  title={GRACE: Empowering LLM-based software vulnerability detection with graph structure and in-context learning},\\n  author={Lu, Guilong and Ju, Xiaolin and Chen, Xiang and Pei, Wenlong and Cai, Zhilong},\\n  journal={Journal of Systems and Software},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"luo2024fellmvp","title":"FELLMVP: An Ensemble LLM Framework for Classifying Smart Contract Vulnerabilities","authors":"Luo, Yu and Xu, Weifeng and Andersson, Karl and Hossain, Mohammad Shahadat and Xu, Dianxiang","year":2024,"venue":"2024 IEEE International Conference on Blockchain (Blockchain)","abstract":"The rapid expansion of smart contracts on blockchain platforms has significantly advanced the automation of transactions and agreements. However, the growing reliance on smart contracts increases security risks due to their immutable nature and interactions with digital assets. Existing vulnerability detection methods often fail to adapt to new and complex attack vectors and struggle to accurately predict specific vulnerability types. This paper introduces FELLMVP 1, a novel framework that integrates ensemble learning with Large Language Models (LLMs) to classify vulnerabilities in smart contracts. FELLMVP starts with the parsing of Solidity files to construct call graphs and Contract-External Function-Call (CEC) files for contract analysis. It fine-tunes eight LLMs, each targeted at detecting specific types of vulnerabilities and culminates and deploys an ensemble model that leverages the collective predictive capabilities of these LLMs. FELLMVP was evaluated on 15,637 real-world smart contracts spanning eight types of vulnerabilities, demonstrating superior performance over existing methods with an accuracy of 98.8% and F1 scores of 88%. FELLMVP also outperforms other LLMs such as Llama2-7b, CodeLlama, and Falcon-7b by 5 % -12 % on F1 score. Additionally, a case study using ChatGPT-4 to locate vulnerable code in smart contracts reveals that FELLMVP's prediction of specific vulnerability types enhances the debugging process compared to binary outcomes.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["fine-tuning"],"system_name":"FELLMVP","summary":"Introduces FELLMVP, an ensemble of 8 fine-tuned LLMs for smart contract vulnerability classification, achieving 98.8% accuracy and 88% F1 on 15,637 contracts across 8 vulnerability types.","summary_zh":"推出FELLMVP，集成8个微调LLM进行智能合约漏洞分类，在15637个合约和8种漏洞类型上达到98.8%准确率和88% F1。","contributions":["Introduces FELLMVP, integrating ensemble learning with fine-tuned LLMs for smart contract vulnerability classification.","Parses Solidity files to construct call graphs and Contract-External Function-Call (CEC) files for analysis.","Fine-tunes eight LLMs, each targeting specific vulnerability types, then deploys an ensemble model.","Achieves 98.8% accuracy and 88% F1 on 15,637 real-world smart contracts across 8 vulnerability types.","Outperforms Llama2-7b, CodeLlama, and Falcon-7b by 5%-12% on F1 score."],"contributions_zh":["推出FELLMVP，将集成学习与微调LLM结合用于智能合约漏洞分类。","解析Solidity文件以构建调用图和合约-外部函数-调用（CEC）文件进行分析。","微调8个LLM，每个针对特定漏洞类型，然后部署集成模型。","在15637个真实世界智能合约和8种漏洞类型上达到98.8%准确率和88% F1。","在F1分数上超越Llama2-7b、CodeLlama和Falcon-7b 5%-12%。"],"abstract_zh":"区块链平台上智能合约的快速扩展极大地推进了交易和协议的自动化。然而，对智能合约日益增长的依赖由于其不可变性和与数字资产的交互而增加了安全风险。现有的漏洞检测方法通常无法适应新的和复杂的攻击向量，并且难以准确预测特定的漏洞类型。本文介绍了FELLMVP，一种将集成学习与大语言模型（LLM）集成以对智能合约中的漏洞进行分类的新框架。FELLMVP首先解析Solidity文件以构建调用图和合约-外部函数-调用（CEC）文件进行合约分析。它微调了八个LLM，每个针对检测特定类型的漏洞，最终部署一个利用这些LLM集体预测能力的集成模型。FELLMVP在涵盖八种漏洞类型的15637个真实世界智能合约上进行了评估，表现出优于现有方法的性能，准确率为98.8%，F1分数为88%。FELLMVP还在F1分数上超越了其他LLM如Llama2-7b、CodeLlama和Falcon-7b 5%-12%。此外，一个使用ChatGPT-4定位智能合约中漏洞代码的案例研究表明，FELLMVP对特定漏洞类型的预测与二进制结果相比增强了调试过程。","experiment":{"language":["Solidity"],"platform":[],"target_domain":["smart contracts"],"llm":["ChatGPT-4","Llama2-7b","CodeLlama","Falcon-7b"],"model_family":["GPT","LLaMA","CodeLlama","Falcon"],"model_size":["7B"],"fine_tuning":true,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"15,637 real-world smart contracts, 8 vulnerability types","baselines":["Llama2-7b","CodeLlama","Falcon-7b"],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"98.8% accuracy and 88% F1 score; outperforms Llama2-7b, CodeLlama, Falcon-7b by 5%-12% on F1.","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@inproceedings{luo2024fellmvp,\\n  title={FELLMVP: An Ensemble LLM Framework for Classifying Smart Contract Vulnerabilities},\\n  author={Luo, Yu and Xu, Weifeng and Andersson, Karl and Hossain, Mohammad Shahadat and Xu, Dianxiang},\\n  booktitle={2024 IEEE International Conference on Blockchain (Blockchain)},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"ma2024combining","title":"Combining Fine-Tuning and LLM-based Agents for Intuitive Smart Contract Auditing with Justifications","authors":"Ma, Wei and Wu, Daoyuan and Sun, Yuqiang and Wang, Tianwen and Liu, Shangqing and Zhang, Jian and Xue, Yue and Liu, Yang","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2403.16073","abstract":"Smart contracts are decentralized applications built atop blockchains like Ethereum. Recent research has shown that large language models (LLMs) have potential in auditing smart contracts, but the state-of-the-art indicates that even GPT-4 can achieve only 30% precision (when both decision and justification are correct). This is likely because off-the-shelf LLMs were primarily pre-trained on a general text/code corpus and not finetuned on the specific domain of Solidity smart contract auditing. In this paper, we propose iAudit, a general framework that combines fine-tuning and LLM-based agents for intuitive smart contract auditing with justifications. Specifically, iAudit is inspired by the observation that expert human auditors first perceive what could be wrong and then perform a detailed analysis of the code to identify the cause. As such, iAudit employs a two-stage fine-tuning approach: it first tunes a Detector model to make decisions and then tunes a Reasoner model to generate causes of vulnerabilities. However, fine-tuning alone faces challenges in accurately identifying the optimal cause of a vulnerability. Therefore, we introduce two LLM-based agents, the Ranker and Critic, to iteratively select and debate the most suitable cause of vulnerability based on the output of the fine-tuned Reasoner model. To evaluate iAudit, we collected a balanced dataset with 1,734 positive and 1,810 negative samples to fine-tune iAudit. We then compared it with traditional fine-tuned models (CodeBERT, GraphCodeBERT, CodeT5, and UnixCoder) as well as prompt learning-based LLMs (GPT4, GPT-3.5, and CodeLlama-13b/34b). On a dataset of 263 real smart contract vulnerabilities, iAudit achieves an F1 score of 91.21% and an accuracy of 91.11%. The causes generated by iAudit achieved a consistency of about 38% compared to the ground truth causes.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["fine-tuning"],"system_name":"iAudit","summary":"Proposes iAudit, combining two-stage fine-tuning (Detector+Reasoner) with LLM agents (Ranker+Critic) for smart contract auditing, achieving 91.21% F1 on 263 real vulnerabilities.","summary_zh":"提出iAudit，结合两阶段微调（检测器+推理器）与LLM代理（排序器+评论者）进行智能合约审计，在263个真实漏洞上达到91.21% F1。","contributions":["Proposes iAudit, combining fine-tuning and LLM-based agents for smart contract auditing with justifications.","Employs two-stage fine-tuning: a Detector model for decisions and a Reasoner model for vulnerability cause generation.","Introduces Ranker and Critic LLM agents to iteratively select and debate the most suitable vulnerability cause.","Achieves 91.21% F1 score and 91.11% accuracy on 263 real smart contract vulnerabilities.","Compares against CodeBERT, GraphCodeBERT, CodeT5, UnixCoder, GPT-4, GPT-3.5, and CodeLlama-13b/34b."],"contributions_zh":["提出iAudit，将微调与基于LLM的代理结合，用于带有理由的智能合约审计。","采用两阶段微调：检测器模型用于决策，推理器模型用于漏洞原因生成。","引入排序器和评论者LLM代理，迭代选择和辩论最合适的漏洞原因。","在263个真实智能合约漏洞上达到91.21%的F1分数和91.11%的准确率。","与CodeBERT、GraphCodeBERT、CodeT5、UnixCoder、GPT-4、GPT-3.5和CodeLlama-13b/34b进行比较。"],"abstract_zh":"智能合约是构建在以太坊等区块链之上的去中心化应用。最近的研究表明大语言模型（LLM）在审计智能合约方面具有潜力，但最先进的方法表明即使GPT-4也只能达到30%的精度（当决策和理由都正确时）。这可能是因为现成的LLM主要在通用文本/代码语料上预训练，没有针对Solidity智能合约审计的特定领域进行微调。本文提出了iAudit，一个结合微调和基于LLM的代理的通用框架，用于带有理由的直观智能合约审计。具体而言，iAudit的灵感来自于专家人类审计员首先感知可能出错的地方然后对代码进行详细分析以识别原因的观察。因此，iAudit采用两阶段微调方法：首先调整检测器模型做出决策，然后调整推理器模型生成漏洞原因。然而，仅靠微调在准确识别漏洞最佳原因方面面临挑战。因此，我们引入了两个基于LLM的代理——排序器和评论者，根据微调推理器模型的输出迭代选择和辩论最合适的漏洞原因。为了评估iAudit，我们收集了一个包含1734个正样本和1810个负样本的平衡数据集来微调iAudit。然后我们将其与传统微调模型（CodeBERT、GraphCodeBERT、CodeT5和UnixCoder）以及基于提示学习的LLM（GPT4、GPT-3.5和CodeLlama-13b/34b）进行了比较。在263个真实智能合约漏洞的数据集上，iAudit达到了91.21%的F1分数和91.11%的准确率。iAudit生成的原因与真实原因相比达到了约38%的一致性。","experiment":{"language":["Solidity"],"platform":["Ethereum"],"target_domain":["smart contracts"],"llm":["GPT-4","GPT-3.5","CodeLlama-13b","CodeLlama-34b"],"model_family":["GPT","CodeLlama"],"model_size":["13B","34B"],"fine_tuning":true,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"1,734 positive + 1,810 negative samples for fine-tuning; 263 real vulnerabilities for evaluation","baselines":["CodeBERT","GraphCodeBERT","CodeT5","UnixCoder","GPT-4","GPT-3.5","CodeLlama-13b","CodeLlama-34b"],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"91.21% F1 score and 91.11% accuracy on 263 real smart contract vulnerabilities; 38% cause consistency with ground truth.","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@article{ma2024combining,\\n  title={Combining Fine-Tuning and LLM-based Agents for Intuitive Smart Contract Auditing with Justifications},\\n  author={Ma, Wei and Wu, Daoyuan and Sun, Yuqiang and Wang, Tianwen and Liu, Shangqing and Zhang, Jian and Xue, Yue and Liu, Yang},\\n  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2403.16073},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"mahyari2024harnessing","title":"Harnessing the Power of LLMs in Source Code Vulnerability Detection","authors":"Mahyari, Andrew A","year":2024,"venue":"MILCOM 2024-2024 IEEE Military Communications Conference (MILCOM)","abstract":"Software vulnerabilities, caused by unintentional flaws in source code, are a primary root cause of cyberattacks. Static analysis of source code has been widely used to detect these unintentional defects introduced by software developers. Large Language Models (LLMs) have demonstrated human-like conversational abilities due to their capacity to capture complex patterns in sequential data, such as natural languages. In this paper, we harness LLMs’ capabilities to analyze source code and detect known vulnerabilities. To ensure the proposed vulnerability detection method is universal across multiple programming languages, we convert source code to LLVM IR and train LLMs on these intermediate representations. We conduct extensive experiments on various LLM architectures and compare their accuracy. Our comprehensive experiments on real-world and synthetic codes from NVD and SARD demonstrate high accuracy in identifying source code vulnerabilities.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"system_name":"","summary":"Trains LLMs on LLVM IR representations of source code for language-universal vulnerability detection, evaluated on NVD and SARD with high accuracy.","summary_zh":"在源代码的LLVM IR表示上训练LLM，实现跨语言通用漏洞检测，在NVD和SARD上评估并取得高准确率。","contributions":["Converts source code to LLVM IR for language-universal vulnerability detection using LLMs.","Conducts extensive experiments on various LLM architectures for vulnerability detection.","Evaluates on real-world (NVD) and synthetic (SARD) code datasets, demonstrating high accuracy.","Proposes a universal approach applicable across multiple programming languages via intermediate representation."],"contributions_zh":["将源代码转换为LLVM IR，使用LLM进行跨语言通用漏洞检测。","在各种LLM架构上进行了广泛的漏洞检测实验。","在真实世界（NVD）和合成（SARD）代码数据集上进行评估，展示了高准确率。","提出了一种通过中间表示适用于多种编程语言的通用方法。"],"abstract_zh":"软件漏洞由源代码中的无意缺陷引起，是网络攻击的主要根源。源代码的静态分析被广泛用于检测软件开发人员引入的这些无意缺陷。大语言模型（LLM）由于其捕获序列数据（如自然语言）中复杂模式的能力，已展示出类人的对话能力。在本文中，我们利用LLM的能力来分析源代码并检测已知漏洞。为确保所提出的漏洞检测方法在多种编程语言中具有通用性，我们将源代码转换为LLVM IR并在这些中间表示上训练LLM。我们在各种LLM架构上进行了广泛的实验并比较了它们的准确性。我们对来自NVD和SARD的真实世界和合成代码的综合实验证明了识别源代码漏洞的高准确性。","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":[],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":true,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["NVD","SARD"],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"High accuracy in identifying source code vulnerabilities on NVD and SARD using LLVM IR representation.","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@inproceedings{mahyari2024harnessing,\\n  title={Harnessing the Power of LLMs in Source Code Vulnerability Detection},\\n  author={Mahyari, Andrew A},\\n  booktitle={MILCOM 2024-2024 IEEE Military Communications Conference (MILCOM)},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"mao2024multi","title":"Multi-role consensus through llms discussions for vulnerability detection","authors":"Mao, Zhenyy and Li, Jialong and Jin, Dongming and Li, Munan and Tei, Kenji","year":2024,"venue":"2024 IEEE 24th International Conference on Software Quality, Reliability, and Security Companion (QRS-C)","abstract":"Recent advancements in large language models (LLMs) have highlighted the potential for vulnerability de-tection, a crucial component of software quality assurance. Despite this progress, most studies have been limited to the perspective of a single role, usually testers, lacking diverse viewpoints from different roles in a typical software de-velopment life-cycle, including both developers and testers. To this end, this paper introduces a multi-role approach to employ LLMs to act as different roles simulating a real-life code review process and engaging in discussions toward a consensus on the existence and classification of vulnerabilities in the code. Preliminary evaluation of this approach indicates a 13.48% increase in the precision rate, an 18.25% increase in the recall rate, and a 16.13% increase in the F1 score.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"system_name":"","summary":"Introduces a multi-role LLM discussion approach simulating code review with developers and testers, improving precision by 13.48%, recall by 18.25%, and F1 by 16.13%.","summary_zh":"引入多角色LLM讨论方法，模拟开发者和测试者的代码审查过程，精度提高13.48%，召回率提高18.25%，F1提高16.13%。","contributions":["Introduces a multi-role approach using LLMs as developers and testers to simulate real-life code review for vulnerability detection.","Engages multiple LLM roles in discussion toward consensus on vulnerability existence and classification.","Achieves 13.48% increase in precision, 18.25% increase in recall, and 16.13% increase in F1 score."],"contributions_zh":["引入多角色方法，使用LLM扮演开发者和测试者，模拟真实代码审查过程进行漏洞检测。","让多个LLM角色参与讨论，就漏洞的存在和分类达成共识。","精度提高13.48%，召回率提高18.25%，F1分数提高16.13%。"],"abstract_zh":"大语言模型（LLM）的最新进展凸显了漏洞检测的潜力，这是软件质量保证的关键组成部分。尽管取得了进展，但大多数研究仅限于单一角色（通常是测试者）的视角，缺乏典型软件开发生命周期中不同角色（包括开发者和测试者）的多样化观点。为此，本文引入了一种多角色方法，使用LLM扮演不同角色来模拟真实的代码审查过程，并就代码中漏洞的存在和分类进行讨论以达成共识。对这种方法的初步评估表明，精度提高了13.48%，召回率提高了18.25%，F1分数提高了16.13%。","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":[],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"13.48% precision increase, 18.25% recall increase, 16.13% F1 increase.","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@inproceedings{mao2024multi,\\n  title={Multi-role consensus through llms discussions for vulnerability detection},\\n  author={Mao, Zhenyy and Li, Jialong and Jin, Dongming and Li, Munan and Tei, Kenji},\\n  booktitle={2024 IEEE 24th International Conference on Software Quality, Reliability, and Security Companion (QRS-C)},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"mao2024towards","title":"Towards Effectively Detecting and Explaining Vulnerabilities Using Large Language Models","authors":"Mao, Qiheng and Li, Zhenhao and Hu, Xing and Liu, Kui and Xia, Xin and Sun, Jianling","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2406.09701","abstract":"Software vulnerabilities pose significant risks to the security and integrity of software systems. Prior studies have proposed a series of approaches to vulnerability detection using deep learning or pre-trained models. However, there is still a lack of vulnerability's detailed explanation for understanding apart from detecting its occurrence. Recently, large language models (LLMs) have shown a remarkable capability in the comprehension of complicated context and content generation, which brings opportunities for the detection and explanation of vulnerabilities of LLMs. In this paper, we conduct a comprehensive study to investigate the capabilities of LLMs in detecting and explaining vulnerabilities and propose LLMVulExp, a framework that utilizes LLMs for vulnerability detection and explanation. Under specialized fine-tuning for vulnerability explanation, LLMVulExp not only detects the types of vulnerabilities in the code but also analyzes the code context to generate the cause, location, and repair suggestions for these vulnerabilities. We find that LLMVulExp can effectively enable the LLMs to perform vulnerability detection (e.g., over 90% F1 score on SeVC dataset) and explanation. We also explore the potential of using advanced strategies such as Chain-of-Thought (CoT) to guide the LLMs concentrating on vulnerability-prone code and achieve promising results.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["fine-tuning"],"system_name":"LLMVulExp","summary":"Proposes LLMVulExp for vulnerability detection and explanation via fine-tuned LLMs, achieving over 90% F1 on SeVC dataset with CoT-guided analysis.","summary_zh":"提出LLMVulExp，通过微调LLM进行漏洞检测和解释，在SeVC数据集上达到90%以上F1，并采用CoT引导分析。","contributions":["Proposes LLMVulExp, a framework using fine-tuned LLMs for both vulnerability detection and explanation.","Generates vulnerability cause, location, and repair suggestions through code context analysis.","Achieves over 90% F1 score on the SeVC dataset for vulnerability detection.","Explores Chain-of-Thought (CoT) strategies to guide LLMs in concentrating on vulnerability-prone code."],"contributions_zh":["提出LLMVulExp，一种使用微调LLM同时进行漏洞检测和解释的框架。","通过代码上下文分析生成漏洞原因、位置和修复建议。","在SeVC数据集上的漏洞检测F1分数超过90%。","探索思维链（CoT）策略引导LLM关注易受漏洞影响的代码。"],"abstract_zh":"软件漏洞对软件系统的安全性和完整性构成重大风险。先前的研究提出了一系列使用深度学习或预训练模型进行漏洞检测的方法。然而，除了检测漏洞发生之外，仍然缺乏对漏洞的详细解释以便理解。最近，大语言模型（LLM）在复杂上下文理解和内容生成方面展示了卓越的能力，这为LLM检测和解释漏洞带来了机遇。在本文中，我们进行了全面研究以调查LLM在检测和解释漏洞方面的能力，并提出了LLMVulExp，一种利用LLM进行漏洞检测和解释的框架。在针对漏洞解释的专门微调下，LLMVulExp不仅检测代码中的漏洞类型，还分析代码上下文以生成这些漏洞的原因、位置和修复建议。我们发现LLMVulExp可以有效地使LLM执行漏洞检测（例如，在SeVC数据集上F1分数超过90%）和解释。我们还探索了使用思维链（CoT）等高级策略引导LLM关注易受漏洞影响的代码，并取得了有前途的结果。","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":[],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":true,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["SeVC"],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Over 90% F1 score on SeVC dataset for vulnerability detection.","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@article{mao2024towards,\\n  title={Towards Effectively Detecting and Explaining Vulnerabilities Using Large Language Models},\\n  author={Mao, Qiheng and Li, Zhenhao and Hu, Xing and Liu, Kui and Xia, Xin and Sun, Jianling},\\n  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2406.09701},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"mathews2024llbezpeky","title":"Llbezpeky: Leveraging large language models for vulnerability detection","authors":"Mathews, Noble Saji and Brus, Yelizaveta and Aafer, Yousra and Nagappan, Meiyappan and McIntosh, Shane","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2401.01269","abstract":"Despite the continued research and progress in building secure systems, Android applications continue to be ridden with vulnerabilities, necessitating effective detection methods. Current strategies involving static and dynamic analysis tools come with limitations like overwhelming number of false positives and limited scope of analysis which make either difficult to adopt. Over the past years, machine learning based approaches have been extensively explored for vulnerability detection, but its real-world applicability is constrained by data requirements and feature engineering challenges. Large Language Models (LLMs), with their vast parameters, have shown tremendous potential in understanding semnatics in human as well as programming languages. We dive into the efficacy of LLMs for detecting vulnerabilities in the context of Android security. We focus on building an AI-driven workflow to assist developers in identifying and rectifying vulnerabilities. Our experiments show that LLMs outperform our expectations in finding issues within applications correctly flagging insecure apps in 91.67% of cases in the Ghera benchmark. We use inferences from our experiments towards building a robust and actionable vulnerability detection system and demonstrate its effectiveness. Our experiments also shed light on how different various simple configurations can affect the True Positive (TP) and False Positive (FP) rates.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"system_name":"LLbezpeky","summary":"Proposes LLbezpeky, an LLM-driven workflow for Android vulnerability detection, correctly flagging insecure apps in 91.67% of cases on the Ghera benchmark.","summary_zh":"提出LLbezpeky，一个LLM驱动的Android漏洞检测工作流，在Ghera基准上正确标记91.67%的不安全应用。","contributions":["Proposes LLbezpeky, an AI-driven workflow for Android vulnerability detection and rectification.","Demonstrates LLMs correctly flag insecure apps in 91.67% of cases on the Ghera benchmark.","Builds a robust and actionable vulnerability detection system for Android applications.","Investigates how different configurations affect True Positive and False Positive rates."],"contributions_zh":["提出LLbezpeky，一个AI驱动的Android漏洞检测和修复工作流。","证明LLM在Ghera基准上正确标记了91.67%的不安全应用。","构建了一个稳健且可操作的Android应用漏洞检测系统。","研究了不同配置如何影响真阳性率和假阳性率。"],"abstract_zh":"尽管在构建安全系统方面持续研究和进步，Android应用程序仍然充满漏洞，需要有效的检测方法。目前涉及静态和动态分析工具的策略存在局限性，如大量误报和有限的分析范围，这使得两者都难以采用。在过去几年中，基于机器学习的方法已被广泛探索用于漏洞检测，但其在真实世界中的适用性受到数据需求和特征工程挑战的限制。大语言模型（LLM）凭借其庞大的参数，在理解人类语言和编程语言语义方面展示了巨大的潜力。我们深入研究了LLM在Android安全背景下检测漏洞的功效。我们专注于构建一个AI驱动的工作流，帮助开发人员识别和修复漏洞。我们的实验表明，LLM在发现应用程序问题方面超出了我们的预期，在Ghera基准中正确标记了91.67%的不安全应用。我们利用实验中的推断来构建一个稳健且可操作的漏洞检测系统，并展示了其有效性。我们的实验还揭示了不同简单配置如何影响真阳性（TP）和假阳性（FP）率。","experiment":{"language":["Java"],"platform":["Android"],"target_domain":["Android applications"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["Ghera"],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Correctly flags insecure apps in 91.67% of cases on the Ghera benchmark.","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@article{mathews2024llbezpeky,\\n  title={Llbezpeky: Leveraging large language models for vulnerability detection},\\n  author={Mathews, Noble Saji and Brus, Yelizaveta and Aafer, Yousra and Nagappan, Meiyappan and McIntosh, Shane},\\n  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2401.01269},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"mishra2024ai","title":"AI-Augmented Vulnerability Detection and Patching","authors":"Mishra, Poornaditya","year":2024,"venue":"","abstract":"Software vulnerabilities remain a persistent threat, and the increasing use of AI-generated code introduces new security challenges. While Large Language Models (LLMs) excel at code generation, they often struggle to consistently produce secure code or apply targeted vulnerability fixes. This work proposes a novel system that bridges this gap by combining the strengths of graph-based deep learning and LLMs for automated vulnerability detection and patching.We first model vulnerability detection as graph representation learning via Graph Attention Network (GAT) to accurately identify vulnerabilities in code, leveraging the rich structural information encoded in Code Property Graphs (CPGs) and Abstract Syntax Trees (ASTs). Our system then leverages the GAT's predictions to guide an LLM, providing both the vulnerability type and the precise location within the code requiring a patch. This targeted guidance enables the LLM to generate more secure and contextually appropriate code modifications.Through experiments on a dataset of real-world vulnerable code, we demonstrate the effectiveness of our approach in detecting critical vulnerabilities like SQL injection and session hijacking. We further evaluate the quality of the LLM-generated patches, showing a significant improvement in security when guided by our system. This research paves the way for more secure and reliable AI-assisted software development by integrating deep learning-based vulnerability analysis with the generative capabilities of LLMs.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"system_name":"","summary":"Combines Graph Attention Networks on Code Property Graphs with LLM-guided patching for automated vulnerability detection and repair of SQL injection and session hijacking.","summary_zh":"将代码属性图上的图注意力网络与LLM引导的补丁生成结合，用于SQL注入和会话劫持的自动化漏洞检测和修复。","contributions":["Models vulnerability detection as graph representation learning via Graph Attention Networks (GAT) on Code Property Graphs and ASTs.","Uses GAT predictions to guide LLM patching with vulnerability type and precise code location.","Demonstrates effectiveness in detecting SQL injection and session hijacking vulnerabilities.","Shows significant improvement in patch security when LLM is guided by the vulnerability detection system."],"contributions_zh":["将漏洞检测建模为在代码属性图和AST上通过图注意力网络（GAT）进行的图表示学习。","使用GAT预测结果引导LLM生成补丁，提供漏洞类型和精确代码位置。","展示了在检测SQL注入和会话劫持漏洞方面的有效性。","表明当LLM由漏洞检测系统引导时，补丁安全性显著提高。"],"abstract_zh":"软件漏洞仍然是一个持续的威胁，AI生成代码的使用增加带来了新的安全挑战。虽然大语言模型（LLM）擅长代码生成，但它们通常难以持续生成安全代码或应用有针对性的漏洞修复。这项工作提出了一个新颖的系统，通过结合基于图的深度学习和LLM的优势来弥合这一差距，实现自动化漏洞检测和补丁生成。我们首先通过图注意力网络（GAT）将漏洞检测建模为图表示学习，以准确识别代码中的漏洞，利用代码属性图（CPG）和抽象语法树（AST）中编码的丰富结构信息。然后我们的系统利用GAT的预测来引导LLM，提供漏洞类型和需要补丁的代码中的精确位置。这种有针对性的引导使LLM能够生成更安全和上下文适当的代码修改。通过在真实世界漏洞代码数据集上的实验，我们展示了我们的方法在检测SQL注入和会话劫持等关键漏洞方面的有效性。我们进一步评估了LLM生成补丁的质量，表明在我们系统引导下安全性有显著改善。这项研究通过将基于深度学习的漏洞分析与LLM的生成能力相结合，为更安全和可靠的AI辅助软件开发铺平了道路。","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":[],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":["SQL injection","session hijacking"],"key_results":"Significant improvement in patch security when LLM is guided by GAT-based vulnerability detection.","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@article{mishra2024ai,\\n  title={AI-Augmented Vulnerability Detection and Patching},\\n  author={Mishra, Poornaditya},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"purba2023software","title":"Software vulnerability detection using large language models","authors":"Purba, Moumita Das and Ghosh, Arpita and Radford, Benjamin J and Chu, Bill","year":2023,"venue":"2023 IEEE 34th International Symposium on Software Reliability Engineering Workshops (ISSREW)","abstract":"Software development is among the first demonstrations of using Large Language Models (LLMs) to enhance human productivity. Such a co-pilot paradigm envisions LLM working side-by-side with human developers to assist in programming tasks. Ensuring the security of software products is a critical factor for the success of such a paradigm. There have been various anecdotal reports on the success of using LLMs to detect vulnerabilities in programs. This paper reports a set of experiments applying four well-known LLMs to two widely referenced public datasets to evaluate the performance of LLMs in detecting software vulnerabilities. Our results show a significant performance gap between these LLMs and those from popular static analysis tools, primarily due to their high false positive rates. However, LLMs show great promise in identifying subtle patterns commonly associated with software vulnerabilities. This observation suggests a possible path forward by combining LLMs and other program analysis techniques to achieve better software vulnerability detection.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["fine-tuning"],"system_name":"","summary":"Evaluates 4 LLMs on 2 public vulnerability datasets, finding high false positive rates compared to static analysis tools but promise in identifying subtle vulnerability patterns.","summary_zh":"在2个公开漏洞数据集上评估4个LLM，发现与静态分析工具相比误报率高，但在识别细微漏洞模式方面有前景。","contributions":["Evaluates four well-known LLMs on two widely referenced public datasets for vulnerability detection.","Identifies a significant performance gap between LLMs and static analysis tools, primarily due to high false positive rates.","Shows LLMs have great promise in identifying subtle patterns commonly associated with software vulnerabilities.","Suggests a path forward by combining LLMs with other program analysis techniques for better vulnerability detection."],"contributions_zh":["在两个广泛引用的公开数据集上评估四个知名LLM的漏洞检测能力。","识别出LLM与静态分析工具之间的显著性能差距，主要由于高误报率。","表明LLM在识别与软件漏洞相关的细微模式方面具有很大前景。","建议通过将LLM与其他程序分析技术结合来实现更好的漏洞检测。"],"abstract_zh":"软件开发是使用大语言模型（LLM）提高人类生产力的首批示范之一。这种协同驾驶范式设想LLM与人类开发人员并肩工作，协助编程任务。确保软件产品的安全性是这种范式成功的关键因素。关于使用LLM检测程序中漏洞的成功案例已有各种报道。本文报告了一组实验，将四个知名LLM应用于两个广泛引用的公开数据集，以评估LLM在检测软件漏洞方面的性能。我们的结果显示，这些LLM与流行的静态分析工具之间存在显著的性能差距，主要原因是它们的高误报率。然而，LLM在识别与软件漏洞相关的细微模式方面显示出巨大的前景。这一观察表明，通过将LLM与其他程序分析技术相结合，可能会实现更好的软件漏洞检测。","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":[],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"2 public datasets","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Significant performance gap vs static analysis tools due to high false positive rates; LLMs show promise in identifying subtle vulnerability patterns.","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@inproceedings{purba2023software,\\n  title={Software vulnerability detection using large language models},\\n  author={Purba, Moumita Das and Ghosh, Arpita and Radford, Benjamin J and Chu, Bill},\\n  booktitle={2023 IEEE 34th International Symposium on Software Reliability Engineering Workshops (ISSREW)},\\n  year={2023}\\n}"},{"id":"sakaoglu2023kartal","title":"KARTAL: Web Application Vulnerability Hunting Using Large Language Models: Novel method for detecting logical vulnerabilities in web applications with finetuned Large Language Models","authors":"Sakaoglu, Sinan","year":2023,"venue":"","abstract":"Broken Access Control is the most serious web application security risk as published by Open Worldwide Application Security Project (OWASP). This category has highly complex vulnerabilities such as Broken Object Level Authorization (BOLA) and Exposure of Sensitive Information. Finding such critical vulnerabilities in large software systems requires intelligent and automated tools. State-of-the-art (SOTA) research including hybrid application security testing tools, algorithmic brute forcers, and artificial intelligence has shown great promise in detection. Nevertheless, there exists a gap in research for reliably identifying logical and context-dependant Broken Access Control vulnerabilities. We modeled the problem as text classification and proposed KARTAL, a novel method for web application vulnerability detection using a Large Language Model (LLM). It consists of 3 components: Fuzzer, Prompter, and Detector. The Fuzzer is responsible for methodically collecting application behavior. The Prompter processes the data from the Fuzzer and formulates a prompt. Finally, the Detector uses an LLM which we have finetuned for detecting vulnerabilities. In the study, we investigate the performance, key factors, and limitations of the proposed method. Our research reveals the need for a labeled Broken Access Control vulnerability dataset in the cybersecurity field. Thus, we custom-generate our own dataset using an auto-regressive LLM with SOTA few-shot prompting techniques. We experiment with finetuning 3 types of decoder-only pre-trained transformers for detecting 2 sophisticated vulnerabilities. Our best model attained an accuracy of 87.19%, with an F1 score of 0.82. By using hardware acceleration on a consumer-grade laptop, our fastest model can make up to 539 predictions per second. The experiments on varying the training sample size demonstrated the great learning capabilities of our model. Every 400 samples added to training resulted in an average MCC score improvement of 19.58%. Furthermore, the dynamic properties of KARTAL enable inferencetime adaption to the application domain, resulting in reduced false positives.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["fine-tuning"],"system_name":"KARTAL","summary":"Proposes KARTAL, a 3-component LLM-based framework for detecting Broken Access Control vulnerabilities in web applications, achieving 87.19% accuracy with fine-tuned decoder-only transformers.","summary_zh":"提出KARTAL，一个由三个组件组成的基于LLM的框架，用于检测Web应用中的访问控制漏洞，使用微调的仅解码器Transformer达到87.19%的准确率。","contributions":["Proposes KARTAL, a novel 3-component (Fuzzer, Prompter, Detector) method for web application vulnerability detection using fine-tuned LLMs.","Addresses the gap in detecting logical and context-dependent Broken Access Control vulnerabilities (BOLA, Sensitive Information Exposure).","Custom-generates a labeled Broken Access Control vulnerability dataset using auto-regressive LLMs with few-shot prompting.","Achieves 87.19% accuracy and 0.82 F1 score by fine-tuning decoder-only pre-trained transformers for 2 vulnerability types.","Demonstrates inference-time domain adaptation reducing false positives, with fastest model making up to 539 predictions per second on consumer hardware."],"contributions_zh":["提出KARTAL，一种新颖的由三个组件（Fuzzer、Prompter、Detector）组成的Web应用漏洞检测方法，使用微调的LLM。","填补了检测逻辑性和上下文相关的访问控制漏洞（BOLA、敏感信息暴露）的研究空白。","使用自回归LLM和少样本提示技术自定义生成了标注的访问控制漏洞数据集。","通过微调仅解码器预训练Transformer检测2种漏洞类型，达到87.19%的准确率和0.82的F1分数。","展示了推理时领域自适应能力以减少误报，最快模型在消费级硬件上每秒可做539次预测。"],"abstract_zh":"访问控制漏洞是OWASP发布的最严重的Web应用安全风险。该类别包含高度复杂的漏洞，如对象级授权失败（BOLA）和敏感信息暴露。在大型软件系统中发现此类关键漏洞需要智能和自动化工具。包括混合应用安全测试工具、算法暴力破解器和人工智能在内的最先进研究在检测方面显示出巨大潜力。然而，在可靠识别逻辑性和上下文相关的访问控制漏洞方面存在研究空白。我们将问题建模为文本分类，并提出了KARTAL，一种使用大型语言模型（LLM）进行Web应用漏洞检测的新方法。它由3个组件组成：Fuzzer、Prompter和Detector。Fuzzer负责系统地收集应用行为。Prompter处理来自Fuzzer的数据并制定提示。最后，Detector使用我们微调过的LLM来检测漏洞。在研究中，我们调查了所提方法的性能、关键因素和局限性。我们的研究揭示了网络安全领域对标注访问控制漏洞数据集的需求。因此，我们使用自回归LLM和最先进的少样本提示技术自定义生成了自己的数据集。我们实验了微调3种仅解码器预训练Transformer来检测2种复杂漏洞。我们最好的模型达到了87.19%的准确率，F1分数为0.82。通过在消费级笔记本电脑上使用硬件加速，我们最快的模型每秒可做多达539次预测。改变训练样本量的实验展示了模型出色的学习能力。每增加400个样本，MCC分数平均提高19.58%。此外，KARTAL的动态属性使其能够在推理时适应应用领域，从而减少误报。","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":["web"],"target_domain":["web application"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":true,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":["Broken Access Control","BOLA","Sensitive Information Exposure"],"key_results":"Best model achieved 87.19% accuracy with F1 score of 0.82; fastest model makes 539 predictions per second; every 400 training samples improve MCC by 19.58%","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@inproceedings{sakaoglu2023kartal,\\n  title={KARTAL: Web Application Vulnerability Hunting Using Large Language Models},\\n  author={Sakaoglu, Sinan},\\n  year={2023}\\n}"},{"id":"shestov2024finetuning","title":"Finetuning large language models for vulnerability detection","authors":"Shestov, Alexey and Cheshkov, Anton and Levichev, Rodion and Mussabayev, Ravil and Zadorozhny, Pavel and Maslov, Evgeny and Vadim, Chibirev and Bulychev, Egor","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2401.17010","abstract":"This paper presents the results of finetuning large language models (LLMs) for the task of detecting vulnerabilities in Java source code. We leverage WizardCoder, a recent improvement of the state-of-the-art LLM StarCoder, and adapt it for vulnerability detection through further finetuning. To accelerate training, we modify WizardCoder’s training procedure, also we investigate optimal training regimes. For the imbalanced dataset with many more negative examples than positive, we also explore different techniques to improve classification performance. The finetuned WizardCoder model achieves improvement in ROC AUC and F1 measures on balanced and imbalanced vulnerability datasets over CodeBERT-like model, demonstrating the effectiveness of adapting pretrained LLMs for vulnerability detection in source code. The key contributions are finetuning the state-ofthe-art code LLM, WizardCoder, increasing its training speed without the performance harm, optimizing the training procedure and regimes, handling class imbalance, and improving performance on difficult vulnerability detection datasets. This demonstrates the potential for transfer learning by finetuning large pretrained language models for specialized source code analysis tasks.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["fine-tuning"],"summary":"Fine-tunes WizardCoder (based on StarCoder) for Java vulnerability detection, improving ROC AUC and F1 over CodeBERT-like models on imbalanced datasets.","summary_zh":"微调WizardCoder（基于StarCoder）用于Java漏洞检测，在不平衡数据集上的ROC AUC和F1优于类CodeBERT模型。","abstract_zh":"本文介绍了微调大型语言模型（LLM）用于Java源代码漏洞检测任务的结果。我们利用WizardCoder（最先进的LLM StarCoder的最新改进版本），通过进一步微调使其适用于漏洞检测。为加速训练，我们修改了WizardCoder的训练流程，同时研究了最优训练方案。对于正样本远少于负样本的不平衡数据集，我们还探索了不同的技术来提高分类性能。微调后的WizardCoder模型在平衡和不平衡漏洞数据集上的ROC AUC和F1指标优于类CodeBERT模型，证明了将预训练LLM适配于源代码漏洞检测的有效性。主要贡献包括微调最先进的代码LLM WizardCoder、在不损害性能的情况下提高训练速度、优化训练流程和方案、处理类别不平衡以及在困难的漏洞检测数据集上提高性能。","contributions":["Fine-tunes the state-of-the-art code LLM WizardCoder for vulnerability detection in Java source code.","Modifies WizardCoder's training procedure to accelerate training without performance degradation.","Investigates optimal training regimes and techniques for handling class imbalance in vulnerability datasets.","Achieves improvements in ROC AUC and F1 over CodeBERT-like models on both balanced and imbalanced datasets.","Demonstrates the potential of transfer learning from large pretrained code LLMs for specialized source code analysis tasks."],"contributions_zh":["微调最先进的代码LLM WizardCoder用于Java源代码的漏洞检测。","修改WizardCoder的训练流程以加速训练且不损害性能。","研究了处理漏洞数据集中类别不平衡问题的最优训练方案和技术。","在平衡和不平衡数据集上的ROC AUC和F1均优于类CodeBERT模型。","展示了从大型预训练代码LLM进行迁移学习用于专业源代码分析任务的潜力。"],"experiment":{"language":["Java"],"platform":[],"target_domain":["source code"],"llm":["WizardCoder","StarCoder"],"model_family":["StarCoder"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":true,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":["CodeBERT"],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Fine-tuned WizardCoder achieves improvement in ROC AUC and F1 over CodeBERT-like models on balanced and imbalanced vulnerability datasets","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@article{shestov2024finetuning,\\n  title={Finetuning large language models for vulnerability detection},\\n  author={Shestov, Alexey and Cheshkov, Anton and Levichev, Rodion and Mussabayev, Ravil and Zadorozhny, Pavel and Maslov, Evgeny and Vadim, Chibirev and Bulychev, Egor},\\n  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2401.17010},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"sindhwad2024vulnarmor","title":"VulnArmor: mitigating software vulnerabilities with code resolution and detection techniques","authors":"Sindhwad, Parul V and Ranka, Prateek and Muni, Siddhi and Kazi, Faruk","year":2024,"venue":"International Journal of Information Technology","abstract":"In today’s swiftly evolving digital environment, the security and dependability of software applications are crucial. In light of industries’ increasing reliance on software, identifying and mitigating vulnerabilities is essential for protecting data, systems, and user trust. With data-driven methodologies, there is increased interest in using Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) for software assurance to construct trustworthy software systems. This research addresses the urgent need for an automated and comprehensive approach to code resolution and vulnerability detection, providing a robust solution to improve software security and reduce potential risks. Code resolution is implemented by fine-tuning Large Language Models (LLM) like Generative Pre-Trained Transformers (GPT)-2, Text-to-Text Transfer Transformers (T5), Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers (BERT), and Large Language Model Meta AI (LLaMA). Secondly, vulnerable code detection plays a crucial role in evaluating the correctness of resolved code and identifying any remaining vulnerabilities. This essential step not only validates the efficacy of code resolution but also identifies areas where additional mitigation efforts are required. Utilizing Deep Learning (DL) models, the top performer of the study, Convolutional Neural Network (CNN), achieved a remarkable 93% accuracy rate, demonstrating its prowess in protecting software applications against potential attacks.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Proposes VulnArmor for code resolution via fine-tuning GPT-2/T5/BERT/LLaMA and vulnerability detection using DL models, with CNN achieving 93% accuracy.","summary_zh":"提出VulnArmor，通过微调GPT-2/T5/BERT/LLaMA进行代码修复，并使用深度学习模型进行漏洞检测，其中CNN达到93%的准确率。","abstract_zh":"在当今快速发展的数字环境中，软件应用的安全性和可靠性至关重要。鉴于各行业对软件的日益依赖，识别和缓解漏洞对于保护数据、系统和用户信任至关重要。随着数据驱动方法的发展，人们越来越关注使用人工智能（AI）和机器学习（ML）进行软件保障以构建可信的软件系统。本研究解决了对代码修复和漏洞检测的自动化综合方法的迫切需求，提供了一个强大的解决方案来提高软件安全性并降低潜在风险。代码修复通过微调大型语言模型（LLM）实现，包括生成式预训练Transformer（GPT）-2、文本到文本迁移Transformer（T5）、双向编码器表示Transformer（BERT）和大型语言模型Meta AI（LLaMA）。其次，漏洞代码检测在评估修复代码正确性和识别任何剩余漏洞方面起着至关重要的作用。这一关键步骤不仅验证了代码修复的效果，还识别了需要额外缓解措施的领域。利用深度学习（DL）模型，本研究的最佳表现者卷积神经网络（CNN）达到了93%的显著准确率，展示了其在保护软件应用免受潜在攻击方面的能力。","contributions":["Proposes VulnArmor, an automated comprehensive approach combining code resolution and vulnerability detection.","Fine-tunes LLMs including GPT-2, T5, BERT, and LLaMA for code resolution tasks.","Uses deep learning models for vulnerable code detection to validate resolved code correctness.","Achieves 93% accuracy with CNN as the top-performing model for vulnerability detection.","Addresses both code repair and residual vulnerability identification in a unified framework."],"contributions_zh":["提出VulnArmor，一种结合代码修复和漏洞检测的自动化综合方法。","微调包括GPT-2、T5、BERT和LLaMA在内的LLM用于代码修复任务。","使用深度学习模型进行漏洞代码检测，以验证修复代码的正确性。","CNN作为最优模型在漏洞检测中达到93%的准确率。","在统一框架中同时解决代码修复和残留漏洞识别问题。"],"system_name":"VulnArmor","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["source code"],"llm":["GPT-2","T5","BERT","LLaMA"],"model_family":["GPT","T5","BERT","LLaMA"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":true,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"CNN achieved 93% accuracy for vulnerability detection","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":2,"bibtex":"@article{sindhwad2024vulnarmor,\\n  title={VulnArmor: mitigating software vulnerabilities with code resolution and detection techniques},\\n  author={Sindhwad, Parul V and Ranka, Prateek and Muni, Siddhi and Kazi, Faruk},\\n  journal={International Journal of Information Technology},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"steenhoek2024comprehensive","title":"A Comprehensive Study of the Capabilities of Large Language Models for Vulnerability Detection","authors":"Steenhoek, Benjamin and Rahman, Md Mahbubur and Roy, Monoshi Kumar and Alam, Mirza Sanjida and Barr, Earl T and Le, Wei","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2403.17218","abstract":"Abstract—Large Language Models (LLMs) have demonstrated great potential for code generation and other software engineering tasks. Vulnerability detection is of crucial importance to maintaining the security, integrity, and trustworthiness of software systems. Precise vulnerability detection requires reasoning about the code, making it a good case study for exploring the limits of LLMs’ reasoning capabilities. Although recent work has applied LLMs to vulnerability detection using generic prompting techniques, their full capabilities for this task and the types of errors they make when explaining identified vulnerabilities remain unclear. In this paper, we surveyed eleven LLMs that are state-of-theart in code generation and commonly used as coding assistants, and evaluated their capabilities for vulnerability detection. We systematically searched for the best-performing prompts, incorporating techniques such as in-context learning and chainof-thought, and proposed three of our own prompting methods. Our results show that while our prompting methods improved the models’ performance, LLMs generally struggled with vulnerability detection. They reported 0.5-0.63 Balanced Accuracy and failed to distinguish between buggy and fixed versions of programs in 76% of cases on average. By comprehensively analyzing and categorizing 287 instances of model reasoning, we found that 57% of LLM responses contained errors, and the models frequently predicted incorrect locations of buggy code and misidentified bug types. LLMs only correctly localized 6 out of 27 bugs in DbgBench, and these 6 bugs were predicted correctly by 70-100% of human participants. These findings suggest that despite their potential for other tasks, LLMs may fail to properly comprehend critical code structures and security-related concepts. Our study highlights the need for further research to improve the vulnerability detection capabilities of LLMs. Our data and code are available at https://figshare.com/s/78fe02e56e09ec49300b.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Evaluates 11 state-of-the-art LLMs for vulnerability detection, finding 0.5-0.63 balanced accuracy and 57% error rate in model reasoning across 287 instances.","summary_zh":"评估11个最先进的LLM用于漏洞检测，发现平衡准确率为0.5-0.63，在287个实例中模型推理错误率为57%。","abstract_zh":"大型语言模型（LLM）在代码生成和其他软件工程任务中展示了巨大潜力。漏洞检测对于维护软件系统的安全性、完整性和可信度至关重要。精确的漏洞检测需要对代码进行推理，使其成为探索LLM推理能力极限的良好案例研究。尽管最近的工作使用通用提示技术将LLM应用于漏洞检测，但它们在这项任务中的全部能力以及在解释已识别漏洞时犯的错误类型仍不清楚。在本文中，我们调查了11个在代码生成方面最先进且常用作编码助手的LLM，并评估了它们的漏洞检测能力。我们系统地搜索了最佳提示，融入了上下文学习和思维链等技术，并提出了三种我们自己的提示方法。结果表明，虽然我们的提示方法提高了模型的性能，但LLM通常在漏洞检测方面表现不佳。它们报告的平衡准确率为0.5-0.63，平均在76%的情况下无法区分有缺陷和已修复版本的程序。通过全面分析和分类287个模型推理实例，我们发现57%的LLM响应包含错误，模型经常预测错误的缺陷代码位置并误判缺陷类型。LLM在DbgBench中仅正确定位了27个缺陷中的6个，而这6个缺陷被70-100%的人类参与者正确预测。这些发现表明，尽管LLM在其他任务上有潜力，但它们可能无法正确理解关键的代码结构和安全相关概念。我们的研究强调了需要进一步研究以提高LLM的漏洞检测能力。","contributions":["Surveys 11 state-of-the-art code generation LLMs and evaluates their capabilities for vulnerability detection.","Proposes three new prompting methods incorporating in-context learning and chain-of-thought techniques.","Finds LLMs achieve only 0.5-0.63 balanced accuracy, failing to distinguish buggy from fixed code in 76% of cases.","Analyzes 287 model reasoning instances, revealing 57% contain errors with frequent misidentification of bug types and locations.","Shows LLMs correctly localized only 6 of 27 bugs in DbgBench, all predicted correctly by 70-100% of human participants."],"contributions_zh":["调查了11个最先进的代码生成LLM，并评估了它们的漏洞检测能力。","提出了三种结合上下文学习和思维链技术的新提示方法。","发现LLM仅达到0.5-0.63的平衡准确率，在76%的情况下无法区分有缺陷和已修复的代码。","分析了287个模型推理实例，发现57%包含错误，模型经常误判缺陷类型和位置。","展示LLM在DbgBench中仅正确定位了27个缺陷中的6个，而这6个缺陷也被70-100%的人类参与者正确预测。"],"experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["source code"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["DbgBench"],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"LLMs achieve 0.5-0.63 balanced accuracy; 57% of responses contain errors; only 6/27 bugs correctly localized in DbgBench","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@article{steenhoek2024comprehensive,\\n  title={A Comprehensive Study of the Capabilities of Large Language Models for Vulnerability Detection},\\n  author={Steenhoek, Benjamin and Rahman, Md Mahbubur and Roy, Monoshi Kumar and Alam, Mirza Sanjida and Barr, Earl T and Le, Wei},\\n  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2403.17218},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"sun2024llm4vuln","title":"Llm4vuln: A unified evaluation framework for decoupling and enhancing llms' vulnerability reasoning","authors":"Sun, Yuqiang and Wu, Daoyuan and Xue, Yue and Liu, Han and Ma, Wei and Zhang, Lyuye and Liu, Yang and Li, Yingjiu","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2401.16185","abstract":"Large language models (LLMs) have demonstrated significant potential in various tasks, including those requiring human-level intelligence, such as vulnerability detection. However, recent efforts to use LLMs for vulnerability detection remain preliminary, as they lack a deep understanding of whether a subject LLM's vulnerability reasoning capability stems from the model itself or from external aids such as knowledge retrieval and tooling support.\\nIn this paper, we aim to decouple LLMs' vulnerability reasoning from other capabilities, such as vulnerability knowledge adoption, context information retrieval, and advanced prompt schemes. We introduce LLM4Vuln, a unified evaluation framework that separates and assesses LLMs' vulnerability reasoning capabilities and examines improvements when combined with other enhancements.\\nWe conduct controlled experiments using 147 ground-truth vulnerabilities and 147 non-vulnerable cases in Solidity, Java and C/C++, testing them in a total of 3,528 scenarios across four LLMs (GPT-3.5, GPT-4, Phi-3, and Llama 3). Our findings reveal the varying impacts of knowledge enhancement, context supplementation, and prompt schemes. We also identify 14 zero-day vulnerabilities in four pilot bug bounty programs, resulting in $3,576 in bounties.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Introduces LLM4Vuln framework to decouple LLMs' vulnerability reasoning from external aids, testing 3,528 scenarios across GPT-3.5/4, Phi-3, Llama 3, discovering 14 zero-days.","summary_zh":"提出LLM4Vuln框架，将LLM的漏洞推理能力与外部辅助解耦，在GPT-3.5/4、Phi-3、Llama 3上测试3528个场景，发现14个零日漏洞并获得$3576赏金。","abstract_zh":"大型语言模型（LLM）在各种任务中展示了巨大潜力，包括需要人类级智能的任务，如漏洞检测。然而，最近使用LLM进行漏洞检测的努力仍处于初步阶段，因为它们缺乏对目标LLM的漏洞推理能力是来自模型本身还是来自知识检索和工具支持等外部辅助的深入理解。在本文中，我们旨在将LLM的漏洞推理与其他能力（如漏洞知识采纳、上下文信息检索和高级提示方案）解耦。我们引入了LLM4Vuln，一个统一的评估框架，它分离和评估LLM的漏洞推理能力，并检验与其他增强功能结合时的改进。我们使用147个真实漏洞和147个非漏洞案例在Solidity、Java和C/C++中进行受控实验，在四个LLM（GPT-3.5、GPT-4、Phi-3和Llama 3）上共测试3528个场景。我们的发现揭示了知识增强、上下文补充和提示方案的不同影响。我们还在四个试点漏洞赏金计划中发现了14个零日漏洞，获得了$3576的赏金。","contributions":["Introduces LLM4Vuln, a unified evaluation framework that decouples and assesses LLMs' vulnerability reasoning capabilities.","Tests 147 ground-truth vulnerabilities and 147 non-vulnerable cases across Solidity, Java, and C/C++ in 3,528 scenarios.","Evaluates four LLMs (GPT-3.5, GPT-4, Phi-3, Llama 3) with varying knowledge enhancement, context supplementation, and prompt schemes.","Reveals varying impacts of knowledge enhancement, context supplementation, and prompt schemes on vulnerability reasoning.","Identifies 14 zero-day vulnerabilities in four pilot bug bounty programs, resulting in $3,576 in bounties."],"contributions_zh":["提出LLM4Vuln，一个解耦和评估LLM漏洞推理能力的统一评估框架。","在Solidity、Java和C/C++中测试147个真实漏洞和147个非漏洞案例，共3528个场景。","评估四个LLM（GPT-3.5、GPT-4、Phi-3、Llama 3），采用不同的知识增强、上下文补充和提示方案。","揭示了知识增强、上下文补充和提示方案对漏洞推理的不同影响。","在四个漏洞赏金计划中发现14个零日漏洞，获得$3576赏金。"],"system_name":"LLM4Vuln","experiment":{"language":["Solidity","Java","C/C++"],"platform":[],"target_domain":["smart contract","source code"],"llm":["GPT-3.5","GPT-4","Phi-3","Llama 3"],"model_family":["GPT","Phi","LLaMA"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"147 vulnerabilities + 147 non-vulnerable cases, 3528 scenarios","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Identified 14 zero-day vulnerabilities in 4 bug bounty programs, earning $3,576 in bounties","real_world_impact":"14 zero-day vulnerabilities discovered, $3,576 in bug bounties","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@article{sun2024llm4vuln,\\n  title={Llm4vuln: A unified evaluation framework for decoupling and enhancing llms' vulnerability reasoning},\\n  author={Sun, Yuqiang and Wu, Daoyuan and Xue, Yue and Liu, Han and Ma, Wei and Zhang, Lyuye and Liu, Yang and Li, Yingjiu},\\n  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2401.16185},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"taghavi2024using","title":"Using large language models to better detect and handle software vulnerabilities and cyber security threats","authors":"Taghavi, Seyed Mohammad and Feyzi, Farid","year":2024,"venue":"","abstract":"Large Language Models (LLMs) have emerged as powerful tools in the domain of software vulnerability and cybersecurity tasks, offering promising capabilities in detecting and handling security threats. This article explores the utilization of LLMs in various aspects of cybersecurity, including vulnerability detection, threat prediction, and automated code repair. We explain the concept of LLMs, highlighting their various applications, and evaluates their effectiveness and challenges through literature review. We explore the effectiveness of various LLMs across different cybersecurity domains, showcasing their pro ciency in tasks like malware detection and code summarization. Comparing LLMs to traditional methods, our work highlights their superior performance in identifying vulnerabilities and proposing xes. Furthermore, we outline the work ow of LLM models, emphasizing their integration into cyber threat detection frameworks and incident response systems. We also discuss complementary methods and tools that enhance LLMs' capabilities, including static and dynamic code analyzers. Additionally, we synthesize ndings from previous research, demonstrating how the utilization of LLMs has signi cantly enhanced productivity in identifying and addressing software vulnerabilities and cybersecurity threats. Finally, the study offers insights into optimizing the implementation of LLMs based on the lessons learned from existing literature.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Literature review on LLMs for cybersecurity tasks including vulnerability detection, malware detection, code summarization, and automated code repair.","summary_zh":"关于LLM在网络安全任务中应用的文献综述，涵盖漏洞检测、恶意软件检测、代码摘要和自动代码修复。","abstract_zh":"大型语言模型（LLM）已成为软件漏洞和网络安全任务领域的强大工具，在检测和处理安全威胁方面提供了有前景的能力。本文探讨了LLM在网络安全各方面的应用，包括漏洞检测、威胁预测和自动代码修复。我们解释了LLM的概念，突出了其各种应用，并通过文献综述评估了其有效性和挑战。我们探讨了各种LLM在不同网络安全领域的有效性，展示了它们在恶意软件检测和代码摘要等任务中的能力。将LLM与传统方法进行比较，我们的工作突出了它们在识别漏洞和提出修复方案方面的优越性能。此外，我们概述了LLM模型的工作流程，强调了它们在网络威胁检测框架和事件响应系统中的集成。我们还讨论了增强LLM能力的辅助方法和工具，包括静态和动态代码分析器。此外，我们综合了先前研究的发现，展示了LLM的使用如何显著提高了识别和解决软件漏洞及网络安全威胁的生产力。最后，本研究基于现有文献的经验教训，提供了优化LLM实施的见解。","contributions":["Provides a comprehensive literature review on the utilization of LLMs in software vulnerability detection and cybersecurity.","Compares LLMs to traditional methods, highlighting their superior performance in identifying vulnerabilities and proposing fixes.","Outlines the workflow of LLM models and their integration into cyber threat detection frameworks and incident response systems.","Discusses complementary tools including static and dynamic code analyzers that enhance LLM capabilities.","Synthesizes findings demonstrating how LLMs have significantly enhanced productivity in identifying and addressing software vulnerabilities."],"contributions_zh":["提供了关于LLM在软件漏洞检测和网络安全中应用的全面文献综述。","将LLM与传统方法进行比较，突出其在识别漏洞和提出修复方案方面的优越性能。","概述了LLM模型的工作流程及其在网络威胁检测框架和事件响应系统中的集成。","讨论了增强LLM能力的辅助工具，包括静态和动态代码分析器。","综合了研究发现，展示LLM如何显著提高识别和解决软件漏洞及网络安全威胁的生产力。"],"experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["cybersecurity"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@article{taghavi2024using,\\n  title={Using large language models to better detect and handle software vulnerabilities and cyber security threats},\\n  author={Taghavi, Seyed Mohammad and Feyzi, Farid},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"wang2023defecthunter","title":"Defecthunter: A novel llm-driven boosted-conformer-based code vulnerability detection mechanism","authors":"Wang, Jin and Huang, Zishan and Liu, Hengli and Yang, Nianyi and Xiao, Yinhao","year":2023,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2309.15324","abstract":"One of the most pressing threats to computing systems is software vulnerabilities, which can compromise both hardware and software components. Existing methods for vulnerability detection remain suboptimal. Traditional techniques are both time-consuming and labor-intensive, while machine-learning-based approaches often underperform when applied to complex datasets, due to their inability to capture high-dimensional relationships. Previous deep-learning strategies also fall short in capturing sufficient feature information. Although self-attention mechanisms can process information over long distances, they fail to capture structural information. In this paper, we introduce DefectHunter, an innovative model for vulnerability identification that employs the Conformer mechanism. This mechanism fuses self-attention with convolutional networks to capture both local, position-wise features and global, content-based interactions. Furthermore, we optimize the self-attention mechanisms to mitigate the issue of excessive attention heads introducing extraneous noise by adjusting the denominator. We evaluated DefectHunter against ten baseline methods using six industrial and two highly complex datasets. On the QEMU dataset, DefectHunter exhibited a 20.62\\\\% improvement in accuracy over Pongo-70B, and for the CWE-754 dataset, its accuracy was 14.64\\\\% higher. To investigate how DefectHunter comprehends vulnerabilities, we conducted a case study, which revealed that our model effectively understands the mechanisms underlying vulnerabilities.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Introduces DefectHunter using Conformer mechanism (self-attention + convolution) for vulnerability detection, outperforming Pongo-70B by 20.62% accuracy on QEMU dataset.","summary_zh":"提出DefectHunter，使用Conformer机制（自注意力+卷积）进行漏洞检测，在QEMU数据集上准确率比Pongo-70B高20.62%。","abstract_zh":"软件漏洞是计算系统面临的最紧迫威胁之一，可能危及硬件和软件组件。现有的漏洞检测方法仍不够理想。传统技术既耗时又费力，而基于机器学习的方法在应用于复杂数据集时往往表现不佳，因为它们无法捕获高维关系。之前的深度学习策略在捕获充分的特征信息方面也存在不足。虽然自注意力机制可以处理长距离信息，但它们无法捕获结构信息。在本文中，我们引入了DefectHunter，一种采用Conformer机制的创新漏洞识别模型。该机制融合了自注意力和卷积网络，以捕获局部的、位置相关的特征和全局的、内容相关的交互。此外，我们优化了自注意力机制，通过调整分母来减轻过多注意力头引入多余噪声的问题。我们使用6个工业数据集和2个高度复杂的数据集，将DefectHunter与10种基线方法进行了评估。在QEMU数据集上，DefectHunter的准确率比Pongo-70B提高了20.62%，在CWE-754数据集上，其准确率高出14.64%。为了研究DefectHunter如何理解漏洞，我们进行了案例研究，结果表明我们的模型有效地理解了漏洞的底层机制。","contributions":["Introduces DefectHunter, an innovative vulnerability identification model employing the Conformer mechanism combining self-attention with convolutional networks.","Optimizes self-attention mechanisms by adjusting the denominator to mitigate noise from excessive attention heads.","Evaluates against 10 baseline methods using 6 industrial and 2 highly complex datasets.","Achieves 20.62% accuracy improvement over Pongo-70B on QEMU dataset and 14.64% higher accuracy on CWE-754 dataset.","Conducts case study demonstrating that DefectHunter effectively understands underlying vulnerability mechanisms."],"contributions_zh":["提出DefectHunter，一种创新的漏洞识别模型，采用Conformer机制将自注意力与卷积网络结合。","通过调整分母优化自注意力机制，以减少过多注意力头引入的多余噪声。","使用6个工业数据集和2个高度复杂的数据集，与10种基线方法进行评估比较。","在QEMU数据集上准确率比Pongo-70B提高20.62%，在CWE-754数据集上准确率高出14.64%。","通过案例研究证明DefectHunter能有效理解漏洞的底层机制。"],"system_name":"DefectHunter","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["source code"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["QEMU","CWE-754"],"benchmark_size":"6 industrial + 2 complex datasets","baselines":["Pongo-70B"],"vulnerability_type":["CWE-754"],"key_results":"20.62% accuracy improvement over Pongo-70B on QEMU dataset; 14.64% higher accuracy on CWE-754 dataset","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@article{wang2023defecthunter,\\n  title={Defecthunter: A novel llm-driven boosted-conformer-based code vulnerability detection mechanism},\\n  author={Wang, Jin and Huang, Zishan and Liu, Hengli and Yang, Nianyi and Xiao, Yinhao},\\n  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2309.15324},\\n  year={2023}\\n}"},{"id":"wang2024anvil","title":"ANVIL: Anomaly-based Vulnerability Identification without Labelled Training Data","authors":"Wang, Weizhou and Liu, Eric and Guo, Xiangyu and Lie, David","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2408.16028","abstract":"Supervised learning-based software vulnerability detectors often fall short due to the inadequate availability of labelled training data. In contrast, Large Language Models (LLMs) such as GPT-4, are not trained on labelled data, but when prompted to detect vulnerabilities, LLM prediction accuracy is only marginally better than random guessing. In this paper, we explore a different approach by reframing vulnerability detection as one of anomaly detection. Since the vast majority of code does not contain vulnerabilities and LLMs are trained on massive amounts of such code, vulnerable code can be viewed as an anomaly from the LLM’s predicted code distribution, freeing the model from the need for labelled data to provide a learnable representation of vulnerable code. Leveraging this perspective, we demonstrate that LLMs trained for code generation exhibit a significant gap in prediction accuracy when prompted to reconstruct vulnerable versus non-vulnerable code. Using this insight, we implement ANVIL, a detector that identifies software vulnerabilities at line-level granularity. Our experiments explore the discriminating power of different anomaly scoring methods, as well as the sensitivity of ANVIL to context size. We also study the effectiveness of ANVIL on various LLM families, and conduct leakage experiments on vulnerabilities that were discovered after the knowledge cutoff of our evaluated LLMs. On a collection of vulnerabilities from the Magma benchmark, ANVIL outperforms state-of-the-art line-level vulnerability detectors, LineVul and LineVD, which have been trained with labelled data, despite ANVIL having never been trained with labelled vulnerabilities. Specifically, our approach achieves 1.62× to 2.18× better Top-5 accuracies and 1.02× to 1.29× times better ROC scores on line-level vulnerability detection tasks.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Proposes ANVIL, an anomaly-based line-level vulnerability detector using LLM code reconstruction accuracy gaps, outperforming LineVul and LineVD without labeled training data.","summary_zh":"提出ANVIL，一种基于异常检测的行级漏洞检测器，利用LLM代码重构准确性差异，无需标注训练数据即优于LineVul和LineVD。","abstract_zh":"基于监督学习的软件漏洞检测器往往因标注训练数据不足而表现不佳。相比之下，大型语言模型（LLM）如GPT-4虽然不是在标注数据上训练的，但当提示检测漏洞时，LLM的预测准确率仅略好于随机猜测。在本文中，我们探索了一种不同的方法，将漏洞检测重新定义为异常检测。由于绝大多数代码不包含漏洞，而LLM是在大量此类代码上训练的，有漏洞的代码可以被视为LLM预测代码分布中的异常，从而使模型无需标注数据即可提供漏洞代码的可学习表示。利用这一观点，我们证明了为代码生成而训练的LLM在提示重构有漏洞代码与无漏洞代码时表现出显著的预测准确率差距。基于这一洞察，我们实现了ANVIL，一种在行级粒度识别软件漏洞的检测器。我们的实验探索了不同异常评分方法的判别能力以及ANVIL对上下文大小的敏感性。我们还研究了ANVIL在不同LLM家族上的有效性，并对在评估的LLM知识截止日期之后发现的漏洞进行了泄漏实验。在Magma基准的漏洞集合上，ANVIL优于最先进的行级漏洞检测器LineVul和LineVD（它们使用标注数据训练），尽管ANVIL从未使用标注漏洞进行训练。具体而言，我们的方法在行级漏洞检测任务上实现了1.62倍至2.18倍更好的Top-5准确率和1.02倍至1.29倍更好的ROC分数。","contributions":["Reframes vulnerability detection as anomaly detection, leveraging LLMs' predicted code distribution without labeled data.","Demonstrates significant prediction accuracy gap when LLMs reconstruct vulnerable versus non-vulnerable code.","Implements ANVIL, a detector identifying software vulnerabilities at line-level granularity.","Achieves 1.62x to 2.18x better Top-5 accuracies and 1.02x to 1.29x better ROC scores than LineVul and LineVD on Magma benchmark.","Outperforms state-of-the-art line-level detectors trained with labeled data despite never being trained with labeled vulnerabilities."],"contributions_zh":["将漏洞检测重新定义为异常检测，利用LLM的预测代码分布，无需标注数据。","展示LLM重构有漏洞代码与无漏洞代码时存在显著的预测准确率差距。","实现ANVIL，一种在行级粒度识别软件漏洞的检测器。","在Magma基准上，Top-5准确率比LineVul和LineVD高1.62至2.18倍，ROC分数高1.02至1.29倍。","尽管从未使用标注漏洞进行训练，但优于使用标注数据训练的最先进行级检测器。"],"system_name":"ANVIL","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["source code"],"llm":["GPT-4"],"model_family":["GPT"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["Magma"],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":["LineVul","LineVD"],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"1.62x-2.18x better Top-5 accuracy and 1.02x-1.29x better ROC than LineVul and LineVD on Magma benchmark without labeled training data","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@article{wang2024anvil,\\n  title={ANVIL: Anomaly-based Vulnerability Identification without Labelled Training Data},\\n  author={Wang, Weizhou and Liu, Eric and Guo, Xiangyu and Lie, David},\\n  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2408.16028},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"wang2024smartinv","title":"Smartinv: Multimodal learning for smart contract invariant inference","authors":"Wang, Sally Junsong and Pei, Kexin and Yang, Junfeng","year":2024,"venue":"2024 IEEE Symposium on Security and Privacy (SP)","abstract":"Smart contracts are software programs that enable diverse business activities on the blockchain. Recent research has identified new classes of \\"machine un-auditable\\" bugs that arise from source code not meeting underlying transaction contexts. Existing detection methods require human understanding of underlying transaction logic and manual reasoning across different sources of context (i.e., modalities), such as code and natural language specifying the expected transaction behavior.To automate the detection of \\"machine un-auditable\\" bugs, we present SmartInv, an accurate and fast smart contract invariant inference framework. Our key insight is that the expected behavior of smart contracts, as specified by invariants, relies on understanding and reasoning across multimodal information, such as source code and natural language. We propose a new finetuning and prompting strategy to foundation models, Tier of Thought (ToT), to reason across multiple modalities of smart contracts and to generate invariants. SmartInv then localizes potential vulnerabilities by checking the violation of those generated invariants.We evaluate SmartInv on real-world smart contract bugs that resulted in financial losses over the past 2.5 years (from January 1, 2021 to May 31, 2023). Extensive evaluation shows that SmartInv can generate useful invariants to effectively localize \\"machine un-auditable\\" bugs, from which SmartInv uncovers 119 zero-day bugs. We sampled eight bugs and reported them to the respective developers. Six vulnerabilities were quickly fixed by the developers, five of which are confirmed as \\"high severity.\\"\\n\\n# Source:\\n\\n[code](https://github.com/columbia/SmartInv)","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Presents SmartInv, a multimodal smart contract invariant inference framework using Tier of Thought prompting, uncovering 119 zero-day bugs with 6 confirmed high-severity.","summary_zh":"提出SmartInv，一种使用层级思维提示的多模态智能合约不变量推理框架，发现119个零日漏洞，其中6个被确认为高严重性。","abstract_zh":"智能合约是在区块链上实现多种商业活动的软件程序。最近的研究识别了新类别的机器不可审计漏洞，这些漏洞源于源代码不满足底层交易上下文。现有的检测方法需要人类理解底层交易逻辑，并在不同来源的上下文（即模态）之间进行手动推理，如代码和描述预期交易行为的自然语言。为了自动化检测机器不可审计漏洞，我们提出了SmartInv，一个准确且快速的智能合约不变量推理框架。我们的关键洞察是，由不变量指定的智能合约预期行为依赖于跨多模态信息的理解和推理，如源代码和自然语言。我们提出了一种新的基础模型微调和提示策略——层级思维（ToT），用于跨智能合约的多种模态进行推理并生成不变量。然后SmartInv通过检查生成的不变量的违反情况来定位潜在漏洞。我们在过去2.5年（2021年1月1日至2023年5月31日）导致经济损失的真实世界智能合约漏洞上评估了SmartInv。广泛的评估表明，SmartInv可以生成有用的不变量来有效定位机器不可审计漏洞，从中SmartInv发现了119个零日漏洞。我们抽样了8个漏洞并向相应开发者报告。6个漏洞被开发者迅速修复，其中5个被确认为高严重性。","contributions":["Proposes SmartInv, a multimodal smart contract invariant inference framework for detecting machine un-auditable bugs.","Introduces Tier of Thought (ToT), a new fine-tuning and prompting strategy for foundation models to reason across multiple modalities.","Localizes vulnerabilities by checking violations of generated invariants from source code and natural language specifications.","Uncovers 119 zero-day bugs from real-world smart contracts (Jan 2021 to May 2023), with 6 confirmed as high severity.","Reports 8 sampled bugs to developers, with 6 quickly fixed and 5 confirmed as high severity."],"contributions_zh":["提出SmartInv，一种用于检测机器不可审计漏洞的多模态智能合约不变量推理框架。","引入层级思维（ToT），一种新的基础模型微调和提示策略，用于跨多种模态进行推理。","通过检查从源代码和自然语言规范生成的不变量的违反情况来定位漏洞。","从真实世界智能合约（2021年1月至2023年5月）中发现119个零日漏洞，其中6个被确认为高严重性。","向开发者报告了8个采样漏洞，其中6个被迅速修复，5个被确认为高严重性。"],"system_name":"SmartInv","experiment":{"language":["Solidity"],"platform":["blockchain"],"target_domain":["smart contract"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":true,"fine_tuning_method":"Tier of Thought (ToT)","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"real-world smart contract bugs from Jan 2021 to May 2023","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":["machine un-auditable bugs"],"key_results":"Uncovered 119 zero-day bugs; 8 reported to developers, 6 quickly fixed, 5 confirmed high severity","real_world_impact":"119 zero-day bugs discovered, 6 fixed by developers, 5 confirmed high severity","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":3,"bibtex":"@inproceedings{wang2024smartinv,\\n  title={Smartinv: Multimodal learning for smart contract invariant inference},\\n  author={Wang, Sally Junsong and Pei, Kexin and Yang, Junfeng},\\n  booktitle={2024 IEEE Symposium on Security and Privacy (SP)},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"wasabi2024sosp","title":"If At First You Don’t Succeed, Try, Try, Again...? Insights and LLM-informed Tooling for Detecting Retry Bugs in Software Systems","authors":"","year":2024,"venue":"SOSP'24","abstract":"Retry—the re-execution of a task on failure—is a common mechanism to enable resilient software systems. Yet, despite its commonality and long history, retry remains difficult to implement and test.\\nGuided by our study of real-world retry issues, we propose a novel suite of static and dynamic techniques to detect retry problems in software. We find that the ad-hoc nature of retry\\nimplementation poses challenges for traditional program analysis but can be well suited for large language models;\\nand that carefully repurposing existing unit tests can, along with fault injection, expose various types of retry problems","paperUrl":"https://dl.acm.org/doi/pdf/10.1145/3694715.3695971","codeUrl":"https://github.com/bastoica/wasabi/","slidesUrl":"https://bastoica.github.io/files/talks/2024_sosp_talk.pdf","talkUrl":"","categories":["fuzzing"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Proposes static and dynamic techniques using LLMs and fault injection to detect retry bugs in software systems, published at SOSP'24.","summary_zh":"提出使用LLM和故障注入的静态和动态技术来检测软件系统中的重试漏洞，发表于SOSP'24。","abstract_zh":"重试——在失败时重新执行任务——是实现弹性软件系统的常见机制。然而，尽管重试很常见且历史悠久，但它仍然难以实现和测试。在对真实世界重试问题的研究指导下，我们提出了一套新颖的静态和动态技术来检测软件中的重试问题。我们发现，临时性的重试实现对传统程序分析构成挑战，但可能非常适合大型语言模型；通过精心复用现有的单元测试配合故障注入，可以暴露各种类型的重试问题。","contributions":["Studies real-world retry issues and proposes a novel suite of static and dynamic techniques for detecting retry problems.","Identifies that ad-hoc retry implementation poses challenges for traditional program analysis but suits LLMs well.","Demonstrates that carefully repurposing existing unit tests with fault injection can expose various retry problems.","Provides LLM-informed tooling for retry bug detection in software systems."],"contributions_zh":["研究真实世界的重试问题，并提出一套新颖的静态和动态技术来检测重试问题。","识别出临时性重试实现对传统程序分析构成挑战，但适合LLM处理。","展示了通过精心复用现有单元测试和故障注入可以暴露各种重试问题。","提供基于LLM的重试漏洞检测工具。"],"system_name":"Wasabi","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["software systems"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":["retry bugs"],"key_results":"","real_world_impact":"","open_source":true,"cost":""},"recommendation":3,"bibtex":"@inproceedings{wasabi2024sosp,\\n  title={If At First You Don't Succeed, Try, Try, Again...? Insights and LLM-informed Tooling for Detecting Retry Bugs in Software Systems},\\n  booktitle={Proceedings of the 30th ACM Symposium on Operating Systems Principles (SOSP'24)},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"wen2024collaboration","title":"Collaboration to Repository-Level Vulnerability Detection","authors":"Wen, Xin-Cheng","year":2024,"venue":"Proceedings of the 33rd ACM SIGSOFT International Symposium on Software Testing and Analysis","abstract":"Large Language Model (LLM)-based methods have proven to be effective for many software engineering domains, with a potential for substantial productivity effective for software vulnerability detection. However, due to the limitation of the length of input contexts of LLM, the existing LLM-based methods mainly focus on detecting function-level and leveraging the in-file context information for vulnerability detection (i.e., intra-procedural vulnerabilities), ignoring the more complex inter-procedural vulnerability detection scenarios in practice. For instance, in real-world scenarios, developers routinely engage with program analysis to detect vulnerabilities that span multiple cross-file information within repositories. Since complex processes tend to have redundancy dependencies from spanning multiple files in the repository level and invoking multiple static analysis tools, the ideal goal of vulnerability detection is to extract the vulnerability-related information from the repository and provide potential possible explanations for vulnerability triggers. However, such a goal is hard to achieve, and thus in this work, we design three works through multi-agent collaboration to approach the goal of repository-level vulnerability detection.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Designs multi-agent collaboration approaches for repository-level vulnerability detection, addressing inter-procedural and cross-file vulnerability analysis via LLMs.","summary_zh":"设计多智能体协作方法用于仓库级漏洞检测，通过LLM解决跨过程和跨文件的漏洞分析问题。","abstract_zh":"基于大型语言模型（LLM）的方法已被证明对许多软件工程领域有效，具有显著提高软件漏洞检测生产力的潜力。然而，由于LLM输入上下文长度的限制，现有的基于LLM的方法主要专注于检测函数级并利用文件内上下文信息进行漏洞检测（即过程内漏洞），忽略了实践中更复杂的过程间漏洞检测场景。例如，在真实世界场景中，开发者通常使用程序分析来检测跨仓库内多个文件信息的漏洞。由于复杂过程往往具有来自仓库级别多个文件的冗余依赖关系，并需要调用多个静态分析工具，漏洞检测的理想目标是从仓库中提取与漏洞相关的信息并提供漏洞触发的可能解释。然而，这样的目标难以实现，因此在这项工作中，我们通过多智能体协作设计了三项工作来接近仓库级漏洞检测的目标。","contributions":["Addresses the limitation of LLM context length for repository-level vulnerability detection beyond function-level analysis.","Proposes multi-agent collaboration to detect inter-procedural vulnerabilities spanning multiple cross-file information.","Designs three works through multi-agent collaboration to approach repository-level vulnerability detection.","Aims to extract vulnerability-related information from repositories and provide explanations for vulnerability triggers."],"contributions_zh":["解决了LLM上下文长度限制对仓库级漏洞检测（超越函数级分析）的局限性。","提出多智能体协作来检测跨多个文件信息的过程间漏洞。","通过多智能体协作设计了三项工作来实现仓库级漏洞检测目标。","旨在从仓库中提取漏洞相关信息并提供漏洞触发的潜在解释。"],"experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["source code","repository-level"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":["inter-procedural vulnerabilities"],"key_results":"","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":3,"bibtex":"@inproceedings{wen2024collaboration,\\n  title={Collaboration to Repository-Level Vulnerability Detection},\\n  author={Wen, Xin-Cheng},\\n  booktitle={Proceedings of the 33rd ACM SIGSOFT International Symposium on Software Testing and Analysis},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"wen2024scale","title":"Scale: Constructing structured natural language comment trees for software vulnerability detection","authors":"Wen, Xin-Cheng and Gao, Cuiyun and Gao, Shuzheng and Xiao, Yang and Lyu, Michael R","year":2024,"venue":"Proceedings of the 33rd ACM SIGSOFT International Symposium on Software Testing and Analysis","abstract":"Recently, there has been a growing interest in automatic software vulnerability detection. Pre-trained model-based approaches have demonstrated superior performance than other Deep Learning (DL)based approaches in detecting vulnerabilities. However, the existing pre-trained model-based approaches generally employ code sequences as input during prediction, and may ignore vulnerabilityrelated structural information, as reflected in the following two aspects. First, they tend to fail to infer the semantics of the code statements with complex logic such as those containing multiple operators and pointers. Second, they are hard to comprehend various code execution sequences, which is essential for precise vulnerability detection. To mitigate the challenges, we propose a Structured Natural Language Comment tree-based vulnerAbiLity dEtection framework based on the pre-trained models, named SCALE. The proposed Structured Natural Language Comment Tree (SCT) integrates the semantics of code statements with code execution sequences based on the Abstract Syntax Trees (ASTs). Specifically, SCALE comprises three main modules: (1) Comment Tree Construction, which aims at enhancing the model’s ability to infer the semantics of code statements by first incorporating Large Language Models (LLMs) for comment generation and then adding the comment node to ASTs. (2) Structured Natural Language Comment Tree Construction, which aims at explicitly involving code execution sequence by combining the code syntax templates with the comment tree. (3) SCT-Enhanced Representation, which finally incorporates the constructed SCTs for well capturing vulnerability patterns. Experimental results demonstrate that SCALE outperforms the best-performing baseline, including the pre-trained model and LLMs, with improvements of 2.96%, 13.47%, and 3.75% in terms of F1 score on the FFMPeg+Qemu, Reveal, and SVulD datasets, respectively. Furthermore, SCALE can be applied to different pre-trained models, such as CodeBERT and  Permission to make digital or hard copies of all or part of this work for personal or classroom use is granted without fee provided that copies are not made or distributed for profit or commercial advantage and that copies bear this notice and the full citation on the first page. Copyrights for components of this work owned by others than the author(s) must be honored. Abstracting with credit is permitted. To copy otherwise, or republish, to post on servers or to redistribute to lists, requires prior specific permission and/or a fee. Request permissions from permissions@acm.org. ISSTA ’24, September 16–20, 2024, Vienna, Austria  © 2024 Copyright held by the owner/author(s). Publication rights licensed to ACM. ACM ISBN 979-8-4007-0612-7/24/09 https://doi.org/10.1145/3650212.3652124  UniXcoder, yielding the F1 score performance enhancements ranging from 1.37% to 10.87%.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["fine-tuning"],"summary":"Proposes SCALE framework using Structured Natural Language Comment Trees on ASTs with LLM-generated comments, improving F1 by 2.96%-13.47% over baselines on FFMPeg+Qemu and Reveal.","summary_zh":"提出SCALE框架，在AST上使用LLM生成注释构建结构化自然语言注释树，在FFMPeg+Qemu和Reveal数据集上F1分数比基线提高2.96%-13.47%。","abstract_zh":"近年来，自动软件漏洞检测引起了越来越多的关注。基于预训练模型的方法已展示出优于其他深度学习方法的检测漏洞性能。然而，现有的预训练模型方法通常在预测时使用代码序列作为输入，可能会忽略与漏洞相关的结构信息，体现在以下两个方面。首先，它们往往无法推断包含多个运算符和指针等复杂逻辑的代码语句的语义。其次，它们难以理解各种代码执行序列，而这对精确漏洞检测至关重要。为了缓解这些挑战，我们提出了一种基于预训练模型的结构化自然语言注释树漏洞检测框架SCALE。所提出的结构化自然语言注释树（SCT）基于抽象语法树（AST）将代码语句的语义与代码执行序列集成。具体而言，SCALE包含三个主要模块：（1）注释树构建，旨在通过首先使用大型语言模型（LLM）生成注释，然后将注释节点添加到AST中来增强模型推断代码语句语义的能力。（2）结构化自然语言注释树构建，旨在通过将代码语法模板与注释树结合来显式地包含代码执行序列。（3）SCT增强表示，最终利用构建的SCT来很好地捕获漏洞模式。实验结果表明，SCALE在FFMPeg+Qemu、Reveal和SVulD数据集上分别以2.96%、13.47%和3.75%的F1分数改进优于最佳基线。此外，SCALE可应用于不同的预训练模型，如CodeBERT和UniXcoder，产生1.37%至10.87%的F1分数性能提升。","contributions":["Proposes SCALE, a Structured Natural Language Comment Tree-based vulnerability detection framework on pre-trained models.","Introduces Comment Tree Construction using LLMs for comment generation integrated into ASTs.","Designs Structured Natural Language Comment Tree (SCT) combining code syntax templates with comment trees for execution sequence encoding.","Outperforms best baselines with F1 improvements of 2.96%, 13.47%, and 3.75% on FFMPeg+Qemu, Reveal, and SVulD datasets.","Demonstrates applicability to different pre-trained models (CodeBERT, UniXcoder) with F1 enhancements ranging from 1.37% to 10.87%."],"contributions_zh":["提出SCALE，一种基于结构化自然语言注释树的预训练模型漏洞检测框架。","引入注释树构建方法，使用LLM生成注释并集成到AST中。","设计结构化自然语言注释树（SCT），将代码语法模板与注释树结合以编码执行序列。","在FFMPeg+Qemu、Reveal和SVulD数据集上F1分数分别提高2.96%、13.47%和3.75%，优于最佳基线。","展示了对不同预训练模型（CodeBERT、UniXcoder）的适用性，F1增强范围为1.37%至10.87%。"],"system_name":"SCALE","experiment":{"language":["C/C++"],"platform":[],"target_domain":["source code"],"llm":[],"model_family":["CodeBERT","UniXcoder"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["FFMPeg+Qemu","Reveal","SVulD"],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":["CodeBERT","UniXcoder"],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"F1 improvements of 2.96%, 13.47%, and 3.75% on FFMPeg+Qemu, Reveal, and SVulD; 1.37%-10.87% F1 enhancement across pre-trained models","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":3,"bibtex":"@inproceedings{wen2024scale,\\n  title={Scale: Constructing structured natural language comment trees for software vulnerability detection},\\n  author={Wen, Xin-Cheng and Gao, Cuiyun and Gao, Shuzheng and Xiao, Yang and Lyu, Michael R},\\n  booktitle={Proceedings of the 33rd ACM SIGSOFT International Symposium on Software Testing and Analysis},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"yang2023iot","title":"Iot software vulnerability detection techniques through large language model","authors":"Yang, Yilin","year":2023,"venue":"International Conference on Formal Engineering Methods","abstract":"The explosion of IoT usage provides efficiency and convenience in various fields including daily life, business and information technology. However, there are potential risks in large-scale IoT systems and vulnerability detection plays a significant role in the application of IoT. Besides, traditional approaches like routine security audits are expensive. Thus, substitution methods with lower costs are needed to achieve IoT system vulnerability detection. LLMs, as new tools, show exceptional natural language processing capabilities, meanwhile, static code analysis offers low-cost software analysis avenues. The paper aims at the combination of LLMs and static code analysis, implemented by prompt engineering, which not only expands the application of LLMs but also provides a probability of accomplishing cost-effective IoT vulnerability software detection.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Explores combining LLMs with static code analysis via prompt engineering for cost-effective IoT software vulnerability detection.","summary_zh":"探索通过提示工程将LLM与静态代码分析结合，实现低成本的IoT软件漏洞检测。","abstract_zh":"IoT使用的爆发式增长在日常生活、商业和信息技术等各领域提供了效率和便利。然而，大规模IoT系统存在潜在风险，漏洞检测在IoT应用中发挥着重要作用。此外，传统方法如定期安全审计成本高昂。因此，需要成本更低的替代方法来实现IoT系统漏洞检测。LLM作为新工具，展示了卓越的自然语言处理能力，同时静态代码分析提供了低成本的软件分析途径。本文旨在通过提示工程实现LLM与静态代码分析的结合，这不仅扩展了LLM的应用范围，还提供了实现低成本IoT漏洞软件检测的可能性。","contributions":["Proposes combining LLMs with static code analysis for IoT software vulnerability detection.","Applies prompt engineering to leverage LLM capabilities for vulnerability detection in IoT systems.","Addresses the high cost of traditional security audit approaches with a lower-cost alternative.","Expands the application scope of LLMs to IoT system vulnerability detection."],"contributions_zh":["提出将LLM与静态代码分析结合用于IoT软件漏洞检测。","应用提示工程来利用LLM能力进行IoT系统中的漏洞检测。","用更低成本的替代方案解决传统安全审计方法成本高的问题。","将LLM的应用范围扩展到IoT系统漏洞检测。"],"experiment":{"language":[],"platform":["IoT"],"target_domain":["IoT"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@inproceedings{yang2023iot,\\n  title={Iot software vulnerability detection techniques through large language model},\\n  author={Yang, Yilin},\\n  booktitle={International Conference on Formal Engineering Methods},\\n  year={2023}\\n}"},{"id":"yang2024large","title":"Large language models for test-free fault localization","authors":"Yang, Aidan ZH and Le Goues, Claire and Martins, Ruben and Hellendoorn, Vincent","year":2024,"venue":"Proceedings of the 46th IEEE/ACM International Conference on Software Engineering","abstract":"Fault Localization (FL) aims to automatically localize buggy lines of code, a key first step in many manual and automatic debugging tasks. Previous FL techniques assume the provision of input tests, and often require extensive program analysis, program instrumentation, or data preprocessing. Prior work on deep learning for APR struggles to learn from small datasets and produces limited results on real-world programs. Inspired by the ability of large language models (LLMs) of code to adapt to new tasks based on very few examples, we investigate the applicability of LLMs to line level fault localization. Specifically, we propose to overcome the left-to-right nature of LLMs by fine-tuning a small set of bidirectional adapter layers on top of the representations learned by LLMs to produce LLMAO, the first language model based fault localization approach that locates buggy lines of code without any test coverage information. We fine-tune LLMs with 350 million, 6 billion, and 16 billion parameters on small, manually curated corpora of buggy programs such as the Defects4J corpus. We observe that our technique achieves substantially more confidence in fault localization when built on the larger models, with bug localization performance scaling consistently with the LLM size. Our empirical evaluation shows that LLMAO improves the Top-1 results over the state-of-the-art machine learning fault localization (MLFL) baselines by 2.3%--54.4%, and Top-5 results by 14.4%-35.6%. LLMAO is also the first FL technique trained using a language model architecture that can detect security vulnerabilities down to the code line level.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Proposes LLMAO, the first LLM-based test-free fault localization using bidirectional adapters on 350M-16B parameter models, improving Top-1 by 2.3%-54.4% over MLFL baselines.","summary_zh":"提出LLMAO，首个基于LLM的无测试故障定位方法，在350M-16B参数模型上使用双向适配器，Top-1比MLFL基线提高2.3%-54.4%。","abstract_zh":"故障定位（FL）旨在自动定位有缺陷的代码行，这是许多手动和自动调试任务中的关键第一步。之前的FL技术假设提供了输入测试，并且通常需要大量的程序分析、程序插桩或数据预处理。先前关于APR深度学习的工作难以从小数据集中学习，在真实世界程序上产生有限的结果。受大型语言模型能够基于很少示例适应新任务的能力启发，我们研究了LLM在行级故障定位中的适用性。具体而言，我们提出通过在LLM学习的表示之上微调一小组双向适配器层来克服LLM从左到右的特性，从而产生LLMAO，首个基于语言模型的故障定位方法，无需任何测试覆盖信息即可定位有缺陷的代码行。我们在Defects4J语料库等小型、手动策展的有缺陷程序语料库上微调具有3.5亿、60亿和160亿参数的LLM。我们观察到，当构建在更大模型之上时，我们的技术在故障定位方面获得了显著更高的置信度，缺陷定位性能随LLM规模一致提升。我们的实证评估表明，LLMAO比最先进的机器学习故障定位（MLFL）基线的Top-1结果提高了2.3%-54.4%，Top-5结果提高了14.4%-35.6%。LLMAO也是第一个使用语言模型架构训练的FL技术，能够在代码行级别检测安全漏洞。","contributions":["Proposes LLMAO, the first language model-based fault localization approach that locates buggy lines without test coverage information.","Fine-tunes bidirectional adapter layers on top of LLM representations with 350M, 6B, and 16B parameter models.","Demonstrates bug localization performance scaling consistently with LLM size on Defects4J corpus.","Improves Top-1 results by 2.3%-54.4% and Top-5 results by 14.4%-35.6% over state-of-the-art MLFL baselines.","First FL technique trained using a language model architecture capable of detecting security vulnerabilities at code line level."],"contributions_zh":["提出LLMAO，首个基于语言模型的故障定位方法，无需测试覆盖信息即可定位有缺陷的代码行。","在350M、6B和16B参数模型的LLM表示之上微调双向适配器层。","在Defects4J语料库上展示了缺陷定位性能随LLM规模一致提升。","Top-1结果比最先进的MLFL基线提高2.3%-54.4%，Top-5结果提高14.4%-35.6%。","首个使用语言模型架构训练的故障定位技术，能够在代码行级别检测安全漏洞。"],"system_name":"LLMAO","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["source code"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":["350M","6B","16B"],"fine_tuning":true,"fine_tuning_method":"bidirectional adapter layers","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["Defects4J"],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Top-1 improvement of 2.3%-54.4% and Top-5 improvement of 14.4%-35.6% over state-of-the-art MLFL baselines","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":3,"bibtex":"@inproceedings{yang2024large,\\n  title={Large language models for test-free fault localization},\\n  author={Yang, Aidan ZH and Le Goues, Claire and Martins, Ruben and Hellendoorn, Vincent},\\n  booktitle={Proceedings of the 46th IEEE/ACM International Conference on Software Engineering},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"yildirim2024evaluating","title":"Evaluating the Impact of Conventional Code Analysis Against Large Language Models in API Vulnerability Detection","authors":"Y{\\\\i","year":2024,"venue":"European Interdisciplinary Cybersecurity Conference","abstract":"In the rapidly changing world of digital technologies, application programming interfaces (APIs) have become extremely important to allow different software applications to communicate with each other. This communication has greatly enhanced the capabilities and functionality of web applications. This shift towards using more APIs in software development marks a major change in how digital services connect with each other. However, this progress also brings certain security concerns. The increasing reliance on APIs underscores the importance of employing tools that allow early detection and remediation of security vulnerabilities. In this paper, we detail a study that engaged 10 static code analysers and four popular Large Language Models (LLMs), each queried with two unique prompts. Our focus was on assessing their ability to detect a compilation of 40 API vulnerabilities in the source code, specifically selected to represent each category within the OWASP Top 10 API Security Risks. Our results revealed significant variations in the performance of these tools. ChatGPT 4 emerged as the most effective LLM, with a detection rate of 62.5% for the first prompt and 42.5% for the second prompt. In contrast, LLaMA 2 showed the lowest effectiveness in both prompts. Meanwhile, static code analyser results showed a generally low detection rate of API vulnerabilities. Snyk led the group with a 25% detection rate, while several analysers such as pylint, Pyre, and Trivy did not detect any vulnerabilities. These findings indicate that while static code analysers are valuable in certain contexts, their effectiveness remains lower than LLMs when appropriately prompted.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Compares 10 static code analyzers and 4 LLMs on 40 API vulnerabilities covering OWASP Top 10 API risks, with ChatGPT-4 achieving 62.5% detection rate versus Snyk's 25%.","summary_zh":"比较10个静态代码分析器和4个LLM在40个涵盖OWASP Top 10 API风险的API漏洞上的表现，ChatGPT-4检测率62.5%，而Snyk为25%。","abstract_zh":"在快速变化的数字技术世界中，应用程序编程接口（API）变得极其重要，它允许不同的软件应用之间进行通信。这种通信极大地增强了Web应用的功能和特性。这种在软件开发中更多使用API的转变标志着数字服务互连方式的重大变化。然而，这种进步也带来了某些安全问题。对API日益增长的依赖突出了采用能够早期检测和修复安全漏洞的工具的重要性。在本文中，我们详细介绍了一项研究，该研究使用了10个静态代码分析器和4个流行的大型语言模型（LLM），每个LLM使用两个不同的提示进行查询。我们的重点是评估它们检测源代码中40个API漏洞的能力，这些漏洞特别选择以代表OWASP Top 10 API安全风险中的每个类别。我们的结果显示这些工具的性能存在显著差异。ChatGPT 4是最有效的LLM，第一个提示的检测率为62.5%，第二个提示为42.5%。相比之下，LLaMA 2在两个提示中都表现出最低的有效性。同时，静态代码分析器的结果显示API漏洞检测率普遍较低。Snyk以25%的检测率领先，而pylint、Pyre和Trivy等分析器未检测到任何漏洞。这些发现表明，虽然静态代码分析器在某些上下文中有价值，但当适当提示时，其有效性仍低于LLM。","contributions":["Compares 10 static code analyzers and 4 LLMs on API vulnerability detection across OWASP Top 10 API Security Risks.","Curates a set of 40 API vulnerabilities representing each OWASP Top 10 API Security Risk category.","Finds ChatGPT 4 achieves 62.5% detection rate with first prompt and 42.5% with second prompt, the best among LLMs.","Shows LLaMA 2 has lowest effectiveness among tested LLMs for API vulnerability detection.","Demonstrates static analyzers have generally lower detection rates (Snyk best at 25%) than appropriately prompted LLMs."],"contributions_zh":["比较10个静态代码分析器和4个LLM在OWASP Top 10 API安全风险中的API漏洞检测能力。","策划了代表每个OWASP Top 10 API安全风险类别的40个API漏洞集合。","发现ChatGPT 4在第一个提示下检测率达62.5%，第二个提示下为42.5%，是LLM中最优的。","展示LLaMA 2在测试的LLM中API漏洞检测效果最低。","证明静态分析器的检测率普遍低于适当提示的LLM（Snyk最高为25%）。"],"experiment":{"language":[],"platform":["web"],"target_domain":["API"],"llm":["ChatGPT 4","LLaMA 2"],"model_family":["GPT","LLaMA"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":["Snyk","pylint","Pyre","Trivy"],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"40 API vulnerabilities","baselines":["Snyk","pylint","Pyre","Trivy"],"vulnerability_type":["OWASP Top 10 API Security Risks"],"key_results":"ChatGPT 4 achieved 62.5% detection rate (prompt 1) and 42.5% (prompt 2); Snyk best static analyzer at 25%; LLaMA 2 lowest LLM effectiveness","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@inproceedings{yildirim2024evaluating,\\n  title={Evaluating the Impact of Conventional Code Analysis Against Large Language Models in API Vulnerability Detection},\\n  author={Yildirim, Enes and others},\\n  booktitle={European Interdisciplinary Cybersecurity Conference},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"yin2024multitask","title":"Multitask-based evaluation of open-source llm on software vulnerability","authors":"Yin, Xin and Ni, Chao and Wang, Shaohua","year":2024,"venue":"IEEE Transactions on Software Engineering","abstract":"This paper proposes a pipeline for quantitatively evaluating interactive Large Language Models (LLMs) using publicly available datasets. We carry out an extensive technical evaluation of LLMs using Big-Vul covering four different common software vulnerability tasks. This evaluation assesses the multi-tasking capabilities of LLMs based on this dataset. We find that the existing state-of-the-art approaches and pre-trained Language Models (LMs) are generally superior to LLMs in software vulnerability detection. However, in software vulnerability assessment and location, certain LLMs (e.g., CodeLlama and WizardCoder) have demonstrated superior performance compared to pre-trained LMs, and providing more contextual information can enhance the vulnerability assessment capabilities of LLMs. Moreover, LLMs exhibit strong vulnerability description capabilities, but their tendency to produce excessive output significantly weakens their performance compared to pre-trained LMs. Overall, though LLMs perform well in some aspects, they still need improvement in understanding the subtle differences in code vulnerabilities and the ability to describe vulnerabilities to fully realize their potential. Our evaluation pipeline provides valuable insights into the capabilities of LLMs in handling software vulnerabilities.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["fine-tuning"],"summary":"Evaluates open-source LLMs (CodeLlama, WizardCoder) on four vulnerability tasks using Big-Vul dataset, finding LLMs excel at assessment and location but lag in detection.","summary_zh":"使用Big-Vul数据集评估开源LLM（CodeLlama、WizardCoder）在四项漏洞任务上的表现，发现LLM在评估和定位方面表现优异但在检测方面落后。","abstract_zh":"本文提出了一个使用公开可用数据集定量评估交互式大型语言模型（LLM）的管道。我们使用Big-Vul对LLM进行了广泛的技术评估，涵盖四种不同的常见软件漏洞任务。此评估基于该数据集评估了LLM的多任务能力。我们发现，现有的最先进方法和预训练语言模型（LM）在软件漏洞检测方面通常优于LLM。然而，在软件漏洞评估和定位方面，某些LLM（如CodeLlama和WizardCoder）已展示出优于预训练LM的表现，且提供更多上下文信息可以增强LLM的漏洞评估能力。此外，LLM展现出强大的漏洞描述能力，但其产生过多输出的倾向显著削弱了其与预训练LM相比的性能。总体而言，虽然LLM在某些方面表现良好，但在理解代码漏洞的细微差异和描述漏洞的能力方面仍需改进，以充分发挥其潜力。我们的评估管道为LLM处理软件漏洞的能力提供了有价值的见解。","contributions":["Proposes a pipeline for quantitatively evaluating interactive LLMs on software vulnerability tasks using public datasets.","Evaluates LLMs on four vulnerability tasks: detection, assessment, location, and description using Big-Vul dataset.","Finds state-of-the-art approaches and pre-trained LMs are generally superior to LLMs in vulnerability detection.","Shows CodeLlama and WizardCoder demonstrate superior performance in vulnerability assessment and location compared to pre-trained LMs.","Reveals LLMs have strong vulnerability description capabilities but excessive output weakens performance compared to pre-trained LMs."],"contributions_zh":["提出一个使用公开数据集定量评估交互式LLM在软件漏洞任务上的管道。","使用Big-Vul数据集评估LLM在四项漏洞任务上的表现：检测、评估、定位和描述。","发现最先进的方法和预训练语言模型在漏洞检测方面通常优于LLM。","展示CodeLlama和WizardCoder在漏洞评估和定位方面的表现优于预训练语言模型。","揭示LLM具有较强的漏洞描述能力，但过多输出削弱了其相对于预训练语言模型的性能。"],"experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["source code"],"llm":["CodeLlama","WizardCoder"],"model_family":["LLaMA","StarCoder"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["Big-Vul"],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Pre-trained LMs superior to LLMs in detection; CodeLlama and WizardCoder outperform pre-trained LMs in vulnerability assessment and location","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":2,"bibtex":"@article{yin2024multitask,\\n  title={Multitask-based evaluation of open-source llm on software vulnerability},\\n  author={Yin, Xin and Ni, Chao and Wang, Shaohua},\\n  journal={IEEE Transactions on Software Engineering},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"yu2024llmfuzzer","title":"LLM-Fuzzer: Scaling Assessment of Large Language Model Jailbreaks","authors":"","year":2024,"venue":"USENIX Security'24","abstract":"The jailbreak threat poses a significant concern for Large Language Models (LLMs), primarily due to their potential to generate content at scale. If not properly controlled, LLMs can be exploited to produce undesirable outcomes, including the dissemination of misinformation, offensive content, and other forms of harmful or unethical behavior. To tackle this pressing issue, researchers and developers often rely on red-team efforts to manually create adversarial inputs and prompts designed to push LLMs into generating harmful, biased, or inappropriate content. However, this approach encounters serious scalability challenges.\\nTo address these scalability issues, we introduce an automated solution for large-scale LLM jailbreak susceptibility assessment called LLM-Fuzzer. Inspired by fuzz testing, LLM-Fuzzer uses human-crafted jailbreak prompts as starting points. By employing carefully customized seed selection strategies and mutation mechanisms, LLM-Fuzzer generates additional jailbreak prompts tailored to specific LLMs. Our experiments show that LLM-Fuzzer-generated jailbreak prompts demonstrate significantly increased exploitability and transferability. This highlights that many open-source and commercial LLMs suffer from severe jailbreak issues, even after safety fine-tuning.","paperUrl":"https://www.usenix.org/system/files/usenixsecurity24-yu-jiahao.pdf","codeUrl":"https://github.com/sherdencooper/GPTFuzz","slidesUrl":"https://www.usenix.org/system/files/usenixsecurity24_slides-yu-jiahao.pdf","talkUrl":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Glj0_5_BI6A","categories":["fuzzing"],"subcategories":[],"summary":"Introduces LLM-Fuzzer, an automated fuzz-testing-inspired framework for scalable LLM jailbreak assessment using seed selection and mutation of jailbreak prompts.","summary_zh":"提出LLM-Fuzzer，一个受模糊测试启发的自动化框架，通过种子选择和越狱提示变异进行可扩展的LLM越狱评估。","abstract_zh":"越狱威胁对大型语言模型（LLM）构成重大关切，主要是因为它们有可能大规模生成内容。如果不加以适当控制，LLM可能被利用来产生不良结果，包括传播虚假信息、攻击性内容以及其他形式的有害或不道德行为。为了解决这一紧迫问题，研究人员和开发者通常依赖红队努力，手动创建对抗性输入和提示，旨在推动LLM生成有害、有偏见或不当的内容。然而，这种方法面临严重的可扩展性挑战。为了解决这些可扩展性问题，我们引入了一种名为LLM-Fuzzer的自动化解决方案，用于大规模LLM越狱易感性评估。受模糊测试启发，LLM-Fuzzer使用人工制作的越狱提示作为起始点。通过采用精心定制的种子选择策略和变异机制，LLM-Fuzzer生成针对特定LLM的额外越狱提示。我们的实验表明，LLM-Fuzzer生成的越狱提示展示了显著提高的可利用性和可迁移性。这突显了许多开源和商业LLM即使在安全微调后仍存在严重的越狱问题。","contributions":["Introduces LLM-Fuzzer, an automated framework for large-scale LLM jailbreak susceptibility assessment inspired by fuzz testing.","Uses human-crafted jailbreak prompts as seeds with customized selection strategies and mutation mechanisms.","Generates additional jailbreak prompts tailored to specific LLMs with increased exploitability and transferability.","Demonstrates that many open-source and commercial LLMs suffer from severe jailbreak issues even after safety fine-tuning."],"contributions_zh":["提出LLM-Fuzzer，一个受模糊测试启发的用于大规模LLM越狱易感性评估的自动化框架。","使用人工制作的越狱提示作为种子，配合定制的选择策略和变异机制。","生成针对特定LLM的额外越狱提示，具有更高的可利用性和可迁移性。","证明许多开源和商业LLM即使在安全微调后仍存在严重的越狱问题。"],"system_name":"LLM-Fuzzer","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["LLM safety"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":["LLM-Fuzzer"],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":["jailbreak"],"key_results":"LLM-Fuzzer-generated jailbreak prompts demonstrate significantly increased exploitability and transferability across open-source and commercial LLMs","real_world_impact":"","open_source":true,"cost":""},"recommendation":3,"bibtex":"@inproceedings{yu2024llmfuzzer,\\n  title={LLM-Fuzzer: Scaling Assessment of Large Language Model Jailbreaks},\\n  author={Yu, Jiahao and others},\\n  booktitle={USENIX Security Symposium},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"zhang2024empirical","title":"An Empirical Study of Automated Vulnerability Localization with Large Language Models","authors":"Zhang, Jian and Wang, Chong and Li, Anran and Sun, Weisong and Zhang, Cen and Ma, Wei and Liu, Yang","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2404.00287","abstract":"Recently, Automated Vulnerability Localization (AVL) has attracted much attention, aiming to facilitate diagnosis by pinpointing the lines of code responsible for discovered vulnerabilities. Large Language Models (LLMs) have shown potential in various domains, yet their effectiveness in vulnerability localization remains underexplored. In this work, we perform the first comprehensive study of LLMs for AVL. Our investigation encompasses 10+ leading LLMs suitable for code analysis, including ChatGPT and various open-source models, across three architectural types: encoder-only, encoder-decoder, and decoder-only, with model sizes ranging from 60M to 16B parameters. We explore the efficacy of these LLMs using 4 distinct paradigms: zero-shot learning, one-shot learning, discriminative fine-tuning, and generative fine-tuning. Our evaluation framework is applied to the BigVul-based dataset for C/C++, and an additional dataset comprising smart contract vulnerabilities. The results demonstrate that discriminative fine-tuning of LLMs can significantly outperform existing learning-based methods for AVL, while other paradigms prove less effective or unexpectedly ineffective for the task. We also identify challenges related to input length and unidirectional context in fine-tuning processes for encoders and decoders. We then introduce two remedial strategies: the sliding window and the right-forward embedding, both of which substantially enhance performance. Furthermore, our findings highlight certain generalization capabilities of LLMs across Common Weakness Enumerations (CWEs) and different projects, indicating a promising pathway toward their practical application in vulnerability localization.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["fine-tuning"],"summary":"First comprehensive study of 10+ LLMs (60M-16B parameters) for automated vulnerability localization using 4 paradigms on BigVul C/C++ and smart contract datasets.","summary_zh":"首次全面研究10多个LLM（60M-16B参数）用于自动漏洞定位，在BigVul C/C++和智能合约数据集上使用4种范式。","abstract_zh":"近年来，自动漏洞定位（AVL）引起了广泛关注，旨在通过精确定位导致已发现漏洞的代码行来促进诊断。大型语言模型（LLM）在各个领域展示了潜力，但它们在漏洞定位方面的有效性仍未得到充分探索。在这项工作中，我们对LLM用于AVL进行了首次全面研究。我们的调查涵盖了10多个适合代码分析的领先LLM，包括ChatGPT和各种开源模型，跨三种架构类型：仅编码器、编码器-解码器和仅解码器，模型大小从60M到16B参数。我们使用4种不同的范式探索这些LLM的效果：零样本学习、单样本学习、判别式微调和生成式微调。我们的评估框架应用于基于BigVul的C/C++数据集以及一个包含智能合约漏洞的额外数据集。结果表明，LLM的判别式微调可以显著优于现有的基于学习的AVL方法，而其他范式被证明效果较差或对该任务出人意料地无效。我们还识别了与微调过程中编码器和解码器的输入长度和单向上下文相关的挑战。然后我们引入了两种补救策略：滑动窗口和右向前嵌入，两者都显著提高了性能。此外，我们的发现强调了LLM在常见弱点枚举（CWE）和不同项目之间的某些泛化能力，表明它们在漏洞定位实际应用方面的前景。","contributions":["Performs the first comprehensive study of LLMs for Automated Vulnerability Localization (AVL) across 10+ LLMs.","Evaluates encoder-only, encoder-decoder, and decoder-only architectures with model sizes from 60M to 16B parameters.","Tests four paradigms: zero-shot learning, one-shot learning, discriminative fine-tuning, and generative fine-tuning.","Demonstrates discriminative fine-tuning significantly outperforms existing learning-based methods for AVL.","Introduces sliding window and right-forward embedding strategies to address input length and unidirectional context challenges."],"contributions_zh":["对10多个LLM进行了首次全面的自动漏洞定位（AVL）研究。","评估了编码器、编码器-解码器和解码器架构，模型大小从60M到16B参数。","测试了四种范式：零样本学习、单样本学习、判别式微调和生成式微调。","证明判别式微调显著优于现有的基于学习的AVL方法。","引入滑动窗口和右向前嵌入策略来解决输入长度和单向上下文挑战。"],"experiment":{"language":["C/C++","Solidity"],"platform":[],"target_domain":["source code","smart contract"],"llm":["ChatGPT"],"model_family":[],"model_size":["60M","16B"],"fine_tuning":true,"fine_tuning_method":"discriminative fine-tuning, generative fine-tuning","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["BigVul"],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"Discriminative fine-tuning significantly outperforms existing learning-based methods for AVL; sliding window and right-forward embedding strategies substantially enhance performance","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@article{zhang2024empirical,\\n  title={An Empirical Study of Automated Vulnerability Localization with Large Language Models},\\n  author={Zhang, Jian and Wang, Chong and Li, Anran and Sun, Weisong and Zhang, Cen and Ma, Wei and Liu, Yang},\\n  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2404.00287},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"zhang2024vtt","title":"VTT-LLM: Advancing Vulnerability-to-Tactic-and-Technique Mapping through Fine-Tuning of Large Language Model","authors":"Zhang, Chenhui and Wang, Le and Fan, Dunqiu and Zhu, Junyi and Zhou, Tang and Zeng, Liyi and Li, Zhaohua","year":2024,"venue":"Mathematics","abstract":"Vulnerabilities are often accompanied by cyberattacks. CVE is the largest repository of open vulnerabilities, which keeps expanding. ATT&CK models known multi-step attacks both tactically and technically and remains up to date. It is valuable to correlate the vulnerability in CVE with the corresponding tactic and technique of ATT&CK which exploit the vulnerability, for active defense. Mappings manually is not only time-consuming but also difficult to keep up-to-date. Existing language-based automated mapping methods do not utilize the information associated with attack behaviors outside of CVE and ATT&CK and are therefore ineffective. In this paper, we propose a novel framework named VTT-LLM for mapping Vulnerabilities to Tactics and Techniques based on Large Language Models, which consists of a generation model and a mapping model. In order to generate fine-tuning instructions for LLM, we create a template to extract knowledge of CWE (a standardized list of common weaknesses) and CAPEC (a standardized list of common attack patterns). We train the generation model of VTT-LLM by fine-tuning the LLM according to the above instructions. The generation model correlates vulnerability and attack through their descriptions. The mapping model transforms the descriptions of ATT&CK tactics and techniques into vectors through text embedding and further associates them with attacks through semantic matching. By leveraging the knowledge of CWE and CAPEC, VTT-LLM can eventually automate the process of linking vulnerabilities in CVE to the attack techniques and tactics of ATT&CK. Experiments on the latest public dataset, ChatGPT-VDMEval, show the effectiveness of VTT-LLM with an accuracy of 85.18%, which is 13.69% and 54.42% higher than the existing CVET and ChatGPT-based methods, respectively. In addition, compared to fine-tuning without outside knowledge, the accuracy of VTT-LLM with chain fine-tuning is 9.24% higher on average across different LLMs.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["fine-tuning"],"summary":"Proposes VTT-LLM framework mapping CVE vulnerabilities to ATT&CK tactics/techniques via LLM fine-tuning with CWE/CAPEC knowledge, achieving 85.18% accuracy.","summary_zh":"提出VTT-LLM框架，通过使用CWE/CAPEC知识微调LLM将CVE漏洞映射到ATT&CK战术/技术，在ChatGPT-VDMEval上达到85.18%的准确率。","abstract_zh":"漏洞通常伴随着网络攻击。CVE是最大的公开漏洞库，不断扩展。ATT&CK从战术和技术两个层面建模已知的多步攻击，并保持更新。将CVE中的漏洞与利用该漏洞的ATT&CK对应战术和技术关联起来，对于主动防御具有重要价值。手动映射不仅耗时，而且难以保持更新。现有的基于语言的自动映射方法没有利用CVE和ATT&CK之外与攻击行为相关的信息，因此效果不佳。在本文中，我们提出了一个名为VTT-LLM的新颖框架，用于基于大型语言模型将漏洞映射到战术和技术。该框架由一个生成模型和一个映射模型组成。为了生成LLM的微调指令，我们创建了一个模板来提取CWE（常见弱点的标准化列表）和CAPEC（常见攻击模式的标准化列表）的知识。我们根据上述指令微调LLM来训练VTT-LLM的生成模型。生成模型通过其描述关联漏洞和攻击。映射模型通过文本嵌入将ATT&CK战术和技术的描述转换为向量，并通过语义匹配进一步将其与攻击关联。通过利用CWE和CAPEC的知识，VTT-LLM最终可以自动化将CVE中的漏洞链接到ATT&CK的攻击技术和战术的过程。在最新公开数据集ChatGPT-VDMEval上的实验表明VTT-LLM的有效性，准确率为85.18%，分别比现有的CVET和基于ChatGPT的方法高13.69%和54.42%。此外，与不使用外部知识的微调相比，使用链式微调的VTT-LLM在不同LLM上的准确率平均高9.24%。","contributions":["Proposes VTT-LLM, a novel framework for mapping vulnerabilities to ATT&CK tactics and techniques using LLMs.","Creates fine-tuning instruction templates extracting knowledge from CWE and CAPEC standards.","Designs a two-stage architecture with a generation model correlating vulnerabilities and attacks, and a mapping model using text embedding and semantic matching.","Achieves 85.18% accuracy on ChatGPT-VDMEval dataset, 13.69% higher than CVET and 54.42% higher than ChatGPT-based methods.","Demonstrates chain fine-tuning with outside knowledge improves accuracy by 9.24% on average compared to fine-tuning without it."],"contributions_zh":["提出VTT-LLM，一种使用LLM将漏洞映射到ATT&CK战术和技术的新颖框架。","创建从CWE和CAPEC标准中提取知识的微调指令模板。","设计了一个两阶段架构，包括关联漏洞和攻击的生成模型，以及使用文本嵌入和语义匹配的映射模型。","在ChatGPT-VDMEval数据集上达到85.18%的准确率，比CVET高13.69%，比基于ChatGPT的方法高54.42%。","展示使用外部知识的链式微调比不使用外部知识的微调平均准确率高9.24%。"],"system_name":"VTT-LLM","experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["CVE-to-ATT&CK mapping"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":true,"fine_tuning_method":"chain fine-tuning with CWE/CAPEC knowledge","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":["ChatGPT-VDMEval","CVE","CWE","CAPEC","ATT&CK"],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":["CVET","ChatGPT"],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"85.18% accuracy on ChatGPT-VDMEval, 13.69% higher than CVET, 54.42% higher than ChatGPT; chain fine-tuning improves accuracy by 9.24% on average","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":2,"bibtex":"@article{zhang2024vtt,\\n  title={VTT-LLM: Advancing Vulnerability-to-Tactic-and-Technique Mapping through Fine-Tuning of Large Language Model},\\n  author={Zhang, Chenhui and Wang, Le and Fan, Dunqiu and Zhu, Junyi and Zhou, Tang and Zeng, Liyi and Li, Zhaohua},\\n  journal={Mathematics},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"zhou2024comparison","title":"Comparison of static application security testing tools and large language models for repo-level vulnerability detection","authors":"Zhou, Xin and Tran, Duc-Manh and Le-Cong, Thanh and Zhang, Ting and Irsan, Ivana Clairine and Sumarlin, Joshua and Le, Bach and Lo, David","year":2024,"venue":"arXiv preprint arXiv:2407.16235","abstract":"Software vulnerabilities pose significant security challenges and potential risks to society, necessitating extensive efforts in automated vulnerability detection. There are two popular lines of work to address automated vulnerability detection. On one hand, Static Application Security Testing (SAST) is usually utilized to scan source code for security vulnerabilities, especially in industries. On the other hand, deep learning (DL)-based methods, especially since the introduction of large language models (LLMs), have demonstrated their potential in software vulnerability detection. However, there is no comparative study between SAST tools and LLMs, aiming to determine their effectiveness in vulnerability detection, understand the pros and cons of both SAST and LLMs, and explore the potential combination of these two families of approaches. In this paper, we compared 15 diverse SAST tools with 12 popular or state-of-the-art open-source LLMs in detecting software vulnerabilities from repositories of three popular programming languages: Java, C, and Python. The experimental results showed that SAST tools obtain low vulnerability detection rates with relatively low false positives, while LLMs can detect up 90% to 100% of vulnerabilities but suffer from high false positives. By further ensembling the SAST tools and LLMs, the drawbacks of both SAST tools and LLMs can be mitigated to some extent. Our analysis sheds light on both the current progress and future directions for software vulnerability detection.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["fine-tuning"],"summary":"Compares 15 SAST tools with 12 open-source LLMs for repo-level vulnerability detection in Java, C, and Python, finding LLMs detect 90-100% but with high false positives.","summary_zh":"比较15个SAST工具和12个开源LLM在Java、C和Python仓库级漏洞检测中的表现，发现LLM检测率达90-100%但误报率高。","abstract_zh":"软件漏洞给安全带来重大挑战并对社会构成潜在风险，需要大量自动化漏洞检测的努力。有两条流行的研究路线来解决自动化漏洞检测。一方面，静态应用安全测试（SAST）通常用于扫描源代码中的安全漏洞，特别是在工业界。另一方面，基于深度学习（DL）的方法，特别是随着大型语言模型（LLM）的引入，已展示了其在软件漏洞检测方面的潜力。然而，目前没有SAST工具与LLM之间的比较研究来确定它们在漏洞检测方面的有效性、了解SAST和LLM的优缺点，以及探索这两类方法的潜在组合。在本文中，我们比较了15种不同的SAST工具和12个流行或最先进的开源LLM在检测三种流行编程语言（Java、C和Python）仓库中的软件漏洞方面的表现。实验结果表明，SAST工具获得的漏洞检测率较低但误报率相对较低，而LLM可以检测到90%到100%的漏洞但误报率较高。通过进一步集成SAST工具和LLM，可以在一定程度上缓解两者的缺点。我们的分析揭示了软件漏洞检测的当前进展和未来方向。","contributions":["Provides the first comparative study between SAST tools and LLMs for vulnerability detection.","Compares 15 diverse SAST tools with 12 popular or state-of-the-art open-source LLMs.","Evaluates on repositories from three programming languages: Java, C, and Python.","Finds SAST tools obtain low detection rates with low false positives, while LLMs detect 90-100% of vulnerabilities with high false positives.","Demonstrates that ensembling SAST tools and LLMs can mitigate drawbacks of both approaches."],"contributions_zh":["提供了SAST工具与LLM在漏洞检测方面的首次比较研究。","比较了15种不同的SAST工具和12个流行或最先进的开源LLM。","在Java、C和Python三种编程语言的仓库上进行评估。","发现SAST工具检测率低但误报低，而LLM检测率达90-100%但误报率高。","证明将SAST工具与LLM集成可以在一定程度上缓解两种方法的缺点。"],"experiment":{"language":["Java","C","Python"],"platform":[],"target_domain":["source code","repository-level"],"llm":[],"model_family":[],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"SAST tools have low detection rates with low false positives; LLMs detect 90-100% of vulnerabilities but with high false positives; ensembling mitigates both drawbacks","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":1,"bibtex":"@article{zhou2024comparison,\\n  title={Comparison of static application security testing tools and large language models for repo-level vulnerability detection},\\n  author={Zhou, Xin and Tran, Duc-Manh and Le-Cong, Thanh and Zhang, Ting and Irsan, Ivana Clairine and Sumarlin, Joshua and Le, Bach and Lo, David},\\n  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2407.16235},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"},{"id":"zhou2024large","title":"Large language model for vulnerability detection: Emerging results and future directions","authors":"Zhou, Xin and Zhang, Ting and Lo, David","year":2024,"venue":"Proceedings of the 2024 ACM/IEEE 44th International Conference on Software Engineering: New Ideas and Emerging Results","abstract":"Previous learning-based vulnerability detection methods relied on either medium-sized pre-trained models or smaller neural networks from scratch. Recent advancements in Large Pre-Trained Language Models (LLMs) have showcased remarkable few-shot learning capabilities in various tasks. However, the effectiveness of LLMs in detecting software vulnerabilities is largely unexplored. This paper aims to bridge this gap by exploring how LLMs perform with various prompts, particularly focusing on two state-of-the-art LLMs: GPT-3.5 and GPT-4. Our experimental results showed that GPT-3.5 achieves competitive performance with the prior state-of-the-art vulnerability detection approach and GPT-4 consistently outperformed the state-of-the-art.","paperUrl":"","codeUrl":"","slidesUrl":"","talkUrl":"","categories":["vulnerability-detection"],"subcategories":["fine-tuning"],"summary":"Explores GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 for vulnerability detection with various prompts, finding GPT-3.5 competitive with and GPT-4 consistently outperforming prior state-of-the-art.","summary_zh":"探索GPT-3.5和GPT-4使用各种提示进行漏洞检测，发现GPT-3.5与先前最优方法持平，GPT-4则始终超越先前最优方法。","abstract_zh":"先前基于学习的漏洞检测方法依赖于中等大小的预训练模型或从头训练的较小神经网络。大型预训练语言模型（LLM）的最新进展在各种任务中展示了出色的少样本学习能力。然而，LLM在检测软件漏洞方面的有效性在很大程度上尚未被探索。本文旨在通过探索LLM在各种提示下的表现来填补这一空白，特别关注两个最先进的LLM：GPT-3.5和GPT-4。我们的实验结果表明，GPT-3.5达到了与先前最优漏洞检测方法持平的性能，而GPT-4始终优于最优方法。","contributions":["Explores the effectiveness of LLMs (GPT-3.5 and GPT-4) for software vulnerability detection with various prompting strategies.","Bridges the gap in understanding LLM capabilities for vulnerability detection compared to smaller pre-trained models.","Shows GPT-3.5 achieves competitive performance with prior state-of-the-art vulnerability detection approaches.","Demonstrates GPT-4 consistently outperforms the state-of-the-art in vulnerability detection."],"contributions_zh":["探索LLM（GPT-3.5和GPT-4）使用各种提示策略进行软件漏洞检测的有效性。","填补了理解LLM漏洞检测能力与较小预训练模型相比的空白。","展示GPT-3.5达到了与先前最优漏洞检测方法持平的性能。","证明GPT-4在漏洞检测方面始终优于最优方法。"],"experiment":{"language":[],"platform":[],"target_domain":["source code"],"llm":["GPT-3.5","GPT-4"],"model_family":["GPT"],"model_size":[],"fine_tuning":false,"fine_tuning_method":"","fuzzer":[],"static_tool":[],"dataset":[],"benchmark_size":"","baselines":[],"vulnerability_type":[],"key_results":"GPT-3.5 achieves competitive performance with prior state-of-the-art; GPT-4 consistently outperforms state-of-the-art","real_world_impact":"","open_source":false,"cost":""},"recommendation":3,"bibtex":"@inproceedings{zhou2024large,\\n  title={Large language model for vulnerability detection: Emerging results and future directions},\\n  author={Zhou, Xin and Zhang, Ting and Lo, David},\\n  booktitle={Proceedings of the 2024 ACM/IEEE 44th International Conference on Software Engineering: New Ideas and Emerging Results},\\n  year={2024}\\n}"}]`);export{e as p};
